methods.description: Removes a collision exception so the ray does report collisions with the specified [RID].

methods.name: set_cast_to
methods.description: Sets the ray destination point, so that the ray will test from the ray's origin to [code]local_point[/code].

methods.name: set_collision_layer
methods.description: Set the mask to filter objects. Only objects with at least the same mask element set will be detected.

methods.name: set_enabled
methods.description: Enables the RayCast2D. Only enabled raycasts will be able to query the space and report collisions.

methods.name: set_type_mask
methods.description: Set the types of objects to detect. For [code]mask[/code] use a logic sum (OR operation) of constants defined in [PhysicsDirectSpaceState], eg. [code]PhysicsDirectSpaceState.TYPE_MASK_STATIC_BODY | PhysicsDirectSpaceState.TYPE_MASK_KINEMATIC_BODY[/code] to detect only those two types.

properties.name: cast_to
properties.description: The ray's destination point, relative to the RayCast's [code]position[/code].

properties.name: collision_layer
properties.description: The RayCast's collision layer(s). Only bodies in the same collision layer(s) will be detected.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], collisions will be reported. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: type_mask
properties.description:
Object types to detect using a logical sum (OR operation) of type constants defined in [Physics2DDirectSpaceState].
			Example:
			[codeblock]
			RayCast.type_mask = Physics2DDirectSpaceState.TYPE_MASK_STATIC_BODY | Physics2DDirectSpaceState.TYPE_MASK_KINEMATIC_BODY
			[/codeblock]

AudioServer.name: AudioServer
AudioServer.brief_description: Server interface for low level audio access.
AudioServer.description: AudioServer is a low level server interface for audio access. It is in charge of creating sample data (playable audio) as well as its playback via a voice interface.

methods.name: add_bus
methods.description: Adds a bus at [code]at_position[/code].

methods.name: add_bus_effect
methods.description: Adds an [AudioEffect] effect to the bus [code]bus_idx[/code] at [code]at_position[/code].

methods.name: generate_bus_layout
methods.description: Generates an [AudioBusLayout] using the available busses and effects.

methods.name: get_bus_count
methods.description: Returns the number of available busses.

methods.name: get_bus_effect
methods.description: Returns the [AudioEffect] at position [code]effect_idx[/code] in bus [code]bus_idx[/code].

methods.name: get_bus_effect_count
methods.description: Returns the number of effects on the bus at [code]bus_idx[/code].

methods.name: get_bus_index
methods.description: Returns the index of the bus with the name [code]bus_name[/code].

methods.name: get_bus_name
methods.description: Returns the name of the bus with the index [code]bus_idx[/code].

methods.name: get_bus_peak_volume_left_db
methods.description: Returns the peak volume of the left speaker at bus index [code]bus_idx[/code] and channel index [code]channel[/code].

methods.name: get_bus_peak_volume_right_db
methods.description: Returns the peak volume of the right speaker at bus index [code]bus_idx[/code] and channel index [code]channel[/code].

methods.name: get_bus_send
methods.description: Returns the name of the bus that the bus at index [code]bus_idx[/code] sends to.

methods.name: get_bus_volume_db
methods.description: Returns the volume of the bus at index [code]bus_idx[/code] in dB.

methods.name: get_mix_rate
methods.description: Returns the sample rate at the output of the audioserver.

methods.name: get_speaker_mode
methods.description: Returns the speaker configuration.

methods.name: is_bus_bypassing_effects
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the bus at index [code]bus_idx[/code] is bypassing effects.

methods.name: is_bus_effect_enabled
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the effect at index [code]effect_idx[/code] on the bus at index [code]bus_idx[/code] is enabled.

methods.name: is_bus_mute
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the bus at index [code]bus_idx[/code] is muted.

methods.name: is_bus_solo
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the bus at index [code]bus_idx[/code] is in solo mode.

methods.name: lock
methods.description: Locks the audio drivers mainloop. Remember to unlock it afterwards.

methods.name: move_bus
methods.description: Moves the bus from index [code]index[/code] to index [code]to_index[/code].

methods.name: remove_bus
methods.description: Removes the bus at index [code]index[/code].

methods.name: remove_bus_effect
methods.description: Removes the effect at index [code]effect_idx[/code] from the bus at index [code]bus_idx[/code].

methods.name: set_bus_bypass_effects
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the bus at index [code]bus_idx[/code] is bypassing effects.

methods.name: set_bus_count
methods.description: Adds and removes busses to make the number of busses match [code]amount[/code].

methods.name: set_bus_effect_enabled
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the effect at index [code]effect_idx[/code] on the bus at index [code]bus_idx[/code] is enabled.

methods.name: set_bus_layout
methods.description: Overwrites the currently used [AudioBusLayout].

methods.name: set_bus_mute
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the bus at index [code]bus_idx[/code] is muted.

methods.name: set_bus_name
methods.description: Sets the name of the bus at index [code]bus_idx[/code] to [code]name[/code].

methods.name: set_bus_send
methods.description: Connects the output of the bus at [code]bus_idx[/code] to the bus named [code]send[/send].

methods.name: set_bus_solo
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the bus at index [code]bus_idx[/code] is in solo mode.

methods.name: set_bus_volume_db
methods.description: Sets the volume of the bus at index [code]bus_idx[/code] to [code]volume_db[/code].

methods.name: swap_bus_effects
methods.description: Swaps the position of two effects in bus [code]bus_idx[/code].

methods.name: unlock
methods.description: Unlocks the audiodriver's main loop. After locking it always unlock it.

signals.name: bus_layout_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the [AudioBusLayout] changes.

constants.name: SPEAKER_MODE_STEREO
constants.description: Two or fewer speakers are detected.

constants.name: SPEAKER_SURROUND_51
constants.description: A 5.1 channel surround setup detected.

constants.name: SPEAKER_SURROUND_71

Sprite.name: Sprite
Sprite.description: A node that displays a 2D texture. The texture displayed can be a region from a larger atlas texture, or a frame from a sprite sheet animation.

methods.name: get_hframes

methods.name: get_offset

methods.name: get_region_rect

methods.name: get_texture
methods.description: Return the base texture for the sprite.

methods.name: get_vframes
methods.description: Return the amount of vertical frames. See [method set_vframes].

methods.name: is_centered
methods.description: Return if the sprite is centered at the local origin.

methods.name: is_flipped_h

methods.name: is_flipped_v
methods.description: Return true if the sprite is flipped vertically.

methods.name: is_region
methods.description: Return if the sprite reads from a region.

methods.name: set_centered

methods.name: set_flip_h
methods.description: Set true to flip the sprite horizontally.

methods.name: set_flip_v
methods.description: Set true to flip the sprite vertically.

methods.name: set_frame
methods.description: Set the texture frame for a sprite-sheet, works when vframes or hframes are greater than 1.

methods.name: set_hframes
methods.description: Set the amount of horizontal frames and converts the sprite into a sprite-sheet. This is useful for animation.

methods.name: set_offset
methods.description: Set the sprite draw offset, useful for setting rotation pivots.

methods.name: set_region
methods.description: Set the sprite as a sub-region of a bigger texture. Useful for texture-atlases.

methods.name: set_region_rect
methods.description: Set the region rect to read from.

methods.name: set_texture
methods.description: Set the base texture for the sprite.

methods.name: set_vframes
methods.description: Set the amount of vertical frames and converts the sprite into a sprite-sheet. This is useful for animation.

signals.name: frame_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the [member frame] changes.

signals.name: texture_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the [member texture] changes.

properties.name: centered

properties.name: normal_map

properties.name: offset

properties.name: region_enabled

properties.name: region_filter_clip

properties.name: region_rect

properties.name: texture

properties.name: vframes

MeshInstance.name: MeshInstance
MeshInstance.brief_description: Node that instances meshes into a scenario.
MeshInstance.description: MeshInstance is a [Node] that takes a [Mesh] resource and adds it to the current scenario by creating an instance of it. This is the class most often used to get 3D geometry rendered and can be used to instance a single [Mesh] in many places. This allows to reuse geometry and save on resources. When a [Mesh] has to be instanced more than thousands of times at close proximity, consider using a [MultiMesh] in a [MultiMeshInstance] instead.

methods.name: create_convex_collision
methods.description: This helper creates a [StaticBody] child [Node] with a [ConvexPolygonShape] [CollisionShape] calculated from the mesh geometry. It's mainly used for testing.

methods.name: create_trimesh_collision
methods.description: This helper creates a [StaticBody] child [Node] with a [ConcavePolygonShape] [CollisionShape] calculated from the mesh geometry. It's mainly used for testing.

methods.name: get_mesh
methods.description: Returns the current [Mesh] resource for the instance.

methods.name: get_surface_material
methods.description: Returns the [Material] for a surface of the [Mesh] resource.

methods.name: set_surface_material
methods.description: Sets the [Material] for a surface of the [Mesh] resource.

properties.name: mesh
properties.description: The [Mesh] resource for the instance.

properties.name: skeleton
properties.description: [NodePath] to the [Skeleton] associated with the instance.

BoneAttachment.name: BoneAttachment
BoneAttachment.brief_description: A node that will attach to a bone.
BoneAttachment.description: This node must be the child of a [Skeleton] node. You can then select a bone for this node to attach to. The BoneAttachment node will copy the transform of the selected bone.

methods.name: get_bone_name
methods.description: Returns the name of the bone node attached to.

methods.name: set_bone_name
methods.description: Changes the name of the bone node

MainLoop.name: MainLoop
MainLoop.brief_description: Main loop is the abstract main loop base class.
MainLoop.description: Main loop is the abstract main loop base class. All other main loop classes are derived from it. Upon application start, a [MainLoop] has to be provided to OS, else the application will exit. This happens automatically (and a [SceneTree] is created), unless a main [Script] is supplied, which may or not create and return a [MainLoop].

methods.name: _finalize
methods.description: Called before the program exits.

methods.name: _idle
methods.description: Called each idle frame with time since last call as an only argument.

methods.name: _initialize
methods.description: Called once during initialization.

SplitContainer.name: SplitContainer
SplitContainer.description: Container for splitting two controls vertically or horizontally, with a grabber that allows adjusting the split offset or ratio.

methods.name: get_dragger_visibility
methods.description: Return visibility of the split dragger (one of [DRAGGER_VISIBLE], [DRAGGER_HIDDEN] or [DRAGGER_HIDDEN_COLLAPSED]).

methods.name: get_split_offset
methods.description: Return the split offset.

methods.name: is_collapsed
methods.description: Return true if the split is collapsed.

methods.name: set_collapsed
methods.description: Set if the split must be collapsed.

methods.name: set_dragger_visibility
methods.description: Set visibility of the split dragger ([i]mode[/i] must be one of [DRAGGER_VISIBLE], [DRAGGER_HIDDEN] or [DRAGGER_HIDDEN_COLLAPSED]).

methods.name: set_split_offset
methods.description: Set the split offset.

signals.name: dragged
signals.description: Emitted when the dragger is dragged by user.

constants.name: DRAGGER_VISIBLE
constants.description: The split dragger is visible.

constants.name: DRAGGER_HIDDEN
constants.description: The split dragger is invisible.

constants.name: DRAGGER_HIDDEN_COLLAPSED
constants.description: The split dragger is invisible and collapsed.

Engine.name: Engine
Engine.description: The [Engine] class allows you to query and modify the game's run-time parameters, such as frames per second, time scale, and others.

methods.name: get_frames_drawn
methods.description: Returns the total number of frames drawn.

methods.name: get_frames_per_second
methods.description: Returns the frames per second of the running game.

methods.name: get_iterations_per_second
methods.description: Returns the number of fixed iterations per second (for fixed process and physics).

methods.name: get_main_loop
methods.description: Returns the main loop object (see [MainLoop] and [SceneTree]).

methods.name: get_target_fps
methods.description: Returns the desired frames per second. If the hardware cannot keep up, this setting may not be respected. It defaults to 0, which indicates no limit.

methods.name: get_time_scale
methods.description: Returns how fast or slow the in-game clock ticks versus the real life one. It defaults to 1.0. A value of 2.0 means the game moves twice as fast as real life, whilst a value of 0.5 means the game moves at half the regular speed.

methods.name: get_version_info
methods.description:
Returns the current engine version information in a Dictionary.

				"major"    - Holds the major version number as a String
				"minor"    - Holds the minor version number as a String
				"patch"    - Holds the patch version number as a String
				"status"   - Holds the status (e.g. "beta", "rc1", "rc2", ... "stable") as a String
				"revision" - Holds the revision (e.g. "custom-build") as a String
				"string"   - major + minor + patch + status + revision in a single String

methods.name: is_editor_hint
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the editor is running.

methods.name: is_in_physics_frame
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the game is inside the fixed process and physics phase of the game loop.

methods.name: set_editor_hint
methods.description: Sets the running inside the editor hint if [code]enabled[/code] is [code]true[/code].

methods.name: set_iterations_per_second
methods.description: Sets the number of fixed iterations per second (for fixed process and physics).

methods.name: set_target_fps
methods.description: Sets the target frames per second.

methods.name: set_time_scale
methods.description: Sets the time scale.

ConfirmationDialog.name: ConfirmationDialog
ConfirmationDialog.description: Dialog for confirmation of actions. This dialog inherits from [AcceptDialog], but has by default an OK and Cancel button (in host OS order).

methods.name: get_cancel
methods.description: Return the cancel button.

Position2D.name: Position2D
Position2D.description: Generic 2D Position hint for editing. It's just like a plain [Node2D] but displays as a cross in the 2D-Editor at all times.

SpinBox.name: SpinBox
SpinBox.description: SpinBox is a numerical input text field. It allows entering integers and floats.

methods.name: get_suffix
methods.description: Return the specific suffix.

methods.name: is_editable
methods.description: Return if the spinbox is editable.

methods.name: set_editable
methods.description: Set whether the spinbox is editable.

methods.name: set_prefix
methods.description: Set a prefix.

methods.name: set_suffix
methods.description: Set a specific suffix.

AudioEffect.name: AudioEffect
AudioEffect.description: Base resource for audio bus. Applies an audio effect on the bus that the resource is applied on.

methods.name: is_refusing_new_connections
methods.description: Return whether this [NetworkedMultiplayerPeer] is refusing new connections.

methods.name: set_refuse_new_connections
methods.description: If [code]endable[/code] is true, this [NetworkedMultiplayerPeer] will refuse new connections.

signals.name: connection_failed
signals.description: Emitted when failed to connect to server.

signals.name: connection_succeeded
signals.description: Emitted when successfully connected to server.

signals.name: peer_connected
signals.description: Emitted by the server when a client is connected.

signals.name: peer_disconnected
signals.description: Emitted by the server when a client is disconnected.

signals.name: server_disconnected
signals.description: Emitted by clients when server is disconnected.

AudioEffectChorus.name: AudioEffectChorus
AudioEffectChorus.description: Adds a chorus audio effect. The effect applies a filter with voices to duplicate the audio source and manipulate it through the filter.

methods.name: get_dry
methods.description: Returns the set dry ratio.

methods.name: get_voice_count
methods.description: Returns the set voice count.

methods.name: get_voice_cutoff_hz
methods.description: Returns the voice's set cutoff frequency.

methods.name: get_voice_delay_ms
methods.description: Returns the voice's set delay.

methods.name: get_voice_depth_ms
methods.description: Returns the voice's set filter depth.

methods.name: get_voice_level_db
methods.description: Returns the voice's set maximum volume.

methods.name: get_voice_pan
methods.description: Returns the voice's set pan.

methods.name: get_voice_rate_hz
methods.description: Returns the voice filter's set rate in cycles.

methods.name: get_wet
methods.description: Returns the set applied wetness of the effect.

methods.name: set_dry
methods.description: Returns the set applied dryness of the effect.

methods.name: set_voice_count
methods.description: Set the number of voices in the effect's filter.

methods.name: set_voice_cutoff_hz
methods.description: Set the cutoff frequency of the voice. The maximum frequency the voice may affect.

methods.name: set_voice_delay_ms
methods.description: Set the delay of the voice's signal.

methods.name: set_voice_depth_ms
methods.description: Set the filter depth of the voice's signal.

methods.name: set_voice_level_db
methods.description: Set the volume level of the voice.

methods.name: set_voice_pan
methods.description: Set the pan level of the voice.

methods.name: set_voice_rate_hz
methods.description: Set the voice filter's rate.

methods.name: set_wet
methods.description: Set the amount of effect.

properties.name: dry
properties.description: The effect's raw signal.

properties.name: voice/1/cutoff_hz
properties.description: The voice's cutoff frequency.

properties.name: voice/1/delay_ms
properties.description: The voice's signal delay.

properties.name: voice/1/depth_ms
properties.description: The voice filter's depth.

properties.name: voice/1/level_db
properties.description: The voice's volume.

properties.name: voice/1/pan
properties.description: The voice's pan level.

properties.name: voice/1/rate_hz
properties.description: The voice's filter rate.

properties.name: voice/2/cutoff_hz
properties.description: The voice's cutoff frequency.

properties.name: voice/2/delay_ms
properties.description: The voice's signal delay.

properties.name: voice/2/depth_ms
properties.description: The voice filter's depth.

properties.name: voice/2/level_db
properties.description: The voice's volume.

properties.name: voice/2/pan
properties.description: The voice's pan level.

properties.name: voice/2/rate_hz
properties.description: The voice's filter rate.

properties.name: voice/3/cutoff_hz
properties.description: The voice's cutoff frequency.

properties.name: voice/3/delay_ms
properties.description: The voice's signal delay.

properties.name: voice/3/depth_ms
properties.description: The voice filter's depth.

properties.name: voice/3/level_db
properties.description: The voice's volume.

properties.name: voice/3/pan
properties.description: The voice's pan level.

properties.name: voice/3/rate_hz
properties.description: The voice's filter rate.

properties.name: voice/4/cutoff_hz
properties.description: The voice's cutoff frequency.

properties.name: voice/4/delay_ms
properties.description: The voice's signal delay.

properties.name: voice/4/depth_ms
properties.description: The voice filter's depth.

properties.name: voice/4/level_db
properties.description: The voice's volume.

properties.name: voice/4/pan
properties.description: The voice's pan level.

properties.name: voice/4/rate_hz
properties.description: The voice's filter rate.

properties.name: voice_count
properties.description: The amount of voices in the effect.

properties.name: wet
properties.description: The effect's processed signal.

World2D.name: World2D
World2D.brief_description: Class that has everything pertaining to a 2D world.
World2D.description: Class that has everything pertaining to a 2D world. A physics space, a visual scenario and a sound space. 2D nodes register their resources into the current 2D world.

methods.name: get_canvas
methods.description: Retrieve the [RID] of this world's canvas resource. Used by the [VisualServer] for 2D drawing.

methods.name: get_direct_space_state
methods.description: Retrieve the state of this world's physics space. This allows arbitrary querying for collision.

methods.name: get_space
methods.description: Retrieve the [RID] of this world's physics space resource. Used by the [Physics2DServer] for 2D physics, treating it as both a space and an area.

AudioEffectEQ.name: AudioEffectEQ
AudioEffectEQ.brief_description:
Base class for audio equalizers. Gives you control over frequencies.
		Use it to create a custom equalizer if [AudioEffectEQ6], [AudioEffectEQ10] or [AudioEffectEQ21] don't fit your needs.
AudioEffectEQ.description: AudioEffectEQ gives you control over frequencies. Use it to compensate for existing deficiencies in audio. AudioEffectEQ are very useful on the Master Bus to completely master a mix and give it character. They are also very useful when a game is run on a mobile device, to adjust the mix to that kind of speakers (it can be added but disabled when headphones are plugged).

methods.name: get_band_count
methods.description: Returns the number of bands of the equalizer.

methods.name: get_band_gain_db
methods.description: Returns the band's gain at the specified index, in dB.

methods.name: set_band_gain_db
methods.description: Sets band's gain at the specified index, in dB.

StyleBoxTexture.name: StyleBoxTexture
StyleBoxTexture.description: Texture Based 3x3 scale style. This stylebox performs a 3x3 scaling of a texture, where only the center cell is fully stretched. This allows for the easy creation of bordered styles.

BackBufferCopy.name: BackBufferCopy
BackBufferCopy.brief_description: Copies a region of the screen (or the whole screen) to a buffer so it can be accessed with the texscreen() shader instruction.
BackBufferCopy.description: Node for back-buffering the currently displayed screen. The region defined in the BackBufferCopy node is bufferized with the content of the screen it covers, or the entire screen according to the copy mode set. Accessing this buffer is done with the texscreen() shader instruction.

methods.name: get_copy_mode
methods.description: Return the copy mode currently applied to the BackBufferCopy. See [code]COPY_MODE_*[/code] constants.

methods.name: get_rect
methods.description: Return the area covered by the BackBufferCopy.

methods.name: set_copy_mode
methods.description: Set the copy mode of the BackBufferCopy. See [code]COPY_MODE_*[/code] constants.

methods.name: set_rect
methods.description: Defines the area covered by the BackBufferCopy.

constants.name: COPY_MODE_DISABLED
constants.description: Disables the buffering mode. This means the BackBufferCopy node will directly use the portion of screen it covers.

constants.name: COPY_MODE_RECT
constants.description: BackBufferCopy buffers a rectangular region.

constants.name: COPY_MODE_VIEWPORT
constants.description: BackBufferCopy buffers the entire screen.

properties.name: copy_mode
properties.description: Buffer mode. See [code]COPY_MODE_*[/code] constants.

properties.name: rect
properties.description: The area covered by the BackBufferCopy. Only used if [code]copy_mode[/code] is [code]COPY_MODE_RECT[/code].

ARVRPositionalTracker.name: ARVRPositionalTracker
ARVRPositionalTracker.description:
An instance of this object represents a device that is tracked such as a controller or anchor point. HMDs aren't represented here as they are fully handled internally.
		As controllers are turned on and the AR/VR interface detects them instances of this object are automatically added to this list of active tracking objects accessible through the ARVRServer
		The ARVRController and ARVRAnchor both consume objects of this type and should be the objects you use in game. The positional trackers are just the under the hood objects that make this all work and are mostly exposed so GDNative based interfaces can interact with them.

methods.name: get_joy_id
methods.description: If this is a controller that is being tracked the controller will also be represented by a joystick entry with this id.

methods.name: get_name
methods.description: If available this returns the name of the controller or anchor point.

methods.name: get_orientation
methods.description: Returns the orientation matrix of the controller.

methods.name: get_position
methods.description: Returns the position of the controller adjusted by world scale.

methods.name: get_tracks_orientation
methods.description: Returns true if the orientation of this device is being tracked.

methods.name: get_tracks_position
methods.description: Returns true if the position of this device is being tracked.

methods.name: get_transform
methods.description: Returns the transform combining the orientation and position of this device.

methods.name: get_type
methods.description: Type of tracker.

VisualScriptConstant.name: VisualScriptConstant
VisualScriptConstant.brief_description: A Visual Script node which returns a constant value.
VisualScriptConstant.description: A Visual Script node which returns the specified constant value.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The constant's type.

properties.name: value
properties.description: The constant's value.

Variant.name: Variant
Variant.brief_description: The most important data type in Godot.
Variant.description: A Variant takes up only 20 bytes and can store almost any engine datatype inside of it. Variants are rarely used to hold information for long periods of time, instead they are used mainly for communication, editing, serialization and moving data around.

CollisionShape.name: CollisionShape
CollisionShape.brief_description: Node that represents collision shape data in 3D space.
CollisionShape.description: Editor facility for creating and editing collision shapes in 3D space. You can use this node to represent all sorts of collision shapes, for example, add this to an [Area] to give it a detection shape, or add it to a [PhysicsBody] to give create solid object. [b]IMPORTANT[/b]: this is an Editor-only helper to create shapes, use [method get_shape] to get the actual shape.

methods.name: make_convex_from_brothers
methods.description: Sets the collision shape's shape to the addition of all its convexed [MeshInstance] siblings geometry.

methods.name: resource_changed
methods.description: If this method exists within a script it will be called whenever the shape resource has been modified.

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: A disabled collision shape has no effect in the world.

properties.name: shape
properties.description: The actual shape owned by this collision shape.

ARVRController.name: ARVRController
ARVRController.brief_description: A spatial node representing a spatially tracked controller.
ARVRController.description:
This is a helper spatial node that is linked to the tracking of controllers. It also offers several handy pass throughs to the state of buttons and such on the controllers.
		Controllers are linked by their id. You can create controller nodes before the controllers are available. Say your game always uses two controllers (one for each hand) you can predefine the controllers with id 1 and 2 and they will become active as soon as the controllers are identified. If you expect additional controllers to be used you should react to the signals and add ARVRController nodes to your scene.
		The position of the controller node is automatically updated by the ARVR Server. This makes this node ideal to add child  nodes to visualise the controller.

methods.name: get_controller_id
methods.description: Returns the controller id currently assigned to this node.

methods.name: get_controller_name
methods.description: If active, returns the name of the associated controller if provided by the AR/VR SDK used.

methods.name: get_is_active
methods.description: Returns true if the controller bound to this node is currently active and being tracked.

methods.name: get_joystick_axis
methods.description: Returns the value of the given axis for things like triggers, touchpads, etc. that are embedded into the controller.

methods.name: get_joystick_id
methods.description: Returns the ID of the joystick object bound to this. Every controller tracked by the ARVR Server that has buttons and axis will also be registered as a joystick within Godot. This means that all the normal joystick tracking and input mapping will work for buttons and axis found on the AR/VR controllers. This ID is purely offered as information so you can link up the controller with its joystick entry.

methods.name: is_button_pressed
methods.description: Is the given button currently pressed?

methods.name: set_controller_id
methods.description: Changes the id that identifies the controller bound to this node. The first controller that the ARVR Server detects will have id 1, the second id 2, the third id 3, etc. When a controller is turned off that slot is freed ensuring that controllers will keep the same id while it is turned on even when controllers with lower ids are turned off.

signals.name: button_pressed
signals.description: When a button on this controller is pressed, this signal is given.

signals.name: button_release
signals.description: When a button on this controller is released, this signal is given.

GDScript.name: GDScript
GDScript.brief_description: A script implemented in the GDScript programming language.
GDScript.description:
A script implemented in the GDScript programming language. The script exends the functionality of all objects that instance it.
		[method new] creates a new instance of the script. [method Object.set_script] extends an existing object, if that object's class matches one of the script's base classes.

methods.name: get_as_byte_code
methods.description: Returns byte code for the script source code.

methods.name: new
methods.description:
Returns a new instance of the script.
				For example:
				[codeblock]
				var MyClass = load("myclass.gd")
				var instance = MyClass.new()
				assert(instance.get_script() == MyClass)
				[/codeblock]

Physics2DServerSW.name: Physics2DServerSW
Physics2DServerSW.description: Software implementation of [Physics2DServer]. This class exposes no new methods or properties and should not be used, as [Physics2DServer] automatically selects the best implementation available.

RID.name: RID
RID.description: The RID type is used to access the unique integer ID of a resource.  They are opaque, so they do not grant access to the associated resource by themselves. They are used by and with the low-level Server classes such as [VisualServer].

methods.name: RID
methods.description: Create a new RID instance with the ID of a given resource. When not handed a valid resource, silently stores the unused ID 0.

methods.name: get_id
methods.description: Retrieve the ID of the referenced resource.

Input.name: Input
Input.brief_description: A Singleton that deals with inputs.
Input.description: A Singleton that deals with inputs. This includes key presses, mouse buttons and movement, joypads, and input actions. Actions and their events can be set in the Project Settings / Input Map tab. Or be set with [InputMap].

methods.name: action_press
methods.description: This will simulate pressing the specificed action.

methods.name: action_release
methods.description: If the specified action is already pressed, this will release it.

methods.name: add_joy_mapping
methods.description: Add a new mapping entry (in SDL2 format) to the mapping database. Optionally update already connected devices.

methods.name: get_accelerometer
methods.description: If the device has an accelerometer, this will return the movement.

methods.name: get_connected_joypads
methods.description: Returns an [Array] containing the device IDs of all currently connected joypads.

methods.name: get_gyroscope
methods.description: If the device has a gyroscope, this will return the rate of rotation in rad/s around a device's x, y, and z axis.

methods.name: get_joy_axis
methods.description: Returns the current value of the joypad axis at given index (see [code]JOY_*[/code] constants in [@Global Scope])

methods.name: get_joy_guid
methods.description: Returns a SDL2 compatible device guid on platforms that use gamepad remapping. Returns "Default Gamepad" otherwise.

methods.name: get_joy_name
methods.description: Returns the name of the joypad at the specified device index

methods.name: get_joy_vibration_duration
methods.description: Returns the duration of the current vibration effect in seconds.

methods.name: get_joy_vibration_strength
methods.description: Returns the strength of the joypad vibration: x is the strength of the weak motor, and y is the strength of the strong motor.

methods.name: get_last_mouse_speed
methods.description: Returns the mouse speed for the last time the cursor was moved, and this until the next frame where the mouse moves. This means that even if the mouse is not moving, this function will still return the value of the last motion.

methods.name: get_magnetometer
methods.description: If the device has a magnetometer, this will return the magnetic field strength in micro-Tesla for all axes.

methods.name: get_mouse_button_mask
methods.description: Returns mouse buttons as a bitmask. If multiple mouse buttons are pressed at the same time the bits are added together.

methods.name: get_mouse_mode
methods.description: Return the mouse mode. See the constants for more information.

methods.name: is_action_just_pressed
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] when you start pressing the action event.

methods.name: is_action_just_released
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] when you stop pressing the action event.

methods.name: is_action_pressed
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if you are pressing the action event.

methods.name: is_joy_button_pressed
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if you are pressing the joypad button. (see [code]JOY_*[/code] constants in [@Global Scope])

methods.name: is_joy_known
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the system knows the specified device. This means that it sets all button and axis indices exactly as defined in the [code]JOY_*[/code] constants (see [@Global Scope]). Unknown joypads are not expected to match these constants, but you can still retrieve events from them.

methods.name: is_key_pressed
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if you are pressing the key. You can pass [code]KEY_*[/code], which are pre-defined constants listed in [@Global Scope].

methods.name: is_mouse_button_pressed
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if you are pressing the mouse button. You can pass [code]BUTTON_*[/code], which are pre-defined constants listed in [@Global Scope].

methods.name: remove_joy_mapping
methods.description: Removes all mappings from the internal db that match the given uid.

methods.name: set_mouse_mode
methods.description: Set the mouse mode. See the constants for more information.

methods.name: start_joy_vibration
methods.description:
Starts to vibrate the joypad. Joypads usually come with two rumble motors, a strong and a weak one. weak_magnitude is the strength of the weak motor (between 0 and 1) and strong_magnitude is the strength of the strong motor (between 0 and 1). duration is the duration of the effect in seconds (a duration of 0 will try to play the vibration indefinitely).
				Note that not every hardware is compatible with long effect durations, it is recommended to restart an effect if in need to play it for more than a few seconds.

methods.name: stop_joy_vibration
methods.description: Stops the vibration of the joypad.

methods.name: warp_mouse_position
methods.description: Sets the mouse position to the specified vector.

signals.name: joy_connection_changed
signals.description: Emitted when a joypad device has been connected or disconnected

constants.name: MOUSE_MODE_VISIBLE
constants.description: Makes the mouse cursor visible if it is hidden.

constants.name: MOUSE_MODE_HIDDEN
constants.description: Makes the mouse cursor hidden if it is visible.

constants.name: MOUSE_MODE_CAPTURED
constants.description: Captures the mouse. The mouse will be hidden and unable to leave the game window. But it will still register movement and mouse button presses.

AudioStreamPlayer2D.name: AudioStreamPlayer2D
AudioStreamPlayer2D.description: Plays audio that dampens with distance from screen center.

methods.name: get_playback_position
methods.description: Returns the position in the [AudioStream].

methods.name: play
methods.description: Plays the audio from the given position 'from_position', in seconds.

methods.name: seek
methods.description: Sets the position from which audio will be played, in seconds.

methods.name: stop
methods.description: Stops the audio.

signals.name: finished
signals.description: Emitted when the audio stops playing.

properties.name: area_mask
properties.description: Areas in which this sound plays.

properties.name: attenuation
properties.description: Dampens audio over distance with this as an exponent.

properties.name: autoplay
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] audio plays when added to scene tree. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: bus
properties.description: Bus on which this audio is playing.

properties.name: max_distance
properties.description: Maximum distance from which audio is still hearable.

properties.name: playing
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] audio is playing.

properties.name: stream
properties.description: The [AudioStream] object to be played.

properties.name: volume_db
properties.description: Base volume without dampening.

methods.name: attach_thread
methods.description: Attaches the current thread to the mono runtime.

methods.name: detach_thread
methods.description: Detaches the current thread from the mono runtime.

methods.name: is_domain_loaded
methods.description: Returns whether the scripts domain is loaded.

methods.name: is_finalizing_domain
methods.description: Returns whether the scripts domain is being finalized.

VisibilityEnabler2D.name: VisibilityEnabler2D
VisibilityEnabler2D.brief_description: Enable certain nodes only when visible.
VisibilityEnabler2D.description: The VisibilityEnabler2D will disable [RigidBody2D], [AnimationPlayer], and other nodes when they are not visible. It will only affect other nodes within the same scene as the VisibilityEnabler2D itself.

methods.name: is_enabler_enabled
methods.description: Returns whether the specified enabler was set to true or not.

methods.name: set_enabler
methods.description: Set an enabler to true for all nodes of its type to be disabled when the VisibilityEnabler2D is not in view. See the constants for enablers and what they affect.

constants.name: ENABLER_FREEZE_BODIES
constants.description: This enabler will freeze [RigidBody2D] nodes.

constants.name: ENABLER_PAUSE_ANIMATIONS
constants.description: This enabler will pause [AnimationPlayer] nodes.

constants.name: ENABLER_PAUSE_PARTICLES
constants.description: This enabler will stop [Particles2D] nodes.

constants.name: ENABLER_PARENT_PROCESS
constants.description: This enabler will stop the parent's _process function.

constants.name: ENABLER_PARENT_PHYSICS_PROCESS
constants.description: This enabler will stop the parent's _physics_process function.

PhysicsShapeQueryResult.name: PhysicsShapeQueryResult

UndoRedo.name: UndoRedo
UndoRedo.brief_description: Helper to manage UndoRedo in the editor or custom tools.
UndoRedo.description:
Helper to manage UndoRedo in the editor or custom tools. It works by storing calls to functions in both 'do' an 'undo' lists.
		Common behavior is to create an action, then add do/undo calls to functions or property changes, then committing the action.

methods.name: add_do_property
methods.description: Set a property with a custom value.

methods.name: add_do_reference
methods.description: Add a 'do' reference that will be erased if the 'do' history is lost. This is useful mostly for new nodes created for the 'do' call. Do not use for resources.

methods.name: add_undo_property
methods.description: Undo setting of a property with a custom value.

methods.name: add_undo_reference
methods.description: Add an 'undo' reference that will be erased if the 'undo' history is lost. This is useful mostly for nodes removed with the 'do' call (not the 'undo' call!).

methods.name: clear_history
methods.description: Clear the undo/redo history and associated references.

methods.name: commit_action
methods.description: Commit the action. All 'do' methods/properties are called/set when this function is called.

methods.name: create_action
methods.description: Create a new action. After this is called, do all your calls to [method add_do_method], [method add_undo_method], [method add_do_property] and [method add_undo_property].

methods.name: get_current_action_name
methods.description: Get the name of the current action.

methods.name: get_version
methods.description:
Get the version, each time a new action is committed, the version number of the UndoRedo is increased automatically.
				This is useful mostly to check if something changed from a saved version.

AudioEffectDistortion.name: AudioEffectDistortion
AudioEffectDistortion.brief_description:
Adds a Distortion audio effect to an Audio bus.
		Modify the sound to make it dirty.
AudioEffectDistortion.description:
Modify the sound and make it dirty. Different types are available : clip, tan, lofi (bit crushing), overdrive, or waveshape.
		By distorting the waveform the frequency content change, which will often make the sound "crunchy" or "abrasive". For games, it can simulate sound coming from some saturated device or speaker very efficiently.

constants.name: MODE_CLIP
constants.description: Digital distortion effect which cuts off peaks at the top and bottom of the waveform.

constants.name: MODE_LOFI
constants.description: Low-resolution digital distortion effect. You can use it to emulate the sound of early digital audio devices.

constants.name: MODE_OVERDRIVE
constants.description: Emulates the warm distortion produced by a field effect transistor, which is commonly used in solid-state musical instrument amplifiers.

constants.name: MODE_WAVESHAPE
constants.description: Waveshaper distortions are used mainly by electronic musicians to achieve an extra-abrasive sound.

properties.name: drive
properties.description: Distortion power. Value can range from 0 to 1. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: keep_hf_hz
properties.description: High-pass filter. Frequencies higher than this value will not be affected by the distortion. Value can range from 1 to 20000. Default value: [code]16000[/code].

properties.name: mode
properties.description: Distortion type. Default value: [code]MODE_CLIP[/code].

properties.name: post_gain
properties.description: Increases or decreases the volume after the effect. Value can range from -80 to 24. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: pre_gain
properties.description: Increases or decreases the volume before the effect. Value can range from -60 to 60. Default value: [code]0[/code].

MarginContainer.name: MarginContainer
MarginContainer.description: Simple margin container. Adds a left margin to anything contained.

Path2D.name: Path2D
Path2D.description: This class is a container/Node-ification of a [Curve2D], so it can have [Node2D] properties and [Node] info.

methods.name: get_curve
methods.description: Returns the [Curve2D] contained.

methods.name: set_curve
methods.description: Sets the [Curve2D].

KinematicBody2D.name: KinematicBody2D
KinematicBody2D.description:
Kinematic bodies are special types of bodies that are meant to be user-controlled. They are not affected by physics at all (to other types of bodies, such a character or a rigid body, these are the same as a static body). They have however, two main uses:
		Simulated Motion: When these bodies are moved manually, either from code or from an AnimationPlayer (with process mode set to fixed), the physics will automatically compute an estimate of their linear and angular velocity. This makes them very useful for moving platforms or other AnimationPlayer-controlled objects (like a door, a bridge that opens, etc).
		Kinematic Characters: KinematicBody2D also has an API for moving objects (the [method move_and_collide] and [method move_and_slide] methods) while performing collision tests. This makes them really useful to implement characters that collide against a world, but that don't require advanced physics.

methods.name: get_floor_velocity
methods.description: Returns the velocity of the floor. Only updates when calling [method move_and_slide].

methods.name: get_slide_collision
methods.description: Returns a [KinematicCollision2D], which contains information about a collision that occured during the last [method move_and_slide] call. Since the body can collide several times in a single call to [method move_and_slide], you must specify the index of the collision in the range 0 to ([method get_slide_count]()-1).

methods.name: get_slide_count
methods.description: Returns the number of times the body collided and changed direction during the last call to [method move_and_slide].

methods.name: is_on_ceiling
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the body is on the ceiling. Only updates when calling [method move_and_slide].

methods.name: is_on_floor
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the body is on the floor. Only updates when calling [method move_and_slide].

methods.name: is_on_wall
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the body is on a wall. Only updates when calling [method move_and_slide].

methods.name: move_and_collide
methods.description: Moves the body along the vector [code]rel_vec[/code]. The body will stop if it collides. Returns a [KinematicCollision2D], which contains information about the collision.

methods.name: move_and_slide
methods.description:
Moves the body along a vector. If the body collides with another, it will slide along the other body rather than stop immediately. If the other body is a [KinematicBody2D] or [RigidBody2D], it will also be affected by the motion of the other body. You can use this to make moving or rotating platforms, or to make nodes push other nodes.
				[code]linear_velocity[/code] is a value in pixels per second. Unlike in for example [method move_and_collide], you should [i]not[/i] multiply it with [code]delta[/code]  this is done by the method.
				[code]floor_normal[/code] is the up direction, used to determine what is a wall and what is a floor or a ceiling. If set to the default value of [code]Vector2(0, 0)[/code], everything is considered a wall. This is useful for topdown games.
				If the body is standing on a slope and the horizontal speed (relative to the floor's speed) goes below [code]slope_stop_min_velocity[/code], the body will stop completely. This prevents the body from sliding down slopes when you include gravity in [code]linear_velocity[/code]. When set to lower values, the body will not be able to stand still on steep slopes.
				If the body collides, it will change direction a maximum of [code]max_bounces[/code] times before it stops.
				[code]floor_max_angle[/code] is the maximum angle (in radians) where a slope is still considered a floor (or a ceiling), rather than a wall. The default value equals 45 degrees.
				Returns the movement that remained when the body stopped. To get more detailed information about collisions that occured, use [method get_slide_collision].

methods.name: test_move
methods.description: Checks for collisions without moving the body. Virtually sets the node's position, scale and rotation to that of the given [Transform2D], then tries to move the body along the vector [code]rel_vec[/code]. Returns [code]true[/code] if a collision would occur.

properties.name: collision/safe_margin
properties.description: If the body is at least this close to another body, this body will consider them to be colliding.

Spatial.name: Spatial
Spatial.brief_description: Most basic 3D game object, parent of all 3D related nodes.
Spatial.description: Most basic 3D game object, with a 3D [Transform] and visibility settings. All other 3D game objects inherit from Spatial. Use Spatial as a parent node to move, scale, rotate and show/hide children in a 3D project.

methods.name: get_gizmo
methods.description: Returns the SpatialGizmo for this node. Used for example in [EditorSpatialGizmo] as custom visualization and editing handles in Editor.

methods.name: get_global_transform
methods.description: Returns the global transform, relative to worldspace.

methods.name: get_parent_spatial
methods.description: Returns the parent [Spatial], or an empty [Object] if no parent exists or parent is not of type [Spatial].

methods.name: get_rotation
methods.description: Returns the rotation (in radians).

methods.name: get_rotation_deg
methods.description: Returns the rotation (in degrees).

methods.name: get_transform
methods.description: Returns the local transform, relative to the bone parent.

methods.name: get_world
methods.description: Returns the current [World] resource this Spatial node is registered to.

methods.name: global_rotate
methods.description: Rotates the current node along normal [Vector3] by angle in radians in Global space.

methods.name: global_translate
methods.description: Moves the node by [Vector3] offset in Global space.

methods.name: hide
methods.description: Disables rendering of this node. Change Spatial Visible property to false.

methods.name: is_local_transform_notification_enabled
methods.description: Returns whether node notifies about its local transformation changes. Spatial will not propagate this by default.

methods.name: is_set_as_toplevel
methods.description: Returns whether this node is set as Toplevel, that is whether it ignores its parent nodes transformations.

methods.name: is_transform_notification_enabled
methods.description: Returns whether the node notifies about its global and local transformation changes. Spatial will not propagate this by default.

methods.name: is_visible
methods.description: Returns whether the node is set to be visible.

methods.name: is_visible_in_tree
methods.description: Returns whether the node is visible, taking into consideration that its parents visibility.

methods.name: look_at
methods.description: Rotates itself to point into direction of target position. Operations take place in global space.

methods.name: look_at_from_position
methods.description: Moves the node to specified position and then rotates itself to point into direction of target position. Operations take place in global space.

methods.name: orthonormalize
methods.description: Resets this node's transformations (like scale, skew and taper) preserving its rotation and translation. Performs orthonormalization on this node [Transform3D].

methods.name: rotate
methods.description: Rotates the node in local space on given normal [Vector3] by angle in radians.

methods.name: rotate_x
methods.description: Rotates the node in local space on X axis by angle in radians.

methods.name: rotate_y
methods.description: Rotates the node in local space on Y axis by angle in radians.

methods.name: rotate_z
methods.description: Rotates the node in local space on Z axis by angle in radians.

methods.name: set_as_toplevel
methods.description: Makes the node ignore its parents transformations. Node transformations are only in global space.

methods.name: set_gizmo
methods.description: Set [SpatialGizmo] for this node. Used for example in [EditorSpatialGizmo] as custom visualization and editing handles in Editor.

methods.name: set_global_transform
methods.description: Set the transform globally, relative to world space.

methods.name: set_identity
methods.description: Reset all transformations for this node. Set its [Transform3D] to identity matrix.

methods.name: set_ignore_transform_notification
methods.description: Set whether the node ignores notification that its transformation (global or local) changed.

methods.name: set_notify_local_transform
methods.description: Set whether the node notifies about its local transformation changes. Spatial will not propagate this by default.

methods.name: set_notify_transform
methods.description: Set whether the node notifies about its global and local transformation changes. Spatial will not propagate this by default.

methods.name: set_rotation
methods.description: Set the rotation (in radians).

methods.name: set_rotation_deg
methods.description: Set the rotation (in degrees).

methods.name: set_scale
methods.description: Set the scale.

methods.name: set_transform
methods.description: Set the transform locally, relative to the parent spatial node.

methods.name: show
methods.description: Enables rendering of this node. Change Spatial Visible property to "True".

methods.name: to_global
methods.description: Transforms [Vector3] "local_point" from this node's local space to world space.

methods.name: to_local
methods.description: Transforms [Vector3] "global_point" from world space to this node's local space.

methods.name: translate
methods.description: Changes the node's position by given offset [Vector3].

methods.name: update_gizmo
methods.description: Updates the [SpatialGizmo] of this node.

signals.name: visibility_changed
signals.description: Emitted when node visibility changes.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_TRANSFORM_CHANGED
constants.description:
Spatial nodes receives this notification when their global transform changes. This means that either the current or a parent node changed its transform.
			In order for NOTIFICATION_TRANSFORM_CHANGED to work user first needs to ask for it, with set_notify_transform(true).

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_ENTER_WORLD
constants.description: Spatial nodes receives this notification when they are registered to new [World] resource.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_EXIT_WORLD
constants.description: Spatial nodes receives this notification when they are unregistered from current [World] resource.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_VISIBILITY_CHANGED
constants.description: Spatial nodes receives this notification when their visibility changes.

properties.name: global_transform

properties.name: rotation

properties.name: scale

properties.name: translation

methods.name: set_abort_on_missing_resources

ImageTexture.description: A [Texture] based on an [Image]. Can be created from an [Image] with [method create_from_image].

methods.description:
Create a new [ImageTexture] with "width" and "height".
				"format" one of [Image].FORMAT_*.
				"flags" one or more of [Texture].FLAG_*.

methods.name: create_from_image
methods.description: Create a new [ImageTexture] from an [Image] with "flags" from [Texture].FLAG_*.

methods.name: get_format
methods.description: Return the format of the [ImageTexture], one of [Image].FORMAT_*.

methods.name: get_lossy_storage_quality
methods.description: Return the storage quality for [ImageTexture].STORAGE_COMPRESS_LOSSY.

methods.name: get_storage

methods.name: set_storage

constants.name: STORAGE_COMPRESS_LOSSLESS

Script.name: Script
Script.brief_description: A class stored as a resource.
Script.description:
A class stored as a resource. The script exends the functionality of all objects that instance it.
		The 'new' method of a script subclass creates a new instance. [method Object.set_script] extends an existing object, if that object's class matches one of the script's base classes.

methods.name: can_instance
methods.description: Returns true if the script can be instanced.

methods.name: get_source_code
methods.description: Returns the script source code, or an empty string if source code is not available.

methods.name: has_script_signal
methods.description: Returns true if the script, or a base class, defines a signal with the given name.

methods.name: has_source_code
methods.description: Returns true if the script contains non-empty source code.

methods.name: instance_has
methods.description: Returns true if 'base_object' is an instance of this script.

methods.name: is_tool
methods.description: Returns true if the script is a tool script. A tool script can run in the editor.

methods.name: reload
methods.description: Reloads the script's class implementation. Returns an error code.

methods.name: set_source_code
methods.description: Sets the script source code. Does not reload the class implementation.

PoolRealArray.name: PoolRealArray
PoolRealArray.description: Real Array. Array of floating point values. Can only contain floats. Optimized for memory usage, can't fragment the memory.

methods.name: PoolRealArray
methods.description: Create from a generic array.

methods.name: append
methods.description: Append an element at the end of the array (alias of [method push_back]).

methods.name: append_array
methods.description: Append an [RealArray] at the end of this array.

methods.name: insert
methods.description: Insert a new element at a given position in the array. The position must be valid, or at the end of the array (pos==size()).

methods.name: invert
methods.description: Reverse the order of the elements in the array (so first element will now be the last).

methods.name: push_back
methods.description: Append an element at the end of the array.

methods.name: remove
methods.description: Remove an element from the array by index.

methods.name: resize
methods.description: Set the size of the array. If the array is grown reserve elements at the end of the array. If the array is shrunk truncate the array to the new size.

methods.name: set

methods.name: size
methods.description: Return the size of the array.

PhysicsBody2D.name: PhysicsBody2D
PhysicsBody2D.brief_description: Base class for all objects affected by physics in 2D space.
PhysicsBody2D.description: PhysicsBody2D is an abstract base class for implementing a physics body. All *Body2D types inherit from it.

methods.name: add_collision_exception_with
methods.description: Adds a body to the list of bodies that this body can't collide with.

methods.name: get_collision_layer
methods.description: Return the physics layer this area is in.

methods.name: get_collision_layer_bit
methods.description: Return an individual bit on the collision mask.

methods.name: get_collision_mask
methods.description: Return the physics layers this area can scan for collisions.

methods.name: get_collision_mask_bit
methods.description: Return an individual bit on the collision mask.

methods.name: remove_collision_exception_with
methods.description: Removes a body from the list of bodies that this body can't collide with.

methods.name: set_collision_layer
methods.description:
Set the physics layers this area is in.
				Collidable objects can exist in any of 32 different layers. These layers are not visual, but more of a tagging system instead. A collidable can use these layers/tags to select with which objects it can collide, using [method set_collision_mask].
				A contact is detected if object A is in any of the layers that object B scans, or object B is in any layer scanned by object A.

methods.name: set_collision_layer_bit
methods.description: Set/clear individual bits on the layer mask. This makes getting a body in/out of only one layer easier.

methods.name: set_collision_mask
methods.description: Set the physics layers this area can scan for collisions.

methods.name: set_collision_mask_bit
methods.description: Set/clear individual bits on the collision mask. This makes selecting the areas scanned easier.

properties.name: collision_layer
properties.description:
The physics layers this area is in.
			Collidable objects can exist in any of 32 different layers. These layers work like a tagging system, and are not visual. A collidable can use these layers to select with which objects it can collide, using the collision_mask property.
			A contact is detected if object A is in any of the layers that object B scans, or object B is in any layer scanned by object A.

properties.name: collision_mask
properties.description: The physics layers this area can scan for collisions.

properties.name: layers
properties.description: Both collision_layer and collision_mask. Returns collision_layer when accessed. Updates collision_layers and collision_mask when modified.

PoolVector3Array.name: PoolVector3Array
PoolVector3Array.description: An Array specifically designed to hold Vector3.

methods.name: PoolVector3Array
methods.description: Construct a new PoolVector3Array. Optionally, you can pass in an Array that will be converted.

methods.name: append

methods.name: append_array
methods.description: Append an [PoolVector3Array] at the end of this array.

methods.name: insert

methods.name: invert
methods.description: Reverse the order of the elements in the array (so first element will now be the last).

methods.name: push_back
methods.description: Insert a [Vector3] at the end.

methods.name: remove
methods.description: Remove an element from the array by index.

methods.name: resize
methods.description: Set the size of the array. If the array is grown reserve elements at the end of the array. If the array is shrunk truncate the array to the new size.

methods.name: set
methods.description: Change the [Vector3] at the given index.

methods.name: size
methods.description: Return the size of the array.

methods.name: get_buffering_msec

methods.name: get_stream

methods.name: get_stream_name

methods.name: get_stream_position

methods.name: get_video_texture

methods.name: get_volume

methods.name: get_volume_db

methods.name: has_autoplay
methods.description: Get whether or not the video is set as autoplay.

methods.name: has_expand
methods.description: Get whether or not the expand property is set.

methods.name: is_paused
methods.description: Get whether or not the video is paused.

methods.name: is_playing
methods.description: Get whether or not the video is playing.

methods.name: set_audio_track

ClassDB.name: ClassDB
ClassDB.description: Provides access to metadata stored for every available class.

methods.name: can_instance
methods.description: Returns true if you can instance objects from the specified 'class', false in other case.

methods.name: class_exists
methods.description: Returns whether the specified 'class' is available or not.

methods.name: class_get_integer_constant
methods.description: Returns the value of the integer constant 'name' of 'class' or its ancestry. Always returns 0 when the constant could not be found.

methods.name: class_get_integer_constant_list
methods.description: Returns an array with the names all the integer constants of 'class' or its ancestry.

methods.name: class_get_method_list
methods.description: Returns an array with all the methods of 'class' or its ancestry if 'no_inheritance' is false. Every element of the array is a [Dictionary] with the following keys: args, default_args, flags, id, name, return: (class_name, hint, hint_string, name, type, usage).

methods.name: class_get_property
methods.description: Returns the value of 'property' of 'class' or its ancestry.

methods.name: class_get_property_list
methods.description: Returns an array with all the properties of 'class' or its ancestry if 'no_inheritance' is false.

methods.name: class_get_signal
methods.description: Returns the 'signal' data of 'class' or its ancestry. The returned value is a [Dictionary] with the following keys: args, default_args, flags, id, name, return: (class_name, hint, hint_string, name, type, usage).

methods.name: class_get_signal_list
methods.description: Returns an array with all the signals of 'class' or its ancestry if 'no_inheritance' is false. Every element of the array is a [Dictionary] as described in [class_get_signal].

methods.name: class_has_integer_constant
methods.description: Return whether 'class' or its ancestry has an integer constant called 'name' or not.

methods.name: class_has_method
methods.description: Return whether 'class' (or its ancestry if 'no_inheritance' is false) has a method called 'method' or not.

methods.name: class_has_signal
methods.description: Return whether 'class' or its ancestry has a signal called 'signal' or not.

methods.name: class_set_property
methods.description: Sets 'property' value of 'class' to 'value'.

methods.name: get_class_list
methods.description: Returns the names of all the classes available.

methods.name: get_inheriters_from_class
methods.description: Returns the names of all the classes that directly or indirectly inherit from 'class'.

methods.name: get_parent_class
methods.description: Returns the parent class of 'class'.

methods.name: instance

TileMap.name: TileMap
TileMap.description: Node for 2D tile-based maps. Tilemaps use a [TileSet] which contain a list of tiles (textures plus optional collision, navigation, and/or occluder shapes) which are used to create grid-based maps.

methods.description: Clear all cells.

methods.name: get_cell
methods.description: Return the tile index of the referenced cell.

methods.name: get_cell_size
methods.description: Return the cell size.

methods.name: get_cellv
methods.description: Return the tile index of the cell referenced by a Vector2.

methods.description: Return true if tiles are to be centered in x coordinate (by default this is false and they are drawn from upper left cell corner).

methods.name: get_center_y
methods.description: Return true if tiles are to be centered in y coordinate (by default this is false and they are drawn from upper left cell corner).

methods.name: get_collision_bounce
methods.description: Return the collision bounce parameter.

methods.name: get_collision_friction
methods.description: Return the collision friction parameter.

methods.description: Return whether the tilemap handles collisions as a kinematic body.

methods.description: Return the custom transform matrix.

methods.name: get_tile_origin
methods.description: Return the tile origin configuration.

methods.name: get_tileset

methods.description: Return an array of all cells containing a tile from the tileset (i.e. a tile index different from -1).

methods.name: is_cell_transposed
methods.description: Return whether the referenced cell is transposed, i.e. the X and Y axes are swapped (mirroring with regard to the (1,1) vector).

methods.name: is_cell_x_flipped
methods.description: Return whether the referenced cell is flipped over the X axis.

methods.name: is_cell_y_flipped
methods.description: Return whether the referenced cell is flipped over the Y axis.

methods.name: is_y_sort_mode_enabled
methods.description: Return the Y sort mode.

methods.name: map_to_world
methods.description:
Return the absolute world position corresponding to the tilemap (grid-based) coordinates given as an argument.
				Optionally, the tilemap's potential half offset can be ignored.

methods.name: set_cell
methods.description:
Set the tile index for the cell referenced by its grid-based X and Y coordinates.
				A tile index of -1 clears the cell.
				Optionally, the tile can also be flipped over the X and Y coordinates or transposed.

methods.name: set_cell_size
methods.description: Set the cell size.

methods.name: set_cellv
methods.description:
Set the tile index for the cell referenced by a Vector2 of grid-based coordinates.
				A tile index of -1 clears the cell.
				Optionally, the tile can also be flipped over the X and Y axes or transposed.

methods.name: set_center_x
methods.description: Set tiles to be centered in x coordinate. (by default this is false and they are drawn from upper left cell corner).

methods.name: set_center_y
methods.description: Set tiles to be centered in y coordinate. (by default this is false and they are drawn from upper left cell corner).

methods.name: set_collision_bounce
methods.description: Set the collision bounce parameter. Allowable values range from 0 to 1.

methods.name: set_collision_friction
methods.description: Set the collision friction parameter. Allowable values range from 0 to 1.

methods.name: set_collision_layer
methods.description:
Set the collision layer.
				Layers are referenced by binary indexes, so allowable values to describe the 20 available layers range from 0 to 2^20-1.

methods.name: set_collision_mask
methods.description:
Set the collision masks.
				Masks are referenced by binary indexes, so allowable values to describe the 20 available masks range from 0 to 2^20-1.

methods.name: set_collision_use_kinematic
methods.description: Set the tilemap to handle collisions as a kinematic body (enabled) or a static body (disabled).

methods.name: set_custom_transform
methods.description: Set custom transform matrix, to use in combination with the custom orientation mode.

methods.name: set_half_offset
methods.description:
Set a half offset on the X coordinate, Y coordinate, or none (use HALF_OFFSET_* constants as argument).
				Half offset sets every other tile off by a half tile size in the specified direction.

methods.name: set_mode
methods.description: Set the orientation mode as square, isometric or custom (use MODE_* constants as argument).

methods.name: set_quadrant_size
methods.description:
Set the quadrant size, this optimizes drawing by batching chunks of map at draw/cull time.
				Allowed values are integers ranging from 1 to 128.

methods.name: set_tile_origin
methods.description: Set the tile origin to the tile center or its top-left corner (use TILE_ORIGIN_* constants as argument).

methods.name: set_tileset
methods.description: Set the current tileset.

methods.name: set_y_sort_mode
methods.description:
Set the Y sort mode. Enabled Y sort mode means that children of the tilemap will be drawn in the order defined by their Y coordinate.
				A tile with a higher Y coordinate will therefore be drawn later, potentially covering up the tile(s) above it if its sprite is higher than its cell size.

methods.name: world_to_map
methods.description: Return the tilemap (grid-based) coordinates corresponding to the absolute world position given as an argument.

signals.description: Emitted when a tilemap setting has changed.

methods.name: _step
methods.description:
Execute the custom node's logic, returning the index of the output sequence port to use or a [String] when there is an error.
				
				The [code]inputs[/code] array contains the values of the input ports.
				[code]outputs[/code] is an array whose indices should be set to the respective outputs.
				The [code]start_mode[/code] is usually [code]START_MODE_BEGIN_SEQUENCE[/code], unless you have used the STEP_* constants.
				[code]working_mem[/code] is an array which can be used to persist information between runs of the custom node.
				
				When returning, you can mask the returned value with one of the STEP_* constants.

constants.name: START_MODE_BEGIN_SEQUENCE
constants.description: The start mode used the first time when [method _step] is called.

constants.name: START_MODE_CONTINUE_SEQUENCE
constants.description: The start mode used when [method _step] is called after coming back from a STEP_PUSH_STACK_BIT.

constants.name: START_MODE_RESUME_YIELD
constants.description: The start mode used when [method _step] is called after resuming from STEP_YIELD_BIT.

constants.name: STEP_PUSH_STACK_BIT
constants.description:
Hint used by [method _step] to tell that control should return to it when there is no other node left to execute.
			This is used by [VisualScriptCondition] to redirect the sequence to the "Done" port after the true/false branch has finished execution.

constants.name: STEP_GO_BACK_BIT
constants.description: Hint used by [method _step] to tell that control should return back, either hitting a previous STEP_PUSH_STACK_BIT or exiting the function.

constants.name: STEP_EXIT_FUNCTION_BIT
constants.description: Hint used by [method _step] to tell that control should stop and exit the function.

constants.name: STEP_YIELD_BIT
constants.description:
Hint used by [method _step] to tell that the function should be yielded.
			Using this requires you to have at least one working memory slot, which is used for the [VisualScriptFunctionState].

NinePatchRect.name: NinePatchRect
NinePatchRect.brief_description: Scalable texture-based frame that tiles the texture's centers and sides, but keeps the corners' original size. Perfect for panels and dialog boxes.
NinePatchRect.description: Better known as 9-slice panels, NinePatchRect produces clean panels of any size, based on a small texture. To do so, it splits the texture in a 3 by 3 grid. When you scale the node, it tiles the texture's sides horizontally or vertically, the center on both axes but it doesn't scale or tile the corners.

properties.description: The height of the 9-slice's bottom row. A margin of 16 means the 9-slice's bottom corners and side will have a height of 16 pixels. You can set all 4 margin values individually to create panels with non-uniform borders.

ConcavePolygonShape2D.name: ConcavePolygonShape2D
ConcavePolygonShape2D.brief_description: Concave polygon 2D shape resource for physics.
ConcavePolygonShape2D.description:
Concave polygon 2D shape resource for physics. It is made out of segments and is very optimal for complex polygonal concave collisions. It is really not advised to use for [RigidBody2D] nodes. A CollisionPolygon2D in convex decomposition mode (solids) or several convex objects are advised for that instead. Otherwise, a concave polygon 2D shape is better for static collisions.
		The main difference between a [ConvexPolygonShape2D] and a [ConcavePolygonShape2D] is that a concave polygon assumes it is concave and uses a more complex method of collision detection, and a convex one forces itself to be convex in order to speed up collision detection.

methods.name: set_segments

This function is used when the user drags a gizmo handle (previously added with [method add_handles]) in screen coordinates.
