properties.name: radius
properties.description: The capsules's radius.

KinematicCollision2D.name: KinematicCollision2D
KinematicCollision2D.description:
Contains collision data for KinematicBody2D collisions. When a [KinematicBody2D] is moved using [method KinematicBody2D.move_and_collide], it stops if it detects a collision with another body. If a collision is detected, a KinematicCollision2D object is returned.
		This object contains information about the collision, including the colliding object, the remaining motion, and the collision position. This information can be used to calculate a collision response.

properties.name: collider
properties.description: The colliding body.

properties.name: collider_id
properties.description: The colliding body's unique [RID].

properties.name: collider_metadata
properties.description: The colliding body's metadata. See [Object].

properties.name: collider_shape
properties.description: The colliding body's shape.

properties.name: collider_shape_index
properties.description: The colliding shape's index. See [CollisionObject2D].

properties.name: collider_velocity
properties.description: The colliding object's velocity.

properties.name: local_shape
properties.description: The moving object's colliding shape.

properties.name: normal
properties.description: The colliding body's shape's normal at the point of collision.

properties.name: position
properties.description: The point of collision.

properties.name: remainder
properties.description: The moving object's remaining movement vector.

properties.name: travel
properties.description: The distance the moving object traveled before collision.

Shape2D.name: Shape2D
Shape2D.description: Base class for all 2D Shapes. All 2D shape types inherit from this.

methods.name: collide
methods.description:
Return whether this shape is colliding with another.
				This method needs the transformation matrix for this shape ([code]local_xform[/code]), the shape to check collisions with ([code]with_shape[/code]), and the transformation matrix of that shape ([code]shape_xform[/code]).

methods.name: collide_and_get_contacts
methods.description:
Return a list of the points where this shape touches another. If there are no collisions, the list is empty.
				This method needs the transformation matrix for this shape ([code]local_xform[/code]), the shape to check collisions with ([code]with_shape[/code]), and the transformation matrix of that shape ([code]shape_xform[/code]).

methods.name: collide_with_motion
methods.description:
Return whether this shape would collide with another, if a given movement was applied.
				This method needs the transformation matrix for this shape ([code]local_xform[/code]), the movement to test on this shape ([code]local_motion[/code]), the shape to check collisions with ([code]with_shape[/code]), the transformation matrix of that shape ([code]shape_xform[/code]), and the movement to test onto the other object ([code]shape_motion[/code]).

methods.name: collide_with_motion_and_get_contacts
methods.description:
Return a list of the points where this shape would touch another, if a given movement was applied. If there are no collisions, the list is empty.
				This method needs the transformation matrix for this shape ([code]local_xform[/code]), the movement to test on this shape ([code]local_motion[/code]), the shape to check collisions with ([code]with_shape[/code]), the transformation matrix of that shape ([code]shape_xform[/code]), and the movement to test onto the other object ([code]shape_motion[/code]).

methods.name: get_custom_solver_bias
methods.description: Return the custom solver bias.

methods.name: set_custom_solver_bias
methods.description:
Use a custom solver bias. No need to change this unless you really know what you are doing.
				The solver bias is a factor controlling how much two objects "rebound" off each other, when colliding, to avoid them getting into each other because of numerical imprecision.

AudioStreamPlayback.name: AudioStreamPlayback
AudioStreamPlayback.brief_description: Meta class for playing back audio.
AudioStreamPlayback.description: Can play, loop, pause a scroll through Audio. See [AudioStream] and [AudioStreamOGGVorbis] for usage.

SphereShape.name: SphereShape
SphereShape.description: Sphere shape for 3D collisions, which can be set into a [PhysicsBody] or [Area]. This shape is useful for modeling sphere-like 3D objects.

properties.name: radius
properties.description: The sphere's radius. The shape's diameter is double the radius.

LargeTexture.name: LargeTexture
LargeTexture.brief_description: A Texture capable of storing many smaller Textures with offsets.
LargeTexture.description:
A Texture capable of storing many smaller Textures with offsets.
		You can dynamically add pieces([Texture]) to this [code]LargeTexture[/code] using different offsets.

methods.name: add_piece
methods.description: Add another [Texture] to this [code]LargeTexture[/code], starting on offset "ofs".

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clears the [code]LargeTexture[/code].

methods.name: get_piece_count
methods.description: Returns the number of pieces currently in this [code]LargeTexture[/code].

methods.name: get_piece_offset
methods.description: Returns the offset of the piece with index "idx".

methods.name: get_piece_texture
methods.description: Returns the [Texture] of the piece with index "idx".

methods.name: set_piece_offset
methods.description: Sets the offset of the piece with index "idx" to "ofs".

methods.name: set_piece_texture
methods.description: Sets the [Texture] of the piece with index "idx" to  "ofs".

methods.name: set_size
methods.description: Sets the size of this [code]LargeTexture[/code].

properties.name: _data
properties.description:
Returns an [Array] with offsets and textures data of each added piece. Schema is [offsets1, texture1, offsets2, texture2, large_texture_size].
			[code]offsets[/code] : [Vector2] offsets of the texture piece.
			[code]second[/code] : [StreamTexture] data of the texture piece.
			[code]last entry[/code] : [Vector2] size of the entire large texture.

AudioStreamRandomPitch.name: AudioStreamRandomPitch
AudioStreamRandomPitch.brief_description: Plays audio with random pitch tweaking.
AudioStreamRandomPitch.description: Randomly varies pitch on each start.

properties.name: audio_stream
properties.description: The current [AudioStream].

properties.name: random_pitch
properties.description: The intensity of random pitch variation.

VScrollBar.name: VScrollBar
VScrollBar.brief_description: Vertical version of [ScrollBar], which goes from left (min) to right (max).

RigidBody.name: RigidBody
RigidBody.brief_description: Physics Body whose position is determined through physics simulation in 3D space.
RigidBody.description:
This is the node that implements full 3D physics. This means that you do not control a RigidBody directly. Instead you can apply forces to it (gravity, impulses, etc.), and the physics simulation will calculate the resulting movement, collision, bouncing, rotating, etc.
		This node can use custom force integration, for writing complex physics motion behavior per node.
		This node can shift state between regular Rigid body, Kinematic, Character or Static.
		Character mode forbids this node from being rotated.
		As a warning, don't change RigidBody's position every frame or very often. Sporadic changes work fine, but physics runs at a different granularity (fixed hz) than usual rendering (process callback) and maybe even in a separate thread, so changing this from a process loop will yield strange behavior.

methods.name: _integrate_forces
methods.description: Called during physics processing, allowing you to read and safely modify the simulation state for the object. By default it works in addition to the usual physics behavior, but [method set_use_custom_integrator] allows you to disable the default behavior and do fully custom force integration for a body.

methods.name: apply_impulse
methods.description: Apply a positioned impulse (which will be affected by the body mass and shape). This is the equivalent of hitting a billiard ball with a cue: a force that is applied once, and only once. Both the impulse and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates.

methods.name: get_angular_damp
methods.description: Return the current body angular damp. Default is -1.

methods.name: get_angular_velocity
methods.description: Return the current body angular velocity.

methods.name: get_axis_lock
methods.description: Return the current axis lock of the body. One of AXIS_LOCK_* enum.

methods.name: get_bounce
methods.description: Return the current body bounciness.

methods.name: get_colliding_bodies
methods.description: Return a list of the bodies colliding with this one. By default, number of max contacts reported is at 0 , see [method set_max_contacts_reported] to increase it.

methods.name: get_friction
methods.description: Return the current body friction, from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (max friction).

methods.name: get_gravity_scale
methods.description: Return the current body gravity scale.

methods.name: get_linear_damp
methods.description: Return the current body linear damp. Default is -1.

methods.name: get_linear_velocity
methods.description: Return the current body linear velocity.

methods.name: get_mass
methods.description: Return the current body mass.

methods.name: get_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Return the maximum contacts that can be reported. See [method set_max_contacts_reported].

methods.name: get_mode
methods.description: Return the current body mode, see [method set_mode].

methods.name: get_weight
methods.description: Return the current body weight, given standard earth-weight (gravity 9.8).

methods.name: is_able_to_sleep
methods.description: Return whether the body has the ability to fall asleep when not moving. See [method set_can_sleep].

methods.name: is_contact_monitor_enabled
methods.description: Return whether contact monitoring is enabled.

methods.name: is_sleeping
methods.description: Return whether the body is sleeping.

methods.name: is_using_continuous_collision_detection
methods.description: Return whether this body is using continuous collision detection.

methods.name: is_using_custom_integrator
methods.description: Return whether the body is using a custom integrator.

methods.name: set_angular_damp
methods.description: Set the angular damp for this body. Default of -1, cannot be less than -1. If this value is different from -1, any angular damp derived from the world or areas will be overridden.

methods.name: set_angular_velocity
methods.description: Set the body angular velocity. Can be used sporadically, but [b]DON'T SET THIS IN EVERY FRAME[/b], because physics may be running in another thread and definitely runs at a different granularity. Use [method _integrate_forces] as your process loop if you want to have precise control of the body state.

methods.name: set_axis_lock
methods.description: Set the axis lock of the body, from the AXIS_LOCK_* enum. Axis lock stops the body from moving along the specified axis(X/Y/Z) and rotating along the other two axes.

methods.name: set_axis_velocity
methods.description: Set an axis velocity. The velocity in the given vector axis will be set as the given vector length. This is useful for jumping behavior.

methods.name: set_bounce
methods.description: Set the body bounciness, from 0 (no bounciness) to 1 (max bounciness).

methods.name: set_can_sleep
methods.description:
Set the body ability to fall asleep when not moving. This saves an enormous amount of processor time when there are plenty of rigid bodies (non static) in a scene.
				Sleeping bodies are not affected by forces until a collision or an [method apply_impulse] / [method set_applied_force] wakes them up. Until then, they behave like a static body.

methods.name: set_contact_monitor
methods.description: Enable contact monitoring. This allows the body to emit signals when it collides with another.

methods.name: set_friction
methods.description: Set the body friction, from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (max friction).

methods.name: set_gravity_scale
methods.description: Set the gravity factor. This factor multiplies gravity intensity just for this body.

methods.name: set_linear_damp
methods.description: Set the linear damp for this body. Default of -1, cannot be less than -1. If this value is different from -1, any linear damp derived from the world or areas will be overridden.

methods.name: set_linear_velocity
methods.description: Set the body linear velocity. Can be used sporadically, but [b]DON'T SET THIS IN EVERY FRAME[/b], because physics may be running in another thread and definitely runs at a different granularity. Use [method _integrate_forces] as your process loop if you want to have precise control of the body state.

methods.name: set_mass
methods.description: Set the body mass.

methods.name: set_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Set the maximum contacts to report. Bodies can keep a log of the contacts with other bodies, this is enabled by setting the maximum amount of contacts reported to a number greater than 0.

methods.name: set_mode
methods.description: Set the body mode, from the MODE_* enum. This allows to change to a static body or a character body.

methods.name: set_sleeping
methods.description: Set whether a body is sleeping or not. Sleeping bodies are not affected by forces until a collision or an [method apply_impulse] wakes them up. Until then, they behave like a static body.

methods.name: set_use_continuous_collision_detection
methods.description:
Set the continuous collision detection mode from the enum CCD_MODE_*.
				Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will collide, instead of moving it and correcting its movement if it collided. The first is more precise, and misses less impacts by small, fast-moving objects. The second is faster to compute, but can miss small, fast-moving objects.

methods.name: set_use_custom_integrator
methods.description: Pass true to disable the internal force integration (like gravity or air friction) for this body. Other than collision response, the body will only move as determined by the [method _integrate_forces] function, if defined.

methods.name: set_weight
methods.description: Set the body weight given standard earth-weight (gravity 9.8).

signals.name: body_entered
signals.description: Emitted when a body enters into contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.

signals.name: body_exited
signals.description: Emitted when a body shape exits contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.

signals.name: body_shape_entered
signals.description:
Emitted when a body enters into contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.
				This signal not only receives the body that collided with this one, but also its [RID] (body_id), the shape index from the colliding body (body_shape), and the shape index from this body (local_shape) the other body collided with.

signals.name: body_shape_exited
signals.description:
Emitted when a body shape exits contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.
				This signal not only receives the body that stopped colliding with this one, but also its [RID] (body_id), the shape index from the colliding body (body_shape), and the shape index from this body (local_shape) the other body stopped colliding with.

signals.name: sleeping_state_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the body changes its sleeping state. Either by sleeping or waking up.

constants.name: MODE_STATIC
constants.description: Static mode. The body behaves like a [StaticBody], and can only move by user code.

constants.name: MODE_KINEMATIC
constants.description: Kinematic body. The body behaves like a [KinematicBody], and can only move by user code.

constants.name: MODE_RIGID
constants.description: Rigid body. This is the "natural" state of a rigid body. It is affected by forces, and can move, rotate, and be affected by user code.

constants.name: MODE_CHARACTER
constants.description: Character body. This behaves like a rigid body, but can not rotate.

properties.name: angular_damp
properties.description: Damps RigidBody's rotational forces.

properties.name: angular_velocity
properties.description: RigidBody's rotational velocity.

properties.name: axis_lock
properties.description: Locks the rotational forces to a particular axis, preventing rotations on other axes.

properties.name: bounce
properties.description: RigidBody's bounciness.

properties.name: can_sleep
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the RigidBody will not calculate forces and will act as a static body while there is no movement. It will wake up when forces are applied through other collisions or when the [code]apply_impulse[/code] method is used.

properties.name: contact_monitor
properties.description: If true, the RigidBody will emit signals when it collides with another RigidBody.

properties.name: contacts_reported
properties.description: The maximum contacts to report. Bodies can keep a log of the contacts with other bodies, this is enabled by setting the maximum amount of contacts reported to a number greater than 0.

properties.name: continuous_cd
properties.description:
If [code]true[/code] continuous collision detection is used.
			Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will collide, instead of moving it and correcting its movement if it collided. Continuous collision detection is more precise, and misses less impacts by small, fast-moving objects. Not using continuous collision detection is faster to compute, but can miss small, fast-moving objects.

properties.name: custom_integrator
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] internal force integration will be disabled (like gravity or air friction) for this body. Other than collision response, the body will only move as determined by the [method _integrate_forces] function, if defined.

properties.name: friction
properties.description: The body friction, from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (max friction).

properties.name: gravity_scale
properties.description: This is multiplied by the global 3D gravity setting found in "Project > Project Settings > Physics > 3d" to produce RigidBody's gravity. E.g. a value of 1 will be normal gravity, 2 will apply double gravity, and 0.5 will apply half gravity to this object.

properties.name: linear_damp
properties.description: RigidBody's linear damp. Default value: -1, cannot be less than -1. If this value is different from -1, any linear damp derived from the world or areas will be overridden.

properties.name: linear_velocity
properties.description: RigidBody's linear velocity. Can be used sporadically, but [b]DON'T SET THIS IN EVERY FRAME[/b], because physics may run in another thread and runs at a different granularity. Use [method _integrate_forces] as your process loop for precise control of the body state.

properties.name: mass
properties.description: RigidBody's mass.

properties.name: mode
properties.description: The body mode from the MODE_* enum. Modes include: MODE_STATIC, MODE_KINEMATIC, MODE_RIGID, and MODE_CHARACTER.

properties.name: sleeping
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] RigidBody is sleeping and will not calculate forces until woken up by a collision or the [code]apply_impulse[/code] method.

properties.name: weight
properties.description: RigidBody's weight based on its mass and the global 3D gravity. Global values are set in "Project > Project Settings > Physics > 3d".

AudioEffectLimiter.name: AudioEffectLimiter
AudioEffectLimiter.brief_description: Adds a soft clip Limiter audio effect to an Audio bus.
AudioEffectLimiter.description:
A limiter is similar to a compressor, but its less flexible and designed to disallow sound going over a given dB threshold. Adding one in the Master Bus is always recommended to reduce the effects of clipping.
		Soft clipping starts to reduce the peaks a little below the threshold level and progressively increases its effect as the input level increases such that the threshold is never exceeded.

properties.name: ceiling_db
properties.description: The waveform's maximum allowed value. Value can range from -20 to -0.1. Default value: [code]-0.1dB[/code].

properties.name: soft_clip_db
properties.description: Applies a gain to the limited waves. Value can range from 0 to 6. Default value: [code]2dB[/code].

properties.name: threshold_db
properties.description: Threshold from which the limiter begins to be active. Value can range from -30 to 0. Default value: [code]0dB[/code].

PinJoint2D.name: PinJoint2D
PinJoint2D.description: Pin Joint for 2D Rigid Bodies. It pins 2 bodies (rigid or static) together, or a single body to a fixed position in space.

properties.name: size
properties.description: Size of the cuboid mesh. Defaults to (2, 2, 2).

properties.name: subdivide_depth
properties.description: Number of extra edge loops inserted along the z-axis. Defaults to 0.

properties.name: subdivide_height
properties.description: Number of extra edge loops inserted along the y-axis. Defaults to 0.

properties.name: subdivide_width
properties.description: Number of extra edge loops inserted along the x-axis. Defaults to 0.

methods.name: action_match
methods.description: Returns true if this input event matches the event passed.

methods.name: as_text
methods.description: Returns a [String] representation of the event.

methods.name: get_device
methods.description: Returns the id of the device that generated the event.

methods.name: get_id
methods.description: Returns the id of the event.

methods.name: is_action
methods.description: Returns true if this input event matches a pre-defined action, no matter the type.

methods.name: is_action_pressed
methods.description: Returns true if the given action is being pressed (and is not an echo event for KEY events). Not relevant for the event types MOUSE_MOTION, SCREEN_DRAG and NONE.

methods.name: is_action_released
methods.description: Returns true if the given action is released (i.e. not pressed). Not relevant for the event types MOUSE_MOTION, SCREEN_DRAG and NONE.

methods.name: is_echo
methods.description: Returns true if this input event is an echo event (only for events of type KEY, it will return false for other types).

methods.name: is_pressed
methods.description: Returns true if this input event is pressed. Not relevant for the event types MOUSE_MOTION, SCREEN_DRAG and NONE.

AudioEffectEQ21.name: AudioEffectEQ21
AudioEffectEQ21.brief_description:
Adds a 21-band equalizer audio effect to an Audio bus. Gives you control over frequencies from 22 Hz to 22000 Hz.
		Each frequency can be modulated between -60/+24 dB.
AudioEffectEQ21.description:
Frequency bands :
		Band 1 : 22 Hz
		Band 2 : 32 Hz
		Band 3 : 44 Hz
		Band 4 : 63 Hz
		Band 5 : 90 Hz
		Band 6 : 125 Hz
		Band 7 : 175 Hz
		Band 8 : 250 Hz
		Band 9 : 350 Hz
		Band 10 : 500 Hz
		Band 11 : 700 Hz
		Band 12 : 1000 Hz
		Band 13 : 1400 Hz
		Band 14 : 2000 Hz
		Band 15 : 2800 Hz
		Band 16 : 4000 Hz
		Band 17 : 5600 Hz
		Band 18 : 8000 Hz
		Band 19 : 11000 Hz
		Band 20 : 16000 Hz
		Band 21 : 22000 Hz

		See also [AudioEffectEQ], [AudioEffectEQ6], [AudioEffectEQ10].

DampedSpringJoint2D.name: DampedSpringJoint2D
DampedSpringJoint2D.description: Damped spring constraint for 2D physics. This resembles a spring joint that always wants to go back to a given length.

methods.name: get_damping
methods.description: Return the damping ratio of the spring joint. A value of 0 indicates an undamped spring, while 1 causes the system to reach equilibrium as fast as possible (critical damping).

methods.name: get_length
methods.description: Return the maximum length of the spring joint.

methods.name: get_rest_length
methods.description: Return the resting length of the spring joint. The joint will always try to go to back this length when pulled apart.

methods.name: get_stiffness
methods.description: Return the stiffness of the spring joint. The joint applies a force equal to the stiffness times the distance from its resting length.

methods.name: set_damping
methods.description: Set the damping ratio of the spring joint. A value of 0 indicates an undamped spring, while 1 causes the system to reach equilibrium as fast as possible (critical damping).

methods.name: set_length
methods.description: Set the maximum length of the spring joint.

methods.name: set_rest_length
methods.description: Set the resting length of the spring joint. The joint will always try to go to back this length when pulled apart.

methods.name: set_stiffness
methods.description: Set the stiffness of the spring joint. The joint applies a force equal to the stiffness times the distance from its resting length.

Shape.name: Shape
Shape.brief_description: Base class for all 3D shape resources.
Shape.description: Base class for all 3D shape resources. All 3D shapes that inherit from this can be set into a [PhysicsBody] or [Area].

InputEventMouseButton.name: InputEventMouseButton
InputEventMouseButton.brief_description: Input event type for mouse button events.

properties.name: button_index
properties.description: Mouse button identifier, one of the BUTTON_* or BUTTON_WHEEL_* constants in [@Global Scope].

properties.name: doubleclick
properties.description: Whether the event is a double-click.

properties.name: pressed
properties.description: Pressed state of the mouse button.

Panel.name: Panel
Panel.brief_description: Provides an opaque background for [Control] children.
Panel.description: Panel is a [Control] that displays an opaque background. It's commonly used as a parent and container for other types of [Control] nodes.

WindowDialog.name: WindowDialog
WindowDialog.description: Windowdialog is the base class for all window-based dialogs. It's a by-default toplevel [Control] that draws a window decoration and allows motion and resizing.

methods.name: get_close_button
methods.description: Return the close [TextureButton].

methods.name: get_title
methods.description: Return the title of the window.

methods.name: set_title
methods.description: Set the title of the window.

MultiMeshInstance.name: MultiMeshInstance
MultiMeshInstance.description: MultiMeshInstance is a [Node] that takes a [MultiMesh] resource and adds it to the current scenario by creating an instance of it (yes, this is an instance of instances).

methods.name: get_multimesh
methods.description: Return the [MultiMesh] that is used for instancing.

methods.name: set_multimesh
methods.description: Set the [MultiMesh] to be instanced.

TextureRect.name: TextureRect
TextureRect.brief_description: Draws a sprite or a texture inside a User Interface. The texture can tile or not.
TextureRect.description: Use TextureRect to draw icons and sprites in your User Interfaces. To create panels and menu boxes, take a look at [NinePatchFrame]. Its Stretch Mode property controls the texture's scale and placement. It can scale, tile and stay centered inside its bounding rectangle. TextureRect is one of the 5 most common nodes to create game UI.

constants.name: STRETCH_SCALE_ON_EXPAND
constants.description: Scale to fit the node's bounding rectangle, only if [code]expand[/code] is [code]true[/code]. Default [code]stretch_mode[/code], for backwards compatibility. Until you set [code]expand[/code] to [code]true[/code], the texture will behave like [code]STRETCH_KEEP[/code].

constants.name: STRETCH_SCALE
constants.description: Scale to fit the node's bounding rectangle.

constants.name: STRETCH_TILE
constants.description: Tile inside the node's bounding rectangle.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP
constants.description: The texture keeps its original size and stays in the bounding rectangle's top-left corner.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP_CENTERED
constants.description: The texture keeps its original size and stays centered in the node's bounding rectangle.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT
constants.description: Scale the texture to fit the node's bounding rectangle, but maintain the texture's aspect ratio.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT_CENTERED
constants.description: Scale the texture to fit the node's bounding rectangle, center it and maintain its aspect ratio.

constants.name: STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT_COVERED
constants.description: Scale the texture so that the shorter side fits the bounding rectangle. The other side clips to the node's limits.

properties.name: expand
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], the texture scales to fit its bounding rectangle. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: stretch_mode
properties.description: Controls the texture's behavior when you resize the node's bounding rectangle. Set it to one of the [code]STRETCH_*[/code] constants. See the constants to learn more.

properties.name: texture
properties.description: The node's [Texture] resource.

Animation.name: Animation
Animation.brief_description: Contains data used to animate everything in the engine.
Animation.description:
An Animation resource contains data used to animate everything in the engine. Animations are divided into tracks, and each track must be linked to a node. The state of that node can be changed through time, by adding timed keys (events) to the track.
		Animations are just data containers, and must be added to odes such as an [AnimationPlayer] or [AnimationTreePlayer] to be played back.

methods.name: add_track
methods.description: Add a track to the Animation. The track type must be specified as any of the values in the TYPE_* enumeration.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear the animation (clear all tracks and reset all).

methods.name: find_track
methods.description: Return the index of the specified track. If the track is not found, return -1.

methods.name: get_length
methods.description: Return the total length of the animation (in seconds).

methods.name: get_step
methods.description: Get the animation step value.

methods.name: get_track_count
methods.description: Return the amount of tracks in the animation.

methods.name: has_loop
methods.description: Return whether the animation has the loop flag set.

methods.name: method_track_get_key_indices
methods.description: Return all the key indices of a method track, given a position and delta time.

methods.name: method_track_get_name
methods.description: Return the method name of a method track.

methods.name: method_track_get_params
methods.description: Return the arguments values to be called on a method track for a given key in a given track.

methods.name: remove_track
methods.description: Remove a track by specifying the track index.

methods.name: set_length
methods.description: Set the total length of the animation (in seconds). Note that length is not delimited by the last key, as this one may be before or after the end to ensure correct interpolation and looping.

methods.name: set_loop
methods.description: Set a flag indicating that the animation must loop. This is uses for correct interpolation of animation cycles, and for hinting the player that it must restart the animation.

methods.name: set_step
methods.description: Set the animation step value.

methods.name: track_find_key
methods.description: Find the key index by time in a given track. Optionally, only find it if the exact time is given.

methods.name: track_get_interpolation_type
methods.description: Return the interpolation type of a given track, from the INTERPOLATION_* enum.

methods.name: track_get_key_count
methods.description: Return the amount of keys in a given track.

methods.name: track_get_key_time
methods.description: Return the time at which the key is located.

methods.name: track_get_key_transition
methods.description: Return the transition curve (easing) for a specific key (see built-in math function "ease").

methods.name: track_get_key_value
methods.description: Return the value of a given key in a given track.

methods.name: track_get_path
methods.description: Get the path of a track. for more information on the path format, see [method track_set_path]

methods.name: track_get_type
methods.description: Get the type of a track.

methods.name: track_insert_key
methods.description: Insert a generic key in a given track.

methods.name: track_is_imported
methods.description: Return true if the given track is imported. Else, return false.

methods.name: track_move_down
methods.description: Move a track down.

methods.name: track_move_up
methods.description: Move a track up.

methods.name: track_remove_key
methods.description: Remove a key by index in a given track.

methods.name: track_remove_key_at_position
methods.description: Remove a key by position (seconds) in a given track.

methods.name: track_set_imported
methods.description: Set the given track as imported or not.

methods.name: track_set_interpolation_type
methods.description: Set the interpolation type of a given track, from the INTERPOLATION_* enum.

methods.name: track_set_key_transition
methods.description: Set the transition curve (easing) for a specific key (see built-in math function "ease").

methods.name: track_set_key_value
methods.description: Set the value of an existing key.

methods.name: track_set_path
methods.description: Set the path of a track. Paths must be valid scene-tree paths to a node, and must be specified starting from the parent node of the node that will reproduce the animation. Tracks that control properties or bones must append their name after the path, separated by ":". Example: "character/skeleton:ankle" or "character/mesh:transform/local"

methods.name: transform_track_insert_key
methods.description: Insert a transform key for a transform track.

methods.name: transform_track_interpolate
methods.description: Return the interpolated value of a transform track at a given time (in seconds). An array consisting of 3 elements: position ([Vector3]), rotation ([Quat]) and scale ([Vector3]).

methods.name: value_track_get_key_indices
methods.description: Return all the key indices of a value track, given a position and delta time.

methods.name: value_track_get_update_mode
methods.description: Return the update mode of a value track.

methods.name: value_track_set_update_mode
methods.description: Set the update mode (UPDATE_*) of a value track.

constants.name: TYPE_VALUE
constants.description: Value tracks set values in node properties, but only those which can be Interpolated.

constants.name: TYPE_TRANSFORM
constants.description: Transform tracks are used to change node local transforms or skeleton pose bones. Transitions are Interpolated.

constants.name: TYPE_METHOD
constants.description: Method tracks call functions with given arguments per key.

constants.name: INTERPOLATION_NEAREST
constants.description: No interpolation (nearest value).

constants.name: INTERPOLATION_LINEAR
constants.description: Linear interpolation.

constants.name: INTERPOLATION_CUBIC
constants.description: Cubic interpolation.

constants.name: UPDATE_CONTINUOUS
constants.description: Update between keyframes.

constants.name: UPDATE_DISCRETE
constants.description: Update at the keyframes and hold the value.

constants.name: UPDATE_TRIGGER
constants.description: Update at the keyframes.

PoolVector2Array.name: PoolVector2Array
PoolVector2Array.description: An Array specifically designed to hold Vector2.

methods.name: PoolVector2Array
methods.description: Construct a new [PoolVector2Array]. Optionally, you can pass in an Array that will be converted.

methods.name: append
methods.description: Append an element at the end of the array (alias of [method push_back]).

methods.name: append_array
methods.description: Append an [PoolVector2Array] at the end of this array.

methods.name: insert
methods.description: Insert a new element at a given position in the array. The position must be valid, or at the end of the array (pos==size()).

methods.name: invert
methods.description: Reverse the order of the elements in the array (so first element will now be the last).

methods.name: push_back
methods.description: Insert a [Vector2] at the end.

methods.name: remove
methods.description: Remove an element from the array by index.

methods.name: resize
methods.description: Set the size of the array. If the array is grown reserve elements at the end of the array. If the array is shrunk truncate the array to the new size.

methods.name: set
methods.description: Change the [Vector2] at the given index.

methods.name: size
methods.description: Return the size of the array.

ConvexPolygonShape2D.name: ConvexPolygonShape2D
ConvexPolygonShape2D.description:
Convex Polygon Shape for 2D physics. A convex polygon, whatever its shape, is internally decomposed into as many convex polygons as needed to ensure all collision checks against it are always done on convex polygons (which are faster to check).
		The main difference between a [ConvexPolygonShape2D] and a [ConcavePolygonShape2D] is that a concave polygon assumes it is concave and uses a more complex method of collision detection, and a convex one forces itself to be convex in order to speed up collision detection.

methods.name: get_points
methods.description: Returns a list of points in either clockwise or counter clockwise order, forming a convex polygon.

methods.name: set_point_cloud
methods.description: Currently, this method does nothing.

methods.name: set_points
methods.description: Sets a list of points in either clockwise or counter clockwise order, forming a convex polygon.

properties.name: points
properties.description: The polygon's list of vertices. Can be in either clockwise or counterclockwise order.

TreeItem.name: TreeItem
TreeItem.brief_description: Control for a single item inside a [Tree].
TreeItem.description: Control for a single item inside a [Tree]. May have child [TreeItem]\ s and be styled as well as contain buttons.

methods.name: add_button
methods.description: Adds a button with [Texture] [code]button[/code] at column [code]column[/code]. The [code]button_idx[/code] index is used to identify the button when calling other methods. If not specified, the next available index is used, which may be retrieved by calling [code]get_buton_count()[/code] immediately after this method. Optionally, the button can be [code]disabled[/code] and have a [code]tooltip[/code].

methods.name: clear_custom_bg_color
methods.description: Resets the background color for the given column to default.

methods.name: clear_custom_color
methods.description: Resets the color for the given column to default.

methods.name: deselect
methods.description: Deselects the given column.

methods.name: erase_button
methods.description: Removes the button at index [code]button_idx[/code] in column [code]column[/code].

methods.name: get_button
methods.description: Returns the [Texture] of the button at index [code]button_idx[/code] in column [code]column[/code].

methods.name: get_button_count
methods.description: Returns the number of buttons in column [code]column[/code]. May be used to get the most recently added button's index, if no index was specified.

methods.name: get_cell_mode
methods.description: Returns the column's cell mode. See [code]CELL_MODE_*[/code] constants.

methods.name: get_children
methods.description: Returns the TreeItem's child items.

methods.name: get_custom_bg_color
methods.description: Returns the custom background color of column [code]column[/code].

methods.name: get_custom_minimum_height
methods.description: Returns the custom minimum height.

methods.name: get_expand_right
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if [code]expand_right[/code] is set.

methods.name: get_icon
methods.description: Returns the given column's icon [Texture]. Error if no icon is set.

methods.name: get_icon_max_width
methods.description: Returns the column's icon's maximum width.

methods.name: get_icon_region
methods.description: Returns the icon [Texture] region as [Rect2].

methods.name: get_next
methods.description: Returns the next TreeItem in the tree.

methods.name: get_next_visible
methods.description: Returns the next visible TreeItem in the tree.

methods.name: get_parent
methods.description: Returns the parent TreeItem.

methods.name: get_prev
methods.description: Returns the previous TreeItem in the tree.

methods.name: get_prev_visible
methods.description: Returns the previous visible TreeItem in the tree.

methods.name: get_text
methods.description: Returns the given column's text.

methods.name: get_text_align
methods.description: Returns the given column's text alignment.

methods.name: get_tooltip
methods.description: Returns the given column's tooltip.

methods.name: is_button_disabled
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the button at index [code]button_idx[/code] for the given column is disabled.

methods.name: is_checked
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if the given column is checked.

methods.name: is_collapsed
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this TreeItem is collapsed.

methods.name: is_editable
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if column [code]column[/code] is editable.

methods.name: is_folding_disabled
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if folding is disabled for this TreeItem.

methods.name: is_selectable
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if column [code]column[/code] is selectable.

methods.name: is_selected
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if column [code]column[/code] is selected.

methods.name: move_to_bottom
methods.description: Moves this TreeItem to the bottom in the [Tree] hierarchy.

methods.name: move_to_top
methods.description: Moves this TreeItem to the top in the [Tree] hierarchy.

methods.name: remove_child
methods.description: Removes the child TreeItem at index [code]index[/code].

methods.name: select
methods.description: Selects the column [code]column[/code].

methods.name: set_button
methods.description: Sets the given column's button [Texture] at index [code]button_idx[/code] to [code]button[/code].

methods.name: set_cell_mode
methods.description: Sets the given column's cell mode to [code]mode[/code]. See [code]CELL_MODE_*[/code] constants.

methods.name: set_checked
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the column [code]column[/code] is checked.

methods.name: set_collapsed
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the TreeItem is collapsed.

methods.name: set_custom_bg_color
methods.description: Sets the given column's custom background color and whether to just use it as an outline.

methods.name: set_custom_color
methods.description: Sets the given column's custom color.

methods.name: set_custom_draw
methods.description: Sets the given column's custom draw callback to [code]callback[/code] method on [code]object[/code].

methods.name: set_custom_minimum_height
methods.description: Sets the custom minimum height of this TreeItem.

methods.name: set_disable_folding
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] folding is disabled for this TreeItem.

methods.name: set_editable
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] column [code]column[/code] is editable.

methods.name: set_expand_right
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] column [code]column[/code] is expanded to the right.

methods.name: set_icon
methods.description: Sets the given column's icon [Texture].

methods.name: set_icon_max_width
methods.description: Sets the given column's icon's maximum width.

methods.name: set_icon_region
methods.description: Sets the given column's icon's texture region.

methods.name: set_selectable
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the given column is selectable.

methods.name: set_text_align
methods.description: Sets the given column's text alignment. See [code]ALIGN_*[/code] constants.

methods.name: set_tooltip
methods.description: Sets the given column's tooltip text.

constants.name: CELL_MODE_STRING
constants.description: Cell contains a string.

constants.name: CELL_MODE_CHECK
constants.description: Cell can be checked.

constants.name: CELL_MODE_RANGE
constants.description: Cell contains a range.

constants.name: CELL_MODE_RANGE_EXPRESSION
constants.description: Cell contains a range expression.

constants.name: CELL_MODE_ICON
constants.description: Cell contains an icon.

constants.name: ALIGN_LEFT
constants.description: Align text to the left. See [code]set_text_align()[/code].

constants.name: ALIGN_CENTER
constants.description: Center text. See [code]set_text_align()[/code].

constants.name: ALIGN_RIGHT
constants.description: Align text to the right. See [code]set_text_align()[/code].

RigidBody2D.name: RigidBody2D
RigidBody2D.brief_description: Physics Body whose position is determined through physics simulation in 2D space.
RigidBody2D.description:
This is the node that implements full 2D physics. This means that you do not control a RigidBody2D directly. Instead you can apply forces to it (gravity, impulses, etc.), and the physics simulation will calculate the resulting movement, collision, bouncing, rotating, etc.
		This node can use custom force integration, for writing complex physics motion behavior per node.
		This node can shift state between regular Rigid body, Kinematic, Character or Static.
		Character mode forbids this node from being rotated.
		As a warning, don't change RigidBody2D's position every frame or very often. Sporadic changes work fine, but physics runs at a different granularity (fixed hz) than usual rendering (process callback) and maybe even in a separate thread, so changing this from a process loop will yield strange behavior.

methods.name: _integrate_forces
methods.description: Called during physics processing, allowing you to read and safely modify the simulation state for the object. By default it works in addition to the usual physics behavior, but [method set_use_custom_integrator] allows you to disable the default behavior and do fully custom force integration for a body.

methods.name: add_force
methods.description: Add a positioned force to the applied force and torque. As with [method apply_impulse], both the force and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates.

methods.name: apply_impulse
methods.description: Apply a positioned impulse (which will be affected by the body mass and shape). This is the equivalent of hitting a billiard ball with a cue: a force that is applied once, and only once. Both the impulse and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates.

methods.name: get_angular_damp
methods.description: Return the angular damp for this body.

methods.name: get_angular_velocity
methods.description: Return the body angular velocity. This changes by physics granularity. See [method set_angular_velocity].

methods.name: get_applied_force
methods.description: Return the applied force vector.

methods.name: get_applied_torque
methods.description: Return the torque which is being applied to this body.

methods.name: get_bounce
methods.description: Return the body bounciness.

methods.name: get_colliding_bodies
methods.description: Return a list of the bodies colliding with this one. By default, number of max contacts reported is at 0 , see [method set_max_contacts_reported] to increase it. You must also enable contact monitor, see [method set_contact_monitor]

methods.name: get_continuous_collision_detection_mode
methods.description: Return whether this body is using continuous collision detection.

methods.name: get_friction
methods.description: Return the body friction.

methods.name: get_gravity_scale
methods.description: Return the gravity factor.

methods.name: get_inertia
methods.description: Return the body's moment of inertia. This is usually automatically computed from the mass and the shapes. Note that this doesn't seem to work in a [code]_ready[/code] function: it apparently has not been auto-computed yet.

methods.name: get_linear_damp
methods.description: Return the linear damp for this body.

methods.name: get_linear_velocity
methods.description: Return the body linear velocity. This changes by physics granularity. See [method set_linear_velocity].

methods.name: get_mass
methods.description: Return the body mass.

methods.name: get_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Return the maximum contacts that can be reported. See [method set_max_contacts_reported].

methods.name: get_mode
methods.description: Return the current body mode, see [method set_mode].

methods.name: get_weight
methods.description: Return the body weight given standard earth-weight (gravity 9.8).

methods.name: is_able_to_sleep
methods.description: Return true if the body has the ability to fall asleep when not moving. See [method set_can_sleep].

methods.name: is_contact_monitor_enabled
methods.description: Return whether contact monitoring is enabled.

methods.name: is_sleeping
methods.description: Return whether the body is sleeping.

methods.name: is_using_custom_integrator
methods.description: Return true if the body is not doing any built-in force integration.

methods.name: set_angular_damp
methods.description: Set the angular damp for this body. If this value is different from -1, any angular damp derived from the world or areas will be overridden.

methods.name: set_angular_velocity
methods.description: Set the body angular velocity. Can be used sporadically, but [b]DON'T SET THIS IN EVERY FRAME[/b], because physics may be running in another thread and definitely runs at a different granularity. Use [method _integrate_forces] as your process loop if you want to have precise control of the body state.

methods.name: set_applied_force
methods.description: Set the applied force vector. This is the equivalent of pushing a box over the ground: the force applied is applied constantly.

methods.name: set_applied_torque
methods.description: Set a constant torque which will be applied to this body.

methods.name: set_axis_velocity
methods.description: Set an axis velocity. The velocity in the given vector axis will be set as the given vector length. This is useful for jumping behavior.

methods.name: set_bounce
methods.description: Set the body bounciness, from 0 (no bounce) to 1 (full bounce).

methods.name: set_can_sleep
methods.description:
Set the body ability to fall asleep when not moving. This saves an enormous amount of processor time when there are plenty of rigid bodies (non static) in a scene.
				Sleeping bodies are not affected by forces until a collision or an [method apply_impulse] / [method set_applied_force] wakes them up. Until then, they behave like a static body.

methods.name: set_contact_monitor
methods.description: Enable contact monitoring. This allows the body to emit signals when it collides with another.

methods.name: set_continuous_collision_detection_mode
methods.description:
Set the continuous collision detection mode from the enum CCD_MODE_*.
				Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will collide, instead of moving it and correcting its movement if it collided. The first is more precise, and misses less impacts by small, fast-moving objects. The second is faster to compute, but can miss small, fast-moving objects.

methods.name: set_friction
methods.description: Set the body friction, from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (full friction).

methods.name: set_gravity_scale
methods.description: Set the gravity factor. This factor multiplies gravity intensity just for this body.

methods.name: set_inertia
methods.description: Set the body's moment of inertia. This is like mass, but for rotation: it determines how much torque it takes to rotate the body. The moment of inertia is usually computed automatically from the mass and the shapes, but this function allows you to set a custom value. Set 0 (or negative) inertia to return to automatically computing it.

methods.name: set_linear_damp
methods.description: Set the linear damp for this body. If this value is different from -1, any linear damp derived from the world or areas will be overridden.

methods.name: set_linear_velocity
methods.description: Set the body linear velocity. Can be used sporadically, but [b]DON'T SET THIS IN EVERY FRAME[/b], because physics may be running in another thread and definitely runs at a different granularity. Use [method _integrate_forces] as your process loop if you want to have precise control of the body state.

methods.name: set_mass
methods.description: Set the body mass.

methods.name: set_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Set the maximum contacts to report. Bodies can keep a log of the contacts with other bodies, this is enabled by setting the maximum amount of contacts reported to a number greater than 0.

methods.name: set_mode
methods.description: Set the body mode, from the MODE_* enum. This allows to change to a static body or a character body.

methods.name: set_sleeping
methods.description: Set whether a body is sleeping or not. Sleeping bodies are not affected by forces until a collision or an [method apply_impulse] / [method set_applied_force] wakes them up. Until then, they behave like a static body.

methods.name: set_use_custom_integrator
methods.description: Pass true to disable the internal force integration (like gravity or air friction) for this body. Other than collision response, the body will only move as determined by the [method _integrate_forces] function, if defined.

methods.name: set_weight
methods.description: Set the body weight given standard earth-weight (gravity 9.8). Not really useful for 2D since most measures for this node are in pixels.

methods.name: test_motion
methods.description: Return whether the body would collide, if it tried to move in the given vector. This method allows two extra parameters: A margin, which increases slightly the size of the shapes involved in the collision detection, and an object of type [Physics2DTestMotionResult], which will store additional information about the collision (should there be one).

signals.name: body_entered
signals.description: Emitted when a body enters into contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.

signals.name: body_exited
signals.description: Emitted when a body exits contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.

signals.name: body_shape_entered
signals.description:
Emitted when a body enters into contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.
				This signal not only receives the body that collided with this one, but also its [RID] (body_id), the shape index from the colliding body (body_shape), and the shape index from this body (local_shape) the other body collided with.

signals.name: body_shape_exited
signals.description:
Emitted when a body shape exits contact with this one. Contact monitor and contacts reported must be enabled for this to work.
				This signal not only receives the body that stopped colliding with this one, but also its [RID] (body_id), the shape index from the colliding body (body_shape), and the shape index from this body (local_shape) the other body stopped colliding with.

signals.name: sleeping_state_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the body changes its sleeping state. Either by sleeping or waking up.

constants.name: MODE_STATIC
constants.description: Static mode. The body behaves like a [StaticBody2D], and can only move by user code.

constants.name: MODE_KINEMATIC
constants.description: Kinematic body. The body behaves like a [KinematicBody2D], and can only move by user code.

constants.name: MODE_RIGID
constants.description: Rigid body. This is the "natural" state of a rigid body. It is affected by forces, and can move, rotate, and be affected by user code.

constants.name: MODE_CHARACTER
constants.description: Character body. This behaves like a rigid body, but can not rotate.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_DISABLED
constants.description: Disables continuous collision detection. This is the fastest way to detect body collisions, but can miss small, fast-moving objects.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_CAST_RAY
constants.description: Enables continuous collision detection by raycasting. It is faster than shapecasting, but less precise.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_CAST_SHAPE
constants.description: Enables continuous collision detection by shapecasting. It is the slowest CCD method, and the most precise.

properties.name: angular_damp
properties.description: Damps RigidBody2D's rotational forces.

properties.name: angular_velocity
properties.description: RigidBody2D's rotational velocity.

properties.name: bounce
properties.description: RigidBody2D's bounciness.

properties.name: can_sleep
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] RigidBody2D will not calculate forces and will act as a static body while there is no movement. It will wake up when other forces are applied through other collisions or when the [code]apply_impulse[/code] method is used. Default value: [code]true[/code]

properties.name: contact_monitor
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] RigidBody2D will emit signals when it collides with another RigidBody2D.

properties.name: contacts_reported
properties.description: The maximum contacts to report. Bodies can keep a log of the contacts with other bodies, this is enabled by setting the maximum amount of contacts reported to a number greater than 0.

properties.name: continuous_cd
properties.description:
If [code]true[/code] continuous collision detection is used. Default value: [code]false[/code]
			Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will collide, instead of moving it and correcting its movement if it collided. Continuous collision detection is more precise, and misses less impacts by small, fast-moving objects. Not using continuous collision detection is faster to compute, but can miss small, fast-moving objects.

properties.name: custom_integrator
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] internal force integration will be disabled (like gravity or air friction) for this body. Other than collision response, the body will only move as determined by the [method _integrate_forces] function, if defined.

properties.name: friction
properties.description: The body friction, from 0 (frictionless) to 1 (max friction).

properties.name: gravity_scale
properties.description: This is multiplied by the global 2D gravity setting found in "Project > Project Settings > Physics > 2d" to produce RigidBody2D's gravity. E.g. a value of 1 will be normal gravity, 2 will apply double gravity, and 0.5 will apply half gravity to this object.

properties.name: linear_damp
properties.description: RigidBody2D's linear damp. Default of -1, cannot be less than -1. If this value is different from -1, any linear damp derived from the world or areas will be overridden.

properties.name: linear_velocity
properties.description: RigidBody2D's linear velocity. Can be used sporadically, but [b]DON'T SET THIS IN EVERY FRAME[/b], because physics may run in another thread and runs at a different granularity. Use [method _integrate_forces] as your process loop for precise control of the body state.

properties.name: mass
properties.description: RigidBody2D's mass.

properties.name: mode
properties.description: The body mode from the MODE_* enum. Modes include: MODE_STATIC, MODE_KINEMATIC, MODE_RIGID, and MODE_CHARACTER.

properties.name: sleeping
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] RigidBody2D is sleeping and will not calculate forces until woken up by a collision or the [code]apply_impulse[/code] method.

properties.name: weight
properties.description: RigidBody2D's weight based on its mass and the global 2D gravity. Global values are set in "Project > Project Settings > Physics > 2d".

RayCast2D.name: RayCast2D
RayCast2D.brief_description: Query the closest object intersecting a ray.
RayCast2D.description:
A RayCast represents a line from its origin to its destination position, [code]cast_to[/code]. It is used to query the 2D space in order to find the closest object along the path of the ray.
		RayCast2D can ignore some objects by adding them to the exception list via [code]add_exception[/code], by setting proper filtering with collision layers, or by filtering object types with type masks.
		Only enabled raycasts will be able to query the space and report collisions.
		RayCast2D calculates intersection every physics frame (see [Node]), and the result is cached so it can be used later until the next frame. If multiple queries are required between physics frames (or during the same frame) use [method force_raycast_update] after adjusting the raycast.

methods.name: add_exception
methods.description: Adds a collision exception so the ray does not report collisions with the specified node.

methods.name: add_exception_rid
methods.description: Adds a collision exception so the ray does not report collisions with the specified [RID].

methods.name: clear_exceptions
methods.description: Removes all collision exceptions for this ray.

methods.name: force_raycast_update
methods.description: Updates the collision information for the ray.  Use this method to update the collision information immediately instead of waiting for the next [code]_physics_process[/code] call, for example if the ray or its parent has changed state. Note: [code]enabled == true[/code] is not required for this to work.

methods.name: get_cast_to
methods.description: Return the destination point of this ray object.

methods.name: get_collider
get_collider_shape
get_collision_layer
methods.description: Returns the collision layer for this ray.

methods.name: get_collision_normal
methods.description: Returns the normal of the intersecting object's shape at the collision point.

methods.name: get_collision_point
methods.description: Returns the collision point at which the ray intersects the closest object. Note: this point is in the [b]global[/b] coordinate system.

methods.name: get_exclude_parent_body
methods.description: Returns whether this ray should hit your parent node, if it's a body.

methods.name: get_type_mask
methods.description: Returns the type mask (types of objects to detect) for this ray. The value is a sum (bitwise OR'd) of constants available for [Physics2DDirectSpaceState].

methods.name: is_colliding
methods.description: Return whether the closest object the ray is pointing to is colliding with the vector (considering the vector length).

methods.name: is_enabled
methods.description: Returns whether this raycast is enabled or not.

methods.name: remove_exception
methods.description: Removes a collision exception so the ray does report collisions with the specified node.

methods.name: remove_exception_rid
methods.description: Removes a collision exception so the ray does report collisions with the specified [RID].

methods.name: set_cast_to
methods.description: Sets the ray destination point, so that the ray will test from the ray's origin to [code]local_point[/code]

methods.name: set_collision_layer
methods.description: Set the mask to filter objects. Only objects with at least the same mask element set will be detected.

methods.name: set_enabled
methods.description: Enables the RayCast2D. Only enabled raycasts will be able to query the space and report collisions.

methods.name: set_exclude_parent_body
methods.description: Toggle whether this ray should hit your parent node, if it's a body.

methods.name: set_type_mask
methods.description: Set the types of objects to detect. For [code]mask[/code] use a logic sum (OR operation) of constants defined in [Physics2DDirectSpaceState], eg. [code]Physics2DDirectSpaceState.TYPE_MASK_STATIC_BODY | Physics2DDirectSpaceState.TYPE_MASK_KINEMATIC_BODY[/code] to detect only those two types.

properties.name: cast_to
properties.description: The ray's destination point, relative to the RayCast's [code]position[/code].

properties.name: collision_layer
properties.description: The RayCast2D's collision layer(s). Only bodies in the same collision layer(s) will be detected.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], collisions will be reported. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: exclude_parent
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], the parent node will be excluded from collision detection. Default value: [code]true[/code].

properties.name: type_mask
properties.description:
Object types to detect using a logical sum (OR operation) of type constants defined in [Physics2DDirectSpaceState].
			Example:
			[codeblock]
			RayCast.type_mask = Physics2DDirectSpaceState.TYPE_MASK_STATIC_BODY | Physics2DDirectSpaceState.TYPE_MASK_KINEMATIC_BODY
			[/codeblock]

Color.name: Color
Color.brief_description: Color in RGBA format with some support for ARGB format.
Color.description: A color is represented as red, green and blue (r,g,b) components. Additionally, "a" represents the alpha component, often used for transparency. Values are in floating point and usually range from 0 to 1.  Some methods (such as set_modulate(color)) may accept values > 1.

methods.name: Color
methods.description:
Constructs a color from an RGBA profile using values between 0 and 1 (float).
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(0.2, 1.0, .7, .8) # a color of an RGBA(51, 255, 178, 204)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: Color
methods.description:
Constructs a color from an RGB profile using values between 0 and 1 (float). Alpha will always be 1.
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(0.2, 1.0, .7) # a color of an RGBA(51, 255, 178, 255)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: Color
methods.description:
Constructs a color from a 32-bit integer (each byte represents a component of the RGBA profile).
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(274) # a color of an RGBA(0, 0, 1, 18)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: Color
methods.description:
Constructs a color from an HTML hexadecimal color string in ARGB or RGB format.
				The following string formats are supported:
					[code]"#ff00ff00"[/code] - ARGB format with '#'
					[code]"ff00ff00"[/code] - ARGB format
					[code]"#ff00ff"[/code] - RGB format with '#'
					[code]"ff00ff"[/code] - RGB format
				[codeblock]
				# The following code creates the same color of an RGBA(178, 217, 10, 255)
				var c1 = Color("#ffb2d90a") # ARGB format with '#'
				var c2 = Color("ffb2d90a")  # ARGB format
				var c3 = Color("#b2d90a")   # RGB format with '#'
				var c4 = Color("b2d90a")    # RGB format
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: blend
methods.description:
Returns a new color resulting from blending this color over another color. If the color is opaque, the result would also be opaque. The other color could then take a range of values with different alpha values.
				[codeblock]
				var bg = Color(0.0, 1.0, 0.0, 0.5) # Green with alpha of 50%
				var fg = Color(1.0, 0.0, 0.0, .5) # Red with alpha of 50%
				var blendedColor = bg.blend(fg) # Brown with alpha of 75%
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: contrasted
gray
methods.description:
Returns the color's grayscale.
				The gray is calculated by (r + g + b) / 3.
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(0.2, 0.45, 0.82)
				var gray = c.gray() # a value of 0.466667
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: inverted
linear_interpolate
to_argb32
methods.description:
Returns the color's 32-bit integer in ARGB format (each byte represents a component of the ARGB profile). More compatible with DirectX.
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(1, .5, .2)
				print(str(c.to_32())) # prints 4294934323
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: to_html
methods.description:
Returns the color's HTML hexadecimal color string in ARGB format (ex: [code]ff34f822[/code]).
				Optionally flag 'false' to not include alpha in hexadecimal string.
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(1, 1, 1, .5)
				var s1 = c.to_html() # Results "7fffffff"
				var s2 = c.to_html(false) # Results 'ffffff'
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: to_rgba32
methods.description:
Returns the color's 32-bit integer in ARGB format (each byte represents a component of the ARGB profile).
				[codeblock]
				var c = Color(1, .5, .2)
				print(str(c.to_32())) # prints 4294934323
				[/codeblock]

				[i]This is same as [method to_ARGB32] but may be changed later to support RGBA format instead[/i].

properties.name: a
properties.description: Alpha (0 to 1)

properties.name: a8
properties.description: Alpha (0 to 255)

properties.name: b
properties.description: Blue (0 to 1)

properties.name: b8
properties.description: Blue (0 to 255)

properties.name: g
properties.description: Green (0 to 1)

properties.name: g8
properties.description: Green (0 to 255)

properties.name: h
properties.description: Hue (0 to 1)

properties.name: r
properties.description: Red (0 to 1)

properties.name: r8
properties.description: Red (0 to 255)

properties.name: s
properties.description: Saturation (0 to 1)

properties.name: v
properties.description: Value (0 to 1)

CollisionObject.name: CollisionObject
CollisionObject.description: CollisionObject is the base class for physics objects. It can hold any number of collision [Shape]\ s. Each shape must be assigned to a [i]shape owner[/i]. The CollisionObject can have any number of shape owners. Shape owners are not nodes and do not appear in the editor, but are accessible through code using the [code]shape_owner_*[/code] methods.

methods.name: create_shape_owner
methods.description: Creates a new shape owner for the given object. Returns [code]owner_id[/code] of the new owner for future reference.

methods.name: get_rid
methods.description: Returns the object's [RID].

methods.name: get_shape_owners
methods.description: Returns an [Array] of [code]owner_id[/code] identifiers. You can use these ids in other methods that take [code]owner_id[/code] as an argument.

methods.name: is_shape_owner_disabled
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the shape owner and its shapes are disabled.

methods.name: remove_shape_owner
methods.description: Removes the given shape owner.

methods.name: shape_find_owner
methods.description: Returns the [code]owner_id[/code] of the given shape.

methods.name: shape_owner_add_shape
methods.description: Adds a [Shape] to the shape owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_clear_shapes
methods.description: Removes all shapes from the shape owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_get_owner
methods.description: Returns the parent object of the given shape owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_get_shape
methods.description: Returns the [Shape] with the given id from the given shape owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_get_shape_count
methods.description: Returns the number of shapes the given shape owner contains.

methods.name: shape_owner_get_transform
methods.description: Returns the shape owner's [Transform].

methods.name: shape_owner_remove_shape
methods.description: Removes a shape from the given shape owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_set_disabled
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] disables the given shape owner.

methods.name: shape_owner_set_transform
methods.description: Sets the [Transform] of the given shape owner.

signals.name: mouse_entered
signals.description: Emitted when the mouse pointer enters any of this object's shapes.

signals.name: mouse_exited
signals.description: Emitted when the mouse pointer exits all this object's shapes.

ParallaxBackground.name: ParallaxBackground
ParallaxBackground.brief_description: A node used to create a parallax scrolling background.
ParallaxBackground.description: A ParallaxBackground will use one or more [ParallaxLayer] nodes to create a parallax scrolling background. Each [ParallaxLayer] can be set to move at different speeds relative to the camera movement, this can be used to create an illusion of depth in a 2D game.

methods.name: get_limit_begin
methods.description: Return the beginning limit.

methods.name: get_limit_end
methods.description: Return the ending limit.

methods.name: get_scroll_base_offset
methods.description: Return the base offset.

methods.name: get_scroll_base_scale
methods.description: Return the base motion scale.

methods.name: is_ignore_camera_zoom
methods.description: Return ignoring camera zoom.

methods.name: set_ignore_camera_zoom
methods.description: Set to true for all child [ParallaxLayer] nodes to not be affected by the zoom level of the camera.

methods.name: set_limit_begin
methods.description: Set the left and top limits in pixels for scrolling to begin. If the camera is outside of this limit the background will not continue to scroll. If an axis is greater than or equal to the corresponding axis of limit_end, then it will not limit scrolling for that axis.

methods.name: set_limit_end
methods.description: Set the right and bottom limits in pixels for scrolling to end. If the camera is outside of this limit the background will not continue to scroll. If an axis is less than or equal to the corresponding axis of limit_begin, then it will not limit scrolling for that axis.

methods.name: set_scroll_base_offset
methods.description: Set the base offset in pixels of all children [ParallaxLayer] nodes.

methods.name: set_scroll_base_scale
methods.description: Set the base motion scale of all children [ParallaxLayer] nodes.

InputEventMouseMotion.name: InputEventMouseMotion
InputEventMouseMotion.brief_description: Input event type for mouse motion events.

properties.name: relative
properties.description: Position of the mouse pointer relative to the previous mouse position.

properties.name: speed
properties.description: Speed of the mouse pointer.

ColorPicker.name: ColorPicker
ColorPicker.description: This is a simple color picker [Control]. It's useful for selecting a color from an RGB/RGBA colorspace.

methods.name: add_preset
methods.description: Adds the current selected to color to a list of colors (presets), the presets will be displayed in the color picker and the user will be able to select them, notice that the presets list is only for this color picker.

methods.name: get_pick_color
methods.description: Gets the current color.

methods.name: is_editing_alpha
methods.description: Returns whether the color has transparency or not.

methods.name: is_raw_mode
methods.description: Returns whether this color picker is in raw mode or not, raw mode will allow the color R, G, B component values to go beyond 1, you have to consider that the max value for color components is 1, going beyond that value will not have effect in the color, but can be used for special operations that require it (like tinting without darkening or rendering sprites in HDR).

methods.name: set_edit_alpha
methods.description: Set true if you want the color to have an alpha channel (transparency), or false if you want a solid color.

methods.name: set_pick_color
methods.description: Select the current color.

methods.name: set_raw_mode
methods.description: Set whether this color picker is using raw mode or not, see [method is_raw_mode].

signals.name: color_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the color is changed.

Marshalls.name: Marshalls

GraphNode.name: GraphNode
GraphNode.brief_description: A GraphNode is a container with several input and output slots allowing connections between GraphNodes. Slots can have different, incompatible types.
GraphNode.description: A GraphNode is a container defined by a title. It can have 1 or more input and output slots, which can be enabled (shown) or disabled (not shown) and have different (incompatible) types. Colors can also be assigned to slots. A tuple of input and output slots is defined for each GUI element included in the GraphNode. Input and output connections are left and right slots, but only enabled slots are counted as connections.
