methods.name: remove
methods.description: Remove an element from the array by index.

methods.name: resize
methods.description: Set the size of the array. If the array is grown reserve elements at the end of the array. If the array is shrunk truncate the array to the new size.

methods.name: set
methods.description: Change the [Color] at the given index.

methods.name: size
methods.description: Return the size of the array.

ParticlesMaterial.name: ParticlesMaterial
ParticlesMaterial.description:
ParticlesMaterial defines particle properties and behavior. It is used in the [code]process_material[/code] of [Particles] and [Particles2D] emitter nodes.
		Some of this material's properties are applied to each particle when emitted, while others can have a [CurveTexture] applied to vary values over the lifetime of the particle.

constants.name: PARAM_INITIAL_LINEAR_VELOCITY
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set initial velocity properties.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGULAR_VELOCITY
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set angular velocity properties.

constants.name: PARAM_ORBIT_VELOCITY
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set orbital_velocity properties.

constants.name: PARAM_LINEAR_ACCEL
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set linear acceleration properties.

constants.name: PARAM_RADIAL_ACCEL
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set radial acceleration properties.

constants.name: PARAM_TANGENTIAL_ACCEL
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set tangential acceleration properties.

constants.name: PARAM_DAMPING
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set damping properties.

constants.name: PARAM_ANGLE
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set angle properties.

constants.name: PARAM_SCALE
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set scale properties.

constants.name: PARAM_HUE_VARIATION
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set hue_variation properties.

constants.name: PARAM_ANIM_SPEED
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set animation speed properties.

constants.name: PARAM_ANIM_OFFSET
constants.description: Use with [method set_param], [method set_param_randomness], and [method set_param_texture] to set animation offset properties.

constants.name: FLAG_ALIGN_Y_TO_VELOCITY
constants.description: Use with [method set_flag] to set [member flag_align_y].

constants.name: FLAG_ROTATE_Y
constants.description: Use with [method set_flag] to set [member flag_rotate_y]

constants.name: EMISSION_SHAPE_POINT
constants.description: All particles will be emitted from a single point.

constants.name: EMISSION_SHAPE_SPHERE
constants.description: Particles will be emitted in the volume of a sphere.

constants.name: EMISSION_SHAPE_BOX
constants.description: Particles will be emitted in the volume of a box.

properties.name: angle
properties.description: Initial rotation applied to each particle.

properties.name: angle_curve
properties.description: Each particle's rotation will be animated along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: angle_random
properties.description: Rotation randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: angular_velocity
properties.description: Initial angular velocity applied to each particle.

properties.name: angular_velocity_curve
properties.description: Each particle's angular velocity will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: angular_velocity_random
properties.description: Angular velocity randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: anim_loop
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] animation will loop. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: anim_offset
properties.description: Particle animation offset.

properties.name: anim_offset_curve
properties.description: Each particle's animation offset will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: anim_offset_random
properties.description: Animation offset randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: anim_speed
properties.description: Particle animation speed.

properties.name: anim_speed_curve
properties.description: Each particle's animation speed will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: anim_speed_random
properties.description: Animation speed randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: color
properties.description: Each particle's initial color. If the [Particle2D]'s [code]texture[/code] is defined, it will be multiplied by this color.

properties.name: color_ramp
properties.description: Each particle's color will vary along this [GradientTexture].

properties.name: damping
properties.description: The rate at which particles lose velocity.

properties.name: damping_curve
properties.description: Damping will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: damping_random
properties.description: Damping randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: emission_box_extents
properties.description: The box's extents if [code]emission_shape[/code] is set to [code]EMISSION_SHAPE_BOX[/code].

properties.name: emission_point_count
properties.description: The number of emission points if [code]emission_shape[/code] is set to [code]EMISSION_SHAPE_POINTS[/code] or [code]EMISSION_SHAPE_DIRECTED_POINTS[/code].

properties.name: emission_shape
properties.description: Particles will be emitted inside this region. Use [code]EMISSION_SHAPE_*[/code] constants for values. Default value: [code]EMISSION_SHAPE_POINT[/code].

properties.name: emission_sphere_radius
properties.description: The sphere's radius if [code]emission_shape[/code] is set to [code]EMISSION_SHAPE_SPHERE[/code].

properties.name: flag_disable_z
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] particles will not move on the z axis. Default value: [code]true[/code] for [Particles2D], [code]false[/code] for [Particles].

properties.name: gravity
properties.description: Gravity applied to every particle. Default value: [code](0, 98, 0)[/code].

properties.name: hue_variation
properties.description: Initial hue variation applied to each particle.

properties.name: hue_variation_curve
properties.description: Each particle's hue will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: hue_variation_random
properties.description: Hue variation randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: initial_velocity
properties.description: Initial velocity for each particle.

properties.name: initial_velocity_random
properties.description: Initial velocity randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: linear_accel
properties.description: Linear acceleration applied to each particle.

properties.name: linear_accel_curve
properties.description: Each particle's linear acceleration will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: linear_accel_random
properties.description: Linear acceleration randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: orbit_velocity
properties.description: Orbital velocity applied to each particle.

properties.name: orbit_velocity_curve
properties.description: Each particle's orbital velocity will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: orbit_velocity_random
properties.description: Orbital velocity randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: radial_accel
properties.description: Linear acceleration applied to each particle.

properties.name: radial_accel_curve
properties.description: Each particle's radial acceleration will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: radial_accel_random
properties.description: Radial acceleration randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: scale
properties.description: Initial scale applied to each particle.

properties.name: scale_curve
properties.description: Each particle's scale will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: scale_random
properties.description: Scale randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: spread
properties.description: Each particle's initial direction range from [code]+spread[/code] to [code]-spread[/code] degrees. Default value: [code]45[/code].

properties.name: tangential_accel
properties.description: Tangential acceleration applied to each particle. Tangential acceleration is perpendicular to the particle's velocity.

properties.name: tangential_accel_curve
properties.description: Each particle's tangential acceleration will vary along this [CurveTexture].

properties.name: tangential_accel_random
properties.description: Tangential acceleration randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: trail_color_modifier
properties.description: Trail particles' color will vary along this [GradientTexture].

properties.name: trail_divisor
properties.description: Emitter will emit [code]amount[/code] divided by [code]trail_divisor[/code] particles. The remaining particles will be used as trail(s).

properties.name: trail_size_modifier
properties.description: Trail particles' size will vary along this [CurveTexture].

ARVRCamera.name: ARVRCamera
ARVRCamera.brief_description: A camera node with a few overrules for AR/VR applied such as location tracking.
ARVRCamera.description:
This is a helper spatial node for our camera, note that if stereoscopic rendering is applicable (VR-HMD) most of the camera properties are ignored as the HMD information overrides them. The only properties that can be trusted are the near and far planes.
		The position and orientation of this node is automatically updated by the ARVR Server to represent the location of the HMD if such tracking is available and can thus be used by game logic. Note that in contrast to the ARVR Controller the render thread has access to the most up to date tracking data of the HMD and the location of the ARVRCamera can lag a few milliseconds behind what is used for rendering as a result.

HSeparator.name: HSeparator
HSeparator.description: Horizontal separator. See [Separator]. It is used to separate objects vertically, though (but it looks horizontal!).

ScrollContainer.name: ScrollContainer
ScrollContainer.brief_description: A helper node for displaying scrollable elements (e.g. lists).
ScrollContainer.description: A ScrollContainer node with a [Control] child and scrollbar child ([HScrollbar], [VScrollBar], or both) will only draw the Control within the ScrollContainer area.  Scrollbars will automatically be drawn at the right (for vertical) or bottom (for horizontal) and will enable dragging to move the viewable Control (and its children) within the ScrollContainer.  Scrollbars will also automatically resize the grabber based on the minimum_size of the Control relative to the ScrollContainer.  Works great with a [Panel] control.  You can set EXPAND on children size flags, so they will upscale to ScrollContainer size if ScrollContainer size is bigger (scroll is invisible for chosen dimension).

methods.name: get_h_scroll
methods.description: Return current horizontal scroll value.

methods.name: get_v_scroll
methods.description: Return current vertical scroll value.

methods.name: is_h_scroll_enabled
methods.description: Return true if horizontal scroll is allowed.

methods.name: is_v_scroll_enabled
methods.description: Return true if vertical scroll is allowed.

methods.name: set_enable_h_scroll
methods.description: Set allows horizontal scroll.

methods.name: set_enable_v_scroll
methods.description: Set allows vertical scroll.

methods.name: set_h_scroll
methods.description: Set horizontal scroll value.

methods.name: set_v_scroll
methods.description: Set vertical scroll value.

PackedScene.name: PackedScene
PackedScene.description: TODO: explain ownership, and that node does not need to own itself

methods.name: pack
methods.description: Pack will ignore any sub-nodes not owned by given node. See [method Node.set_owner].

ScrollBar.name: ScrollBar
ScrollBar.description: Scrollbars are a [Range] based [Control], that display a draggable area (the size of the page). Horizontal ([HScrollBar]) and Vertical ([VScrollBar]) versions are available.

Mesh.name: Mesh
Mesh.brief_description: A [Resource] that contains vertex-array based geometry.
Mesh.description: Mesh is a type of [Resource] that contains vertex-array based geometry, divided in [i]surfaces[/i]. Each surface contains a completely separate array and a material used to draw it. Design wise, a mesh with multiple surfaces is preferred to a single surface, because objects created in 3D editing software commonly contain multiple materials.

methods.name: create_convex_shape
methods.description: Calculate a [ConvexPolygonShape] from the mesh.

methods.name: create_outline
methods.description: Calculate an outline mesh at a defined offset (margin) from the original mesh. Note: Typically returns the vertices in reverse order (e.g. clockwise to anti-clockwise).

methods.name: create_trimesh_shape
methods.description: Calculate a [ConcavePolygonShape] from the mesh.

methods.name: generate_triangle_mesh
methods.description: Generate a [TriangleMesh] from the mesh.

methods.name: get_faces
methods.description: Returns all the vertices that make up the faces of the mesh. Each three vertices represent one triangle.

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_POINTS
constants.description: Render array as points (one vertex equals one point).

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_LINES
constants.description: Render array as lines (every two vertices a line is created).

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_LINE_STRIP
constants.description: Render array as line strip.

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_LINE_LOOP
constants.description: Render array as line loop (like line strip, but closed).

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLES
constants.description: Render array as triangles (every three vertices a triangle is created).

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLE_STRIP
constants.description: Render array as triangle strips.

constants.name: PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLE_FAN
constants.description: Render array as triangle fans.

VisualScriptClassConstant.name: VisualScriptClassConstant
VisualScriptClassConstant.brief_description: A Visual Script node representing a constant from a class.
VisualScriptClassConstant.description: A Visual Script node representing a constant from the classes, such as [@GlobalScope.TYPE_INT].

properties.name: base_type
properties.description: The type to get the constant from.

properties.name: constant
properties.description: The name of the constant to return.

Translation.name: Translation
Translation.description: Translations are resources that can be loaded/unloaded on demand. They map a string to another string.

methods.name: add_message
methods.description: Add a message for translation.

methods.name: erase_message
methods.description: Erase a message.

methods.name: get_locale
methods.description: Return the locale of the translation.

methods.name: get_message
methods.description: Return a message for translation.

methods.name: get_message_list
methods.description: Return all the messages (keys).

methods.name: set_locale
methods.description: Set the locale of the translation.

LinkButton.name: LinkButton
LinkButton.brief_description: Simple button used to represent a link to some resource
LinkButton.description: This kind of buttons are primarily used when the interaction with the button causes a context change (like linking to a web page).

methods.name: get_text
methods.description: Returns the text of the button.

methods.name: get_underline_mode
methods.description: Returns the underline mode for this button.

methods.name: set_text
methods.description: Sets the text of the button.

methods.name: set_underline_mode
methods.description: Sets the underline mode for this button, the argument must be one of the [LinkButton] constants (see constants section).

constants.name: UNDERLINE_MODE_ALWAYS
constants.description: The LinkButton will always show an underline at the bottom of its text

constants.name: UNDERLINE_MODE_ON_HOVER
constants.description: The LinkButton will show an underline at the bottom of its text when the mouse cursor is over it.

constants.name: UNDERLINE_MODE_NEVER
constants.description: The LinkButton will never show an underline at the bottom of its text.

Range.name: Range
Range.brief_description: Abstract base class for range-based controls.
Range.description: Range is a base class for [Control] nodes that change a floating point [i]value[/i] between a [i]minimum[/i] and a [i]maximum[/i], using [i]step[/i] and [i]page[/i], for example a [ScrollBar].

methods.name: get_as_ratio
methods.description: Return value mapped to 0 to 1 range.

methods.name: get_max
methods.description: Return the maximum value.

methods.name: get_min
methods.description: Return the minimum value.

methods.name: get_page
methods.description: Return the page size, if page is 0, paging is disabled.

methods.name: get_step
methods.description: Return the stepping, if step is 0, stepping is disabled.

methods.name: set_as_ratio
methods.description: Set value mapped to 0 to 1 (unit) range, it will then be converted to the actual value within min and max.

methods.name: set_min
methods.description: Set minimum value, clamped range value to it if it's less.

methods.name: set_page
methods.description: Set page size. Page is mainly used for scrollbars or anything that controls text scrolling.

methods.name: set_step
methods.description: Set step value. If step is 0, stepping will be disabled.

methods.name: share
methods.description: Binds two Ranges together along with any Ranges previously grouped with either of them. When any of Range's member variables change, it will share the new value with all other Ranges in its group.

methods.name: unshare
methods.description: Stop Range from sharing its member variables with any other Range.

signals.name: changed
signals.description: This signal is emitted when min, max, range or step change.

signals.name: value_changed
signals.description: This signal is emitted when value changes.

properties.name: exp_edit
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] and [code]min_value[/code] is greater than 0, [code]value[/code] will be represented exponentially rather than linearly.

properties.name: max_value
properties.description: Maximum value. Range is clamped if [code]value[/code] is greater than [code]max_value[/code]. Default value: 100.

properties.name: min_value
properties.description: Minimum value. Range is clamped if [code]value[/code] is less than [code]min_value[/code]. Default value: 0.

properties.name: page
properties.description: Page size. Used mainly for [ScrollBar]. ScrollBar's length is its size multiplied by [code]page[/code] over the difference between [code]min_value[/code] and [code]max_value[/code].

properties.name: rounded
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], [code]value[/code] will always be rounded to the nearest integer.

properties.name: step
properties.description: If greater than 0, [code]value[/code] will always be rounded to a multiple of [code]step[/code]. If [code]rounded[/code] is also [code]true[/code], [code]value[/code] will first be rounded to a multiple of [code]step[/code] then rounded to the nearest integer.

properties.name: value
properties.description: Range's current value.

EditorFileSystemDirectory.name: EditorFileSystemDirectory
EditorFileSystemDirectory.brief_description: A diretory for the resource filesystem.

OptionButton.name: OptionButton
OptionButton.brief_description: Button control that provides selectable options when pressed.
OptionButton.description: OptionButton is a type button that provides a selectable list of items when pressed. The item selected becomes the "current" item and is displayed as the button text.

methods.name: add_icon_item
methods.description: Add an item, with a "texture" icon, text "label" and (optionally) id. If no "id" is passed, "id" becomes the item index. New items are appended at the end.

methods.name: add_item
methods.description: Add an item, with text "label" and (optionally) id. If no "id" is passed, "id" becomes the item index. New items are appended at the end.

methods.name: add_separator
methods.description: Add a separator to the list of items. Separators help to group items. Separator also takes up an index and is appended at the end.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear all the items in the [OptionButton].

methods.name: get_item_count
methods.description: Return the amount of items in the OptionButton.

methods.name: get_item_icon
methods.description: Return the icon of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: get_item_id
methods.description: Return the ID of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: get_item_text
methods.description: Return the text of the item at index "idx".

methods.name: get_selected
methods.description: Return the current item index

methods.name: select
methods.description: Select an item by index and make it the current item.

methods.name: set_item_icon
methods.description: Set the icon of an item at index "idx".

methods.name: set_item_id
methods.description: Set the ID of an item at index "idx".

methods.name: set_item_text
methods.description: Set the text of an item at index "idx".

signals.name: item_selected
signals.description: This signal is emitted when the current item was changed by the user. ID of the item selected is passed as argument (if no IDs were added, ID will be just the item index).

ConvexPolygonShape.name: ConvexPolygonShape
ConvexPolygonShape.description: Convex polygon shape resource, which can be added to a [PhysicsBody] or area.

properties.name: points
properties.description: The list of 3D points forming the convex polygon shape.

Polygon2D.name: Polygon2D
Polygon2D.description: A Polygon2D is defined by a set of points. Each point is connected to the next, with the final point being connected to the first, resulting in a closed polygon. Polygon2Ds can be filled with color (solid or gradient) or filled with a given texture.

methods.name: get_color
methods.description: Return the polygon fill color.

methods.name: get_invert
methods.description: Return whether this polygon is inverted or not.

methods.name: get_invert_border
methods.description: Return the added padding around the bounding box.

methods.name: get_offset
methods.description: Return the offset for the polygon vertices.

methods.name: get_polygon
methods.description: Return the set of vertices that defines this polygon.

methods.name: get_texture
methods.description: Return the polygon texture

methods.name: get_texture_offset
methods.description: Return the polygon texture offset.

methods.name: get_texture_rotation
methods.description: Return the rotation in radians of the texture polygon.

methods.name: get_texture_scale
methods.description: Return the uv coordinate multiplier.

methods.name: get_uv
methods.description: Return the texture coordinates associated with every vertex of the polygon.

methods.name: get_vertex_colors
methods.description: Return the list of vertex colors.

methods.name: set_color
methods.description: Set the polygon fill color. If the polygon has a texture defined, the defined texture will be multiplied by the polygon fill color. This, also, is the default color for those vertices that are not defined by [method get_vertex_colors].

methods.name: set_invert
methods.description: Set the polygon as the defined polygon bounding box minus the defined polygon (the defined polygon will appear as a hole on the square that contains the defined polygon).

methods.name: set_invert_border
methods.description: Add extra padding around the bounding box, making it bigger. Too small a value can make the polygon triangulate strangely, due to numerical imprecision.

methods.name: set_offset
methods.description: Set the an offset that will be added to the vertices' position. E.g. if the offset is set to (10,10) then all the polygon points will move 10 units to the right and 10 units to the bottom.

methods.name: set_polygon
methods.description: Define the set of vertices that will represent the polygon.

methods.name: set_texture_offset
methods.description: Set the offset of the polygon texture. Initially the texture will appear anchored to the polygon position, the offset is used to move the texture location away from that point (notice that the texture origin is set to its top left corner, so when offset is 0,0 the top left corner of the texture is at the polygon position), for example setting the offset to 10, 10 will move the texture 10 units to the left and 10 units to the top.

methods.name: set_texture_rotation
methods.description: Set the amount of rotation of the polygon texture, [code]texture_rotation[/code] is specified in radians and clockwise rotation.

methods.name: set_texture_scale
methods.description: Set the value that will multiply the uv coordinates ([method get_uv]) when applying the texture. Larger values make the texture smaller, and vice versa.

methods.name: set_uv
methods.description: Set the texture coordinates for every vertex of the polygon. There should be one uv vertex for every vertex in the polygon. If there are less, the undefined ones will be assumed to be (0,0). Extra uv vertices are ignored.

methods.name: set_vertex_colors
methods.description:
Set the color for each vertex of the polygon. There should be one color for every vertex in the polygon. If there are less, the undefined ones will be assumed to be [method get_color]. Extra color entries are ignored.
	Colors are interpolated between vertices, resulting in smooth gradients when they differ.

properties.name: antialiased
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] polygon edges will be anti-aliased. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: color
properties.description: The polygon's fill color. If [code]texture[/code] is defined, it will be multiplied by this color. It will also be the default color for vertices not set in [code]vertex_colors[/code].

properties.name: invert_border
properties.description: Added padding applied to the bounding box when using [code]invert[/code]. Setting this value too small may result in a "Bad Polygon" error. Default value: [code]100[/code].

properties.name: invert_enable
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] polygon will be inverted, containing the area outside the defined points and extending to the [code]invert_border[/code]. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: offset
properties.description: The offset applied to each vertex.

properties.name: polygon
properties.description: The polygon's list of vertices. The final point will be connected to the first.

properties.name: texture
properties.description: The polygon's fill texture. Use [code]uv[/code] to set texture coordinates.

properties.name: texture_offset
properties.description: Amount to offset the polygon's [code]texture[/code]. If [code](0, 0)[/code] the texture's origin (its top-left corner) will be placed at the polygon's [code]position[/code].

properties.name: texture_rotation
properties.description: The texture's rotation in degrees.

properties.name: texture_scale
properties.description: Amount to multiply the [code]uv[/code] coordinates when using a [code]texture[/code]. Larger values make the texture smaller, and vice versa.

properties.name: uv
properties.description: Texture coordinates for each vertex of the polygon. There should be one [code]uv[/code] per polygon vertex. If there are fewer, undefined vertices will use [code](0, 0)[/code].

properties.name: vertex_colors
properties.description: Color for each vertex. Colors are interpolated between vertices, resulting in smooth gradients. There should be one per polygon vertex. If there are fewer, undefined vertices will use [code]color[/code].

Semaphore.name: Semaphore
Semaphore.description: A synchronization Semaphore. Element used in multi-threadding. Initialized to zero on creation.

methods.name: post
methods.description: Lowers the [Semaphore], allowing one more thread in.

methods.name: wait
methods.description: Tries to wait for the [Semaphore], if its value is zero, blocks until non-zero.

CollisionShape2D.name: CollisionShape2D
CollisionShape2D.brief_description: Node that represents collision shape data in 2D space.
CollisionShape2D.description: Editor facility for creating and editing collision shapes in 2D space. You can use this node to represent all sorts of collision shapes, for example, add this to an [Area2D] to give it a detection shape, or add it to a [PhysicsBody2D] to give create solid object. [b]IMPORTANT[/b]: this is an Editor-only helper to create shapes, use [method get_shape] to get the actual shape.

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: A disabled collision shape has no effect in the world.

properties.name: one_way_collision
properties.description: Sets whether this collision shape should only detect collision on one side (top or bottom).

properties.name: shape
properties.description: The actual shape owned by this collision shape.

methods.name: float
methods.description: Cast a [bool] value to a floating point value, [code]float(true)[/code] will be equals to 1.0 and [code]float(false)[/code] will be equals to 0.0.

methods.name: float
methods.description: Cast an [int] value to a floating point value, [code]float(1)[/code] will be equals to 1.0.

methods.name: float
methods.description: Cast a [String] value to a floating point value. This method accepts float value strings like [code] '1.23' [/code] and exponential notation strings for its parameter so calling [code] float('1e3') [/code] will return 1000.0 and calling [code] float('1e-3') [/code] will return -0.001.

Physics2DServer.name: Physics2DServer
Physics2DServer.description: Physics 2D Server is the server responsible for all 2D physics. It can create many kinds of physics objects, but does not insert them on the node tree.

methods.name: area_add_shape
methods.description: Add a shape to the area, along with a transform matrix. Shapes are usually referenced by their index, so you should track which shape has a given index.

methods.name: area_attach_object_instance_id
methods.description: Assign the area to a descendant of [Object], so it can exist in the node tree.

methods.name: area_clear_shapes
methods.description: Remove all shapes from an area. It does not delete the shapes, so they can be reassigned later.

methods.name: area_create
methods.description: Create an [Area2D].

methods.name: area_get_object_instance_id
methods.description: Get the instance ID of the object the area is assigned to.

methods.name: area_get_param
methods.description: Return an area parameter value.

methods.name: area_get_shape
methods.description: Return the [RID] of the nth shape of an area.

methods.name: area_get_shape_count
methods.description: Return the number of shapes assigned to an area.

methods.name: area_get_shape_transform
methods.description: Return the transform matrix of a shape within an area.

methods.name: area_get_space
methods.description: Return the space assigned to the area.

methods.name: area_get_space_override_mode
methods.description: Return the space override mode for the area.

methods.name: area_get_transform
methods.description: Return the transform matrix for an area.

methods.name: area_remove_shape
methods.description: Remove a shape from an area. It does not delete the shape, so it can be reassigned later.

methods.name: area_set_collision_layer
methods.description: Assign the area to one or many physics layers.

methods.name: area_set_collision_mask
methods.description: Set which physics layers the area will monitor.

methods.name: area_set_monitor_callback
methods.description:
Set the function to call when any body/area enters or exits the area. This callback will be called for any object interacting with the area, and takes five parameters:
				1: AREA_BODY_ADDED or AREA_BODY_REMOVED, depending on whether the object entered or exited the area.
				2: [RID] of the object that entered/exited the area.
				3: Instance ID of the object that entered/exited the area.
				4: The shape index of the object that entered/exited the area.
				5: The shape index of the area where the object entered/exited.

methods.name: area_set_param
methods.description: Set the value for an area parameter. A list of available parameters is on the AREA_PARAM_* constants.

methods.name: area_set_shape
methods.description: Substitute a given area shape by another. The old shape is selected by its index, the new one by its [RID].

methods.name: area_set_shape_transform
methods.description: Set the transform matrix for an area shape.

methods.name: area_set_space
methods.description: Assign a space to the area.

methods.name: area_set_space_override_mode
methods.description: Set the space override mode for the area. The modes are described in the constants AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_*.

methods.name: area_set_transform
methods.description: Set the transform matrix for an area.

methods.name: body_add_collision_exception
methods.description: Add a body to the list of bodies exempt from collisions.

methods.name: body_add_force
methods.description: Add a positioned force to the applied force and torque. As with [method body_apply_impulse], both the force and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates. A force differs from an impulse in that, while the two are forces, the impulse clears itself after being applied.

methods.name: body_add_shape
methods.description: Add a shape to the body, along with a transform matrix. Shapes are usually referenced by their index, so you should track which shape has a given index.

methods.name: body_apply_impulse
methods.description: Add a positioned impulse to the applied force and torque. Both the force and the offset from the body origin are in global coordinates.

methods.name: body_attach_object_instance_id
methods.description: Assign the area to a descendant of [Object], so it can exist in the node tree.

methods.name: body_clear_shapes
methods.description: Remove all shapes from a body.

methods.name: body_create
methods.description: Create a physics body. The first parameter can be any value from constants BODY_MODE*, for the type of body created. Additionally, the body can be created in sleeping state to save processing time.

methods.name: body_get_collision_layer
methods.description: Return the physics layer or layers a body belongs to.

methods.name: body_get_collision_mask
methods.description: Return the physics layer or layers a body can collide with.

methods.name: body_get_continuous_collision_detection_mode
methods.description: Return the continuous collision detection mode.

methods.name: body_get_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Return the maximum contacts that can be reported. See [method body_set_max_contacts_reported].

methods.name: body_get_mode
methods.description: Return the body mode.

methods.name: body_get_object_instance_id
methods.description: Get the instance ID of the object the area is assigned to.

methods.name: body_get_param
methods.description: Return the value of a body parameter.

methods.name: body_get_shape
methods.description: Return the [RID] of the nth shape of a body.

methods.name: body_get_shape_count
methods.description: Return the number of shapes assigned to a body.

methods.name: body_get_shape_metadata
methods.description: Return the metadata of a shape of a body.

methods.name: body_get_shape_transform
methods.description: Return the transform matrix of a body shape.

methods.name: body_get_space
methods.description: Return the [RID] of the space assigned to a body.

methods.name: body_get_state
methods.description: Return a body state.

methods.name: body_is_omitting_force_integration
methods.description: Return whether a body uses a callback function to calculate its own physics (see [method body_set_force_integration_callback]).

methods.name: body_remove_collision_exception
methods.description: Remove a body from the list of bodies exempt from collisions.

methods.name: body_remove_shape
methods.description: Remove a shape from a body. The shape is not deleted, so it can be reused afterwards.

methods.name: body_set_axis_velocity
methods.description: Set an axis velocity. The velocity in the given vector axis will be set as the given vector length. This is useful for jumping behavior.

methods.name: body_set_collision_layer
methods.description: Set the physics layer or layers a body belongs to.

methods.name: body_set_collision_mask
methods.description: Set the physics layer or layers a body can collide with.

methods.name: body_set_continuous_collision_detection_mode
methods.description:
Set the continuous collision detection mode from any of the CCD_MODE_* constants.
				Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will collide, instead of moving it and correcting its movement if it collided.

methods.name: body_set_force_integration_callback
methods.description: Set the function used to calculate physics for an object, if that object allows it (see [method body_set_omit_force integration]).

methods.name: body_set_max_contacts_reported
methods.description: Set the maximum contacts to report. Bodies can keep a log of the contacts with other bodies, this is enabled by setting the maximum amount of contacts reported to a number greater than 0.

methods.name: body_set_mode
methods.description: Set the body mode, from one of the constants BODY_MODE*.

methods.name: body_set_omit_force_integration
methods.description: Set whether a body uses a callback function to calculate its own physics (see [method body_set_force_integration_callback]).

methods.name: body_set_param
methods.description: Set a body parameter (see BODY_PARAM* constants).

methods.name: body_set_shape
methods.description: Substitute a given body shape by another. The old shape is selected by its index, the new one by its [RID].

methods.name: body_set_shape_metadata
methods.description: Set metadata of a shape within a body. This metadata is different from [method Object.set_meta], and can be retrieved on shape queries.

methods.name: body_set_shape_transform
methods.description: Set the transform matrix for a body shape.

methods.name: body_set_space
methods.description: Assign a space to the body (see [method create_space]).

methods.name: body_set_state
methods.description: Set a body state (see BODY_STATE* constants).

methods.name: body_test_motion
methods.description: Return whether a body can move from a given point in a given direction. Apart from the boolean return value, a [Physics2DTestMotionResult] can be passed to return additional information in.

methods.name: damped_spring_joint_create
methods.description: Create a damped spring joint between two bodies. If not specified, the second body is assumed to be the joint itself.

methods.name: damped_string_joint_get_param
methods.description: Return the value of a damped spring joint parameter.

methods.name: damped_string_joint_set_param
methods.description: Set a damped spring joint parameter. Parameters are explained in the DAMPED_STRING* constants.

methods.name: free_rid
methods.description: Destroy any of the objects created by Physics2DServer. If the [RID] passed is not one of the objects that can be created by Physics2DServer, an error will be sent to the console.

methods.name: get_process_info
methods.description: Return information about the current state of the 2D physics engine. The states are listed under the INFO_* constants.

methods.name: groove_joint_create
methods.description: Create a groove joint between two bodies. If not specified, the bodyies are assumed to be the joint itself.

methods.name: joint_get_param
methods.description: Return the value of a joint parameter.

methods.name: joint_get_type
methods.description: Return the type of a joint (see JOINT_* constants).

methods.name: joint_set_param
methods.description: Set a joint parameter. Parameters are explained in the JOINT_PARAM* constants.

methods.name: pin_joint_create
methods.description: Create a pin joint between two bodies. If not specified, the second body is assumed to be the joint itself.

methods.name: set_active
methods.description: Activate or deactivate the 2D physics engine.

methods.name: shape_create
methods.description: Create a shape of type SHAPE_*. Does not assign it to a body or an area. To do so, you must use [method area_set_shape] or [method body_set_shape].

methods.name: shape_get_data
methods.description: Return the shape data.

methods.name: shape_get_type
methods.description: Return the type of shape (see SHAPE_* constants).

methods.name: shape_set_data
methods.description: Set the shape data that defines its shape and size. The data to be passed depends on the kind of shape created [method shape_get_type].

methods.name: space_create
methods.description: Create a space. A space is a collection of parameters for the physics engine that can be assigned to an area or a body. It can be assigned to an area with [method area_set_space], or to a body with [method body_set_space].

methods.name: space_get_direct_state
methods.description: Return the state of a space, a [Physics2DDirectSpaceState]. This object can be used to make collision/intersection queries.

methods.name: space_get_param
methods.description: Return the value of a space parameter.

methods.name: space_is_active
methods.description: Return whether the space is active.

methods.name: space_set_active
methods.description: Mark a space as active. It will not have an effect, unless it is assigned to an area or body.

methods.name: space_set_param
methods.description: Set the value for a space parameter. A list of available parameters is on the SPACE_PARAM_* constants.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_CONTACT_RECYCLE_RADIUS
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum distance a pair of bodies has to move before their collision status has to be recalculated.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_CONTACT_MAX_SEPARATION
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum distance a shape can be from another before they are considered separated.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_BODY_MAX_ALLOWED_PENETRATION
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum distance a shape can penetrate another shape before it is considered a collision.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_BODY_TIME_TO_SLEEP
constants.description: Constant to set/get the maximum time of activity. A body marked as potentially inactive for both linear and angular velocity will be put to sleep after this time.

constants.name: SPACE_PARAM_CONSTRAINT_DEFAULT_BIAS
constants.description: Constant to set/get the default solver bias for all physics constraints. A solver bias is a factor controlling how much two objects "rebound", after violating a constraint, to avoid leaving them in that state because of numerical imprecision.

constants.name: SHAPE_LINE
constants.description: This is the constant for creating line shapes. A line shape is an infinite line with an origin point, and a normal. Thus, it can be used for front/behind checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_SEGMENT
constants.description: This is the constant for creating segment shapes. A segment shape is a line from a point A to a point B. It can be checked for intersections.

constants.name: SHAPE_CIRCLE
constants.description: This is the constant for creating circle shapes. A circle shape only has a radius. It can be used for intersections and inside/outside checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_RECTANGLE
constants.description: This is the constant for creating rectangle shapes. A rectangle shape is defined by a width and a height. It can be used for intersections and inside/outside checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_CAPSULE
constants.description: This is the constant for creating capsule shapes. A capsule shape is defined by a radius and a length. It can be used for intersections and inside/outside checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_CONVEX_POLYGON
constants.description: This is the constant for creating convex polygon shapes. A polygon is defined by a list of points. It can be used for intersections and inside/outside checks. Unlike the method [method CollisionPolygon2D.set_polygon], polygons modified with [method shape_set_data] do not verify that the points supplied form, in fact, a convex polygon.

constants.name: SHAPE_CONCAVE_POLYGON
constants.description: This is the constant for creating concave polygon shapes. A polygon is defined by a list of points. It can be used for intersections checks, but not for inside/outside checks.

constants.name: SHAPE_CUSTOM
constants.description: This constant is used internally by the engine. Any attempt to create this kind of shape results in an error.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get gravity strength in an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_VECTOR
constants.description: Constant to set/get gravity vector/center in an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_IS_POINT
constants.description: Constant to set/get whether the gravity vector of an area is a direction, or a center point.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_DISTANCE_SCALE
constants.description: Constant to set/get the falloff factor for point gravity of an area. The greater this value is, the faster the strength of gravity decreases with the square of distance.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_POINT_ATTENUATION
constants.description: This constant was used to set/get the falloff factor for point gravity. It has been superseded by AREA_PARAM_GRAVITY_DISTANCE_SCALE.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_LINEAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get the linear dampening factor of an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_ANGULAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get the angular dampening factor of an area.

constants.name: AREA_PARAM_PRIORITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get the priority (order of processing) of an area.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_DISABLED
constants.description: This area does not affect gravity/damp. These are generally areas that exist only to detect collisions, and objects entering or exiting them.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_COMBINE
constants.description: This area adds its gravity/damp values to whatever has been calculated so far. This way, many overlapping areas can combine their physics to make interesting effects.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_COMBINE_REPLACE
constants.description: This area adds its gravity/damp values to whatever has been calculated so far. Then stops taking into account the rest of the areas, even the default one.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_REPLACE
constants.description: This area replaces any gravity/damp, even the default one, and stops taking into account the rest of the areas.

constants.name: AREA_SPACE_OVERRIDE_REPLACE_COMBINE
constants.description: This area replaces any gravity/damp calculated so far, but keeps calculating the rest of the areas, down to the default one.

constants.name: BODY_MODE_STATIC
constants.description: Constant for static bodies.

constants.name: BODY_MODE_KINEMATIC
constants.description: Constant for kinematic bodies.

constants.name: BODY_MODE_RIGID
constants.description: Constant for rigid bodies.

constants.name: BODY_MODE_CHARACTER
constants.description: Constant for rigid bodies in character mode. In this mode, a body can not rotate, and only its linear velocity is affected by physics.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_BOUNCE
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's bounce factor.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_FRICTION
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's friction.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_MASS
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's mass.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_INERTIA
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's inertia.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_GRAVITY_SCALE
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's gravity multiplier.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_LINEAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's linear dampening factor.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_ANGULAR_DAMP
constants.description: Constant to set/get a body's angular dampening factor.

constants.name: BODY_PARAM_MAX
constants.description: This is the last ID for body parameters. Any attempt to set this property is ignored. Any attempt to get it returns 0.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_TRANSFORM
constants.description: Constant to set/get the current transform matrix of the body.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_LINEAR_VELOCITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get the current linear velocity of the body.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_ANGULAR_VELOCITY
constants.description: Constant to set/get the current angular velocity of the body.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_SLEEPING
constants.description: Constant to sleep/wake up a body, or to get whether it is sleeping.

constants.name: BODY_STATE_CAN_SLEEP
constants.description: Constant to set/get whether the body can sleep.

constants.name: JOINT_PIN
constants.description: Constant to create pin joints.

constants.name: JOINT_GROOVE
constants.description: Constant to create groove joints.

constants.name: JOINT_DAMPED_SPRING
constants.description: Constant to create damped spring joints.

constants.name: DAMPED_STRING_REST_LENGTH
constants.description: Set the resting length of the spring joint. The joint will always try to go to back this length when pulled apart.

constants.name: DAMPED_STRING_STIFFNESS
constants.description: Set the stiffness of the spring joint. The joint applies a force equal to the stiffness times the distance from its resting length.

constants.name: DAMPED_STRING_DAMPING
constants.description: Set the damping ratio of the spring joint. A value of 0 indicates an undamped spring, while 1 causes the system to reach equilibrium as fast as possible (critical damping).

constants.name: CCD_MODE_DISABLED
constants.description: Disables continuous collision detection. This is the fastest way to detect body collisions, but can miss small, fast-moving objects.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_CAST_RAY
constants.description: Enables continuous collision detection by raycasting. It is faster than shapecasting, but less precise.

constants.name: CCD_MODE_CAST_SHAPE
constants.description: Enables continuous collision detection by shapecasting. It is the slowest CCD method, and the most precise.

constants.name: AREA_BODY_ADDED
constants.description: The value of the first parameter and area callback function receives, when an object enters one of its shapes.

constants.name: AREA_BODY_REMOVED
constants.description: The value of the first parameter and area callback function receives, when an object exits one of its shapes.

constants.name: INFO_ACTIVE_OBJECTS
constants.description: Constant to get the number of objects that are not sleeping.

constants.name: INFO_COLLISION_PAIRS
constants.description: Constant to get the number of possible collisions.

constants.name: INFO_ISLAND_COUNT
constants.description: Constant to get the number of space regions where a collision could occur.

VisualScriptCondition.name: VisualScriptCondition
VisualScriptCondition.brief_description: A Visual Script node which branches the flow.
VisualScriptCondition.description:
A Visual Script node that checks a [bool] input port. If [code]true[/code] it will exit via the true sequence port. If [code]false[/code] it will exit via the "false" sequence port. After exiting either, it exits via the done port. Sequence ports may be left disconnected.
		[b]Input Ports:[/b]
		- Sequence: [code]if (cond) is[/code]
		- Data (boolean): [code]cond[/code]
		[b]Output Ports:[/b]
		- Sequence: [code]true[/code]
		- Sequence: [code]false[/code]
