@GDScript.name: @GDScript
@GDScript.description: This contains the list of built-in gdscript functions. Mostly math functions and other utilities. Everything else is expanded by objects.

methods.name: Color8
methods.description:
Returns a 32 bit color with red, green, blue and alpha channels. Each channel has 8 bits of information ranging from 0 to 255.
				[code]r8[/code] red channel
				[code]g8[/code] green channel
				[code]b8[/code] blue channel
				[code]a8[/code] alpha channel
				[codeblock]
				red = Color8(255, 0, 0)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: ColorN
methods.description:
Returns color [code]name[/code] with [code]alpha[/code] ranging from 0 to 1. Note: [code]name[/code] is defined in color_names.inc.
				[codeblock]
				red = ColorN('red')
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: abs
methods.description:
Returns the absolute value of parameter [code]s[/code]  (i.e. unsigned value, works for integer and float).
				[codeblock]
				# a is 1
				a = abs(-1)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: acos
methods.description:
Returns the arc cosine of [code]s[/code] in radians. Use to get the angle of cosine [code]s[/code].
				[codeblock]
				# c is 0.523599 or 30 degrees if converted with rad2deg(s)
				c = acos(0.866025)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: asin
methods.description:
Returns the arc sine of [code]s[/code] in radians. Use to get the angle of sine [code]s[/code].
				[codeblock]
				# s is 0.523599 or 30 degrees if converted with rad2deg(s)
				s = asin(0.5)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: assert
methods.description:
Assert that the [code]condition[/code] is true. If the [code]condition[/code] is false a fatal error is generated and the program is halted. Useful for debugging to make sure a value is always true.
				[codeblock]
				# Speed should always be between 0 and 20
				speed = -10
				assert(speed < 20) # Is true and program continues
				assert(speed >= 0) # Is false and program stops
				assert(speed >= 0 && speed < 20) # Or combined
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: atan
methods.description:
Returns the arc tangent of [code]s[/code] in radians. Use it to get the angle from an angle's tangent in trigonometry: [code]atan(tan(angle)) == angle[/code].
				The method cannot know in which quadrant the angle should fall. See [method atan2] if you always want an exact angle.
				[codeblock]
				a = atan(0.5) # a is 0.463648
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: atan2
methods.description:
Returns the arc tangent of [code]y/x[/code] in radians. Use to get the angle of tangent [code]y/x[/code]. To compute the value, the method takes into account the sign of both arguments in order to determine the quadrant.
				[codeblock]
				a = atan(0,-1) # a is 3.141593
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: bytes2var
methods.description: Decodes a byte array back to a value.

methods.name: ceil
methods.description:
Rounds [code]s[/code] upward, returning the smallest integral value that is not less than [code]s[/code].
				[codeblock]
				i = ceil(1.45)  # i is 2
				i = ceil(1.001) # i is 2
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: char
methods.description:
Returns a character as a String of the given ASCII code.
				[codeblock]
				# a is 'A'
				a = char(65)
				# a is 'a'
				a = char(65+32)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: clamp
methods.description:
Clamps [code]val[/code] and returns a value not less than [code]min[/code] and not more than [code]max[/code].
				[codeblock]
				speed = 1000
				# a is 20
				a = clamp(speed, 1, 20)

				speed = -10
				# a is 1
				a = clamp(speed, 1, 20)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: convert
methods.description:
Converts from a type to another in the best way possible. The [code]type[/code] parameter uses the enum TYPE_* in [@Global Scope].
				[codeblock]
				a = Vector2(1, 0)
				# prints 1
				print(a.length())
				a = convert(a, TYPE_STRING)
				# prints 6
				# (1, 0) is 6 characters
				print(a.length())
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: cos
methods.description:
Returns the cosine of angle [code]s[/code] in radians.
				[codeblock]
				# prints 1 and -1
				print(cos(PI*2))
				print(cos(PI))
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: cosh
methods.description:
Returns the hyperbolic cosine of [code]s[/code] in radians.
				[codeblock]
				# prints 1.543081
				print(cosh(1))
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: db2linear
methods.description: Converts from decibels to linear energy (audio).

methods.name: decimals
methods.description:
Returns the position of the first non-zero digit, after the decimal point.
				[codeblock]
				# n is 2
				n = decimals(0.035)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: dectime
methods.description:
Returns the result of [code]value[/code] decreased by [code]step[/code] * [code]amount[/code].
				[codeblock]
				# a = 59
				a = dectime(60, 10, 0.1))
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: deg2rad
methods.description:
Returns degrees converted to radians.
				[codeblock]
				# r is 3.141593
				r = deg2rad(180)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: dict2inst
methods.description: Converts a previously converted instance to a dictionary, back into an instance. Useful for deserializing.

methods.name: ease
methods.description: Easing function, based on exponent. 0 is constant, 1 is linear, 0 to 1 is ease-in, 1+ is ease out. Negative values are in-out/out in.

methods.name: exp
methods.description:
Raises the Euler's constant [b]e[/b] to the power of [code]s[/code] and returns it. [b]e[/b] has an approximate value of 2.71828.
				[codeblock]
				a = exp(2) # approximately 7.39
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: floor
methods.description:
Rounds [code]s[/code] to the closest smaller integer and returns it.
				[codeblock]
				# a is 2
				a = floor(2.99)
				# a is -3
				a = floor(-2.99)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: fmod
methods.description:
Returns the floating-point remainder of [code]x/y[/code].
				[codeblock]
				# remainder is 1.5
				var remainder = fmod(7, 5.5)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: fposmod
methods.description:
Returns the floating-point remainder of [code]x/y[/code] that wraps equally in positive and negative.
				[codeblock]
				var i = -10;
				while i < 0:
				    prints(i, fposmod(i, 10))
				    i += 1
				[/codeblock]
				Produces:
				[codeblock]
				-10 10
				-9 1
				-8 2
				-7 3
				-6 4
				-5 5
				-4 6
				-3 7
				-2 8
				-1 9
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: funcref
methods.description:
Returns a reference to the specified function [code]funcname[/code] in the [code]instance[/code] node. As functions aren't first-class objects in GDscript, use [code]funcref[/code] to store a [FuncRef] in a variable and call it later.
				[codeblock]
				func foo():
				    return("bar")

				a = funcref(self, "foo")
				print(a.call_func()) # prints bar
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: hash
methods.description:
Returns the integer hash of the variable passed.
				[codeblock]
				print(hash("a")) # prints 177670
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: inst2dict
methods.description:
Returns the passed instance converted to a dictionary (useful for serializing).
				[codeblock]
				var foo = "bar"
				func _ready():
				    var d = inst2dict(self)
				    print(d.keys())
				    print(d.values())
				[/codeblock]
				Prints out:
				[codeblock]
				[@subpath, @path, foo]
				[, res://test.gd, bar]
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: instance_from_id
inverse_lerp
methods.description:
Returns a normalized value considering the given range.
				[codeblock]
				inverse_lerp(3, 5, 4) # returns 0.5
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: is_inf
methods.description: Returns True/False whether [code]s[/code] is an infinity value (either positive infinity or negative infinity).

methods.name: is_nan
methods.description: Returns True/False whether [code]s[/code] is a NaN (Not-A-Number) value.

methods.name: len
methods.description:
Returns length of Variant [code]var[/code]. Length is the character count of String, element count of Array, size of Dictionary, etc. Note: Generates a fatal error if Variant can not provide a length.
				[codeblock]
				a = [1, 2, 3, 4]
				len(a) # returns 4
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: lerp
methods.description:
Linearly interpolates between two values by a normalized value.
				[codeblock]
				lerp(1, 3, 0.5) # returns 2
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: linear2db
methods.description: Converts from linear energy to decibels (audio).

methods.name: load
methods.description:
Loads a resource from the filesystem located at 'path'. Note: resource paths can be obtained by right clicking on a resource in the Assets Panel and choosing "Copy Path".
				[codeblock]
				# load a scene called main located in the root of the project directory
				var main = load("res://main.tscn")
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: log
methods.description:
Natural logarithm. The amount of time needed to reach a certain level of continuous growth. Note: This is not the same as the log function on your calculator which is a base 10 logarithm.
				[codeblock]
				log(10) # returns 2.302585
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: max
methods.description:
Returns the maximum of two values.
				[codeblock]
				max(1,2) # returns 2
				max(-3.99, -4) # returns -3.99
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: min
methods.description:
Returns the minimum of two values.
				[codeblock]
				min(1,2) # returns 1
				min(-3.99, -4) # returns -4
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: nearest_po2
methods.description:
Returns the nearest larger power of 2 for integer [code]val[/code].
				[codeblock]
				nearest_po2(3) # returns 4
				nearest_po2(4) # returns 4
				nearest_po2(5) # returns 8
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: parse_json
methods.description:
Parse JSON text to a Variant (use [method typeof] to check if it is what you expect).
				Be aware that the JSON specification does not define integer or float types, but only a number type. Therefore, parsing a JSON text will convert all numerical values to [float] types.
				[codeblock]
				p = parse_json('["a", "b", "c"]')
				if typeof(p) == TYPE_ARRAY:
				    print(p[0]) # prints a
				else:
				    print("unexpected results")
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: pow
methods.description:
Returns the result of [code]x[/code] raised to the power of [code]y[/code].
				[codeblock]
				pow(2,5) # returns 32
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: preload
methods.description:
Returns a resource from the filesystem that is loaded during script parsing. Note: resource paths can be obtained by right clicking on a resource in the Assets Panel and choosing "Copy Path".
				[codeblock]
				# load a scene called main located in the root of the project directory
				var main = preload("res://main.tscn")
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: print
methods.description:
Converts one or more arguments to strings in the best way possible and prints them to the console.
				[codeblock]
				a = [1,2,3]
				print("a","b",a) # prints ab[1, 2, 3]
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: print_stack
methods.description:
Prints a stack track at code location, only works when running with debugger turned on.
				Output in the console would look something like this:
				[codeblock]
				Frame 0 - res://test.gd:16 in function '_process'
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: printerr
methods.description:
Prints one or more arguments to strings in the best way possible to standard error line.
				[codeblock]
				printerr("prints to stderr")
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: printraw
methods.description:
Prints one or more arguments to strings in the best way possible to console. No newline is added at the end.
				[codeblock]
				printraw("A")
				printraw("B")
				# prints AB
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: prints
methods.description:
Prints one or more arguments to the console with a space between each argument.
				[codeblock]
				prints("A", "B", "C") # prints A B C
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: printt
methods.description:
Prints one or more arguments to the console with a tab between each argument.
				[codeblock]
				printt("A", "B", "C") # prints A       B       C
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: rad2deg
methods.description:
Converts from radians to degrees.
				[codeblock]
				rad2deg(0.523599) # returns 30
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: rand_range
methods.description:
Random range, any floating point value between [code]from[/code] and [code]to[/code].
				[codeblock]
				prints(rand_range(0, 1), rand_range(0, 1)) # prints 0.135591 0.405263
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: rand_seed
methods.description: Random from seed: pass a [code]seed[/code], and an array with both number and new seed is returned. "Seed" here refers to the internal state of the pseudo random number generator. The internal state of the current implementation is 64 bits.

methods.name: randf
methods.description:
Returns a random floating point value between 0 and 1.
				[codeblock]
				randf() # returns 0.375671
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: randi
methods.description:
Returns a random 32 bit integer. Use remainder to obtain a random value between 0 and N (where N is smaller than 2^32 -1).
				[codeblock]
				randi() % 20      # returns random number between 0 and 19
				randi() % 100     # returns random number between 0 and 99
				randi() % 100 + 1 # returns random number between 1 and 100
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: randomize
methods.description:
Randomizes the seed (or the internal state) of the random number generator. Current implementation reseeds using a number based on time.
				[codeblock]
				func _ready():
				    randomize()
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: range
methods.description:
Returns an array with the given range. Range can be 1 argument N (0 to N-1), two arguments (initial, final-1) or three arguments (initial, final-1, increment).
				[codeblock]
				for i in range(4):
				    print(i)
				for i in range(2, 5):
				    print(i)
				for i in range(0, 6, 2):
				    print(i)
				[/codeblock]
				Output:
				[codeblock]
				0
				1
				2
				3

				2
				3
				4

				0
				2
				4
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: range_lerp
methods.description:
Maps a [code]value[/code] from range [code][istart, istop][/code] to [code][ostart, ostop][/code].
				[codeblock]
				range_lerp(75, 0, 100, -1, 1) # returns 0.5
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: round
methods.description:
Returns the integral value that is nearest to [code]s[/code], with halfway cases rounded away from zero.
				[codeblock]
				round(2.6) # returns 3
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: seed
methods.description:
Sets seed for the random number generator.
				[codeblock]
				my_seed = "Godot Rocks"
				seed(my_seed.hash())
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: sign
methods.description:
Returns sign of [code]s[/code] -1 or 1.
				[codeblock]
				sign(-6) # returns -1
				sign(6)  # returns 1
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: sin
methods.description:
Returns the sine of angle [code]s[/code] in radians.
				[codeblock]
				sin(0.523599) # returns 0.5
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: sinh
methods.description:
Returns the hyperbolic sine of [code]s[/code].
				[codeblock]
				a = log(2.0) # returns 0.693147
				sinh(a) # returns 0.75
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: sqrt
methods.description:
Returns the square root of [code]s[/code].
				[codeblock]
				sqrt(9) # returns 3
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: stepify
methods.description: Snaps float value [code]s[/code] to a given [code]step[/code].

methods.name: str
methods.description:
Converts one or more arguments to string in the best way possible.
				[codeblock]
				var a = [10, 20, 30]
				var b = str(a);
				len(a) # returns 3
				len(b) # returns 12
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: str2var
methods.description:
Converts a formatted string that was returned by [method var2str] to the original value.
				[codeblock]
				a = '{ "a": 1, "b": 2 }'
				b = str2var(a)
				print(b['a']) # prints 1
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: tan
methods.description:
Returns the tangent of angle [code]s[/code] in radians.
				[codeblock]
				tan( deg2rad(45) ) # returns 1
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: tanh
methods.description:
Returns the hyperbolic tangent of [code]s[/code].
				[codeblock]
				a = log(2.0) # returns 0.693147
				tanh(a)      # returns 0.6
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: to_json
type_exists
methods.description:
Returns whether the given class exists in [ClassDB].
				[codeblock]
				type_exists("Sprite") # returns true
				type_exists("Variant") # returns false
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: typeof
methods.description:
Returns the internal type of the given Variant object, using the TYPE_* enum in [@Global Scope].
				[codeblock]
				p = parse_json('["a", "b", "c"]')
				if typeof(p) == TYPE_ARRAY:
				    print(p[0]) # prints a
				else:
				    print("unexpected results")
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: validate_json
methods.description:
Checks that [code]json[/code] is valid JSON data. Returns empty string if valid. Returns error message if not valid.
				[codeblock]
				j = to_json([1, 2, 3])
				v = validate_json(j)
				if not v:
				    print("valid")
				else:
				    prints("invalid", v)
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: var2bytes
methods.description: Encodes a variable value to a byte array.

methods.name: var2str
methods.description:
Converts a Variant [code]var[/code] to a formatted string that can later be parsed using [method str2var].
				[codeblock]
				a = { 'a': 1, 'b': 2 }
				print(var2str(a))
				[/codeblock]
				prints
				[codeblock]
				{
				"a": 1,
				"b": 2
				}
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: weakref
methods.description:
Returns a weak reference to an object.
				A weak reference to an object is not enough to keep the object alive: when the only remaining references to a referent are weak references, garbage collection is free to destroy the referent and reuse its memory for something else. However, until the object is actually destroyed the weak reference may return the object even if there are no strong references to it.

methods.name: yield
methods.description:
Stops the function execution and returns the current state. Call [method GDFunctionState.resume] on the state to resume execution. This invalidates the state.
				Returns anything that was passed to the resume function call. If passed an object and a signal, the execution is resumed when the object's signal is emitted.

constants.name: PI
constants.description: Constant that represents how many times the diameter of a circumference fits around its perimeter.

constants.name: INF
constants.description: A positive infinity. (For negative infinity, use -INF).

constants.name: NAN
constants.description:
Macro constant that expands to an expression of type float that represents a NaN.
			The NaN values are used to identify undefined or non-representable values for floating-point elements, such as the square root of negative numbers or the result of 0/0.

CanvasLayer.name: CanvasLayer
CanvasLayer.description: Canvas drawing layer. [CanvasItem] nodes that are direct or indirect children of a [CanvasLayer] will be drawn in that layer. The layer is a numeric index that defines the draw order. The default 2D scene renders with index 0, so a [CanvasLayer] with index -1 will be drawn below, and one with index 1 will be drawn above. This is very useful for HUDs (in layer 1+ or above), or backgrounds (in layer -1 or below).

methods.name: get_layer
methods.description: Return the layer index, determines the draw order, a lower value will be below a higher one.

methods.name: get_offset
methods.description: Return the base offset for this layer (helper).

methods.name: get_rotation
methods.description: Return the base rotation for this layer in radians (helper).

methods.name: get_rotationd
methods.description: Return the base rotation for this layer in degrees.

methods.name: get_scale
methods.description: Return the base scale for this layer (helper).

methods.name: get_transform
methods.description: Return the base transform for this layer.

methods.name: get_world_2d
methods.description: Return the [World2D] used by this layer.

methods.name: set_layer
methods.description: Set the layer index, determines the draw order, a lower value will be below a higher one.

methods.name: set_offset
methods.description: Set the base offset for this layer (helper).

methods.name: set_rotation
methods.description: Set the base rotation for this layer in radians (helper).

methods.name: set_rotationd
methods.description: Set the base rotation for this layer in degrees (helper).

methods.name: set_scale
methods.description: Set the base scale for this layer (helper).

methods.name: set_transform
methods.description: Set the base transform for this layer.

properties.name: layer
properties.description: Layer index for draw order. Lower values are drawn first. Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: offset
properties.description: The layer's base offset.

properties.name: rotation
properties.description: The layer's rotation in degrees.

properties.name: scale
properties.description: The layer's scale.

AudioEffectPitchShift.name: AudioEffectPitchShift
AudioEffectPitchShift.brief_description:
Adds a Pitch shift audio effect to an Audio bus.
		Raises or lowers the pitch of original sound.
AudioEffectPitchShift.description: Allows modulation of pitch independently of tempo. All frequencies can be increased/decreased with minimal effect on transients.

properties.name: pitch_scale
properties.description: Pitch value. Can range from 0 (-1 octave) to 16 (+16 octaves).

AudioEffectReverb.name: AudioEffectReverb
AudioEffectReverb.brief_description:
Adds a Reverb audio effect to an Audio bus.
		Simulates the sound of acoustic environments such as rooms, concert halls, caverns, or an open spaces.
AudioEffectReverb.description: Simulates rooms of different sizes. Its parameters can be adjusted to simulate the sound of a specific room.

properties.name: damping
properties.description: Widens or narrows the stereo image of the reverb tail. 1 means fully widens. Value can range from 0 to 1. Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: dry
properties.description: Output percent of original sound. At 0, only modified sound is outputted. Value can range from 0 to 1. Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: hipass
properties.description: High-pass filter passes signals with a frequency higher than a certain cutoff frequency and attenuates signals with frequencies lower than the cutoff frequency. Value can range from 0 to 1. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: predelay_feedback
properties.description: Output percent of predelay. Value can range from 0 to 1. Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: predelay_msec
properties.description: Time between the original signal and the early reflections of the reverb signal. Default value: [code]150ms[/code].

properties.name: room_size
properties.description: Dimensions of simulated room. Bigger means more echoes. Value can range from 0 to 1. Default value: [code]0.8[/code].

properties.name: spread
properties.description: Defines how reflective the imaginary room's walls are. Value can range from 0 to 1. Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: wet
properties.description: Output percent of modified sound. At 0, only original sound is outputted. Value can range from 0 to 1. Default value: [code]0.5[/code].

TileSet.name: TileSet
TileSet.description:
A TileSet is a library of tiles for a [TileMap]. It contains a list of tiles, each consisting of a sprite and optional collision shapes.
		Tiles are referenced by a unique integer ID.

methods.name: clear
methods.description: Clear all tiles.

methods.name: create_tile
methods.description: Create a new tile which will be referenced by the given ID.

methods.name: find_tile_by_name
methods.description: Find the first tile matching the given name.

methods.name: get_last_unused_tile_id
methods.description: Return the ID following the last currently used ID, useful when creating a new tile.

methods.name: get_tiles_ids
methods.description: Return an array of all currently used tile IDs.

methods.name: remove_tile
methods.description: Remove the tile referenced by the given ID.

methods.name: tile_get_light_occluder
methods.description: Return the light occluder of the tile.

methods.name: tile_get_material
methods.description: Return the material of the tile.

methods.name: tile_get_name
methods.description: Return the name of the tile.

methods.name: tile_get_navigation_polygon
methods.description: Return the navigation polygon of the tile.

methods.name: tile_get_navigation_polygon_offset
methods.description: Return the offset of the tile's navigation polygon.

methods.name: tile_get_occluder_offset
methods.description: Return the offset of the tile's light occluder.

methods.name: tile_get_region
methods.description: Return the tile sub-region in the texture.

methods.name: tile_get_shapes
methods.description: Return the array of shapes of the tile.

methods.name: tile_get_texture
methods.description: Return the texture of the tile.

methods.name: tile_get_texture_offset
methods.description: Return the texture offset of the tile.

methods.name: tile_set_light_occluder
methods.description: Set a light occluder for the tile.

methods.name: tile_set_material
methods.description: Set the material of the tile.

methods.name: tile_set_name
methods.description: Set the name of the tile, for descriptive purposes.

methods.name: tile_set_navigation_polygon
methods.description: Set a navigation polygon for the tile.

methods.name: tile_set_navigation_polygon_offset
methods.description: Set an offset for the tile's navigation polygon.

methods.name: tile_set_occluder_offset
methods.description: Set an offset for the tile's light occluder.

methods.name: tile_set_region
methods.description: Set the tile sub-region in the texture. This is common in texture atlases.

methods.name: tile_set_shapes
methods.description: Set an array of shapes for the tile, enabling physics to collide with it.

methods.name: tile_set_texture
methods.description: Set the texture of the tile.

methods.name: tile_set_texture_offset
methods.description: Set the texture offset of the tile.

Node.name: Node
Node.brief_description: Base class for all the [i]scene[/i] elements.
Node.description:
Nodes are the base bricks with which Godot games are developed. They can be set as children of other nodes, resulting in a tree arrangement. A given node can contain any number of nodes as children (but there is only one scene tree root node) with the requirement that all siblings (direct children of a node) should have unique names.
		Any tree of nodes is called a [i]scene[/i]. Scenes can be saved to the disk and then instanced into other scenes. This allows for very high flexibility in the architecture and data model of the projects. Nodes can optionally be added to groups. This makes it easy to reach a number of nodes from the code (for example an "enemies" group) to perform grouped actions.
		[b]Scene tree:[/b] The [SceneTree] contains the active tree of nodes. When a node is added to the scene tree, it receives the NOTIFICATION_ENTER_TREE notification and its [method _enter_tree] callback is triggered. Children nodes are always added [i]after[/i] their parent node, i.e. the [method _enter_tree] callback of a parent node will be triggered before its child's.
		Once all nodes have been added in the scene tree, they receive the NOTIFICATION_READY notification and their respective [method _ready] callbacks are triggered. For groups of nodes, the [method _ready] callback is called in reverse order, from the children up to the parent nodes.
		It means that when adding a scene to the scene tree, the following order will be used for the callbacks: [method _enter_tree] of the parent, [method _enter_tree] of the children, [method _ready] of the children and finally [method _ready] of the parent (and that recursively for the whole scene).
		[b]Processing:[/b] Nodes can be set to the "process" state, so that they receive a callback on each frame requesting them to process (do something). Normal processing (callback [method _process], toggled with [method set_process]) happens as fast as possible and is dependent on the frame rate, so the processing time [i]delta[/i] is variable. Physics processing (callback [method _physics_process], toggled with [method set_physics_process]) happens a fixed amount of times per second (by default 60) and is useful to link itself to the physics.
		Nodes can also process input events. When set, the [method _input] function will be called for each input that the program receives. In many cases, this can be overkill (unless used for simple projects), and the [method _unhandled_input] function might be preferred; it is called when the input event was not handled by anyone else (typically, GUI [Control] nodes), ensuring that the node only receives the events that were meant for it.
		To keep track of the scene hierarchy (especially when instancing scenes into other scenes), an "owner" can be set for the node with [method set_owner]. This keeps track of who instanced what. This is mostly useful when writing editors and tools, though.
		Finally, when a node is freed with [method free] or [method queue_free], it will also free all its children.
		[b]Networking with nodes:[/b] After connecting to a server (or making one, see [NetworkedMultiplayerENet]) it is possible to use the built-in RPC (remote procedure call) system to easily communicate over the network. By calling [method rpc] with a method name, it will be called locally, and in all connected peers (peers = clients and the server that accepts connections), with behaviour varying depending on the network mode ([method set_network_mode]) on the receiving peer. To identify which [Node] receives the RPC call Godot will use its [NodePath] (make sure node names are the same on all peers).

methods.name: _enter_tree
methods.description:
Called when the node enters the [SceneTree] (e.g. upon instancing, scene changing or after calling [method add_child] in a script). If the node has children, its [method _enter_tree] callback will be called first, and then that of the children.
				Corresponds to the NOTIFICATION_ENTER_TREE notification in [method Object._notification].

methods.name: _exit_tree
methods.description:
Called when the node leaves the [SceneTree] (e.g. upon freeing, scene changing or after calling [method remove_child] in a script). If the node has children, its [method _exit_tree] callback will be called last, after all its children have left the tree.
				Corresponds to the NOTIFICATION_EXIT_TREE notification in [method Object._notification].

methods.name: _input
methods.description: Called when there is a change to input devices. Propagated through the node tree until a Node consumes it.

methods.name: _physics_process
methods.description:
Called during the physics processing step of the main loop. Physics processing means that the frame rate is synced to the physics, i.e. the [code]delta[/code] variable should be constant.
				It is only called if physics processing has been enabled with [method set_physics_process].
				Corresponds to the NOTIFICATION_PHYSICS_PROCESS notification in [method Object._notification].

methods.name: _process
methods.description:
Called during the processing step of the main loop. Processing happens at every frame and as fast as possible, so the [code]delta[/code] time since the previous frame is not constant.
				It is only called if processing has been enabled with [method set_process].
				Corresponds to the NOTIFICATION_PROCESS notification in [method Object._notification].

methods.name: _ready
methods.description:
Called when the node is "ready", i.e. when both the node and its children have entered the scene tree. If the node has children, their [method _ready] callback gets triggered first, and the node will receive the ready notification only afterwards.
				Corresponds to the NOTIFICATION_READY notification in [method Object._notification].

methods.name: _unhandled_input
methods.description: Propagated to all nodes when the previous InputEvent is not consumed by any nodes.

methods.name: add_child
methods.description:
Add a child [Node]. Nodes can have as many children as they want, but every child must have a unique name. Children nodes are automatically deleted when the parent node is deleted, so deleting a whole scene is performed by deleting its topmost node.
				The optional boolean argument enforces creating child nodes with human-readable names, based on the name of the node being instanced instead of its type only.

methods.name: add_to_group
methods.description: Add a node to a group. Groups are helpers to name and organize a subset of nodes, like for example "enemies" or "collectables". A [Node] can be in any number of groups. Nodes can be assigned a group at any time, but will not be added to it until they are inside the scene tree (see [method is_inside_tree]).

methods.name: can_process
methods.description: Return true if the node can process, i.e. whether its pause mode allows processing while the scene tree is paused (see [method set_pause_mode]). Always returns true if the scene tree is not paused, and false if the node is not in the tree. FIXME: Why FAIL_COND?

methods.name: duplicate
methods.description:
Duplicate the node, returning a new [Node].
				You can fine-tune the behavior using the [code]flags[/code], which are based on the DUPLICATE_* constants.

methods.name: find_node
methods.description: Find a descendant of this node whose name matches [code]mask[/code] as in [method String.match] (i.e. case sensitive, but '*' matches zero or more characters and '?' matches any single character except '.'). Note that it does not match against the full path, just against individual node names.

methods.name: get_child
methods.description: Return a child node by its index (see [method get_child_count]). This method is often used for iterating all children of a node.

methods.name: get_child_count
methods.description: Return the amount of child nodes.

methods.name: get_children
methods.description: Return an array of references ([Node]) to the child nodes.

methods.name: get_filename
methods.description: Return a filename that may be contained by the node. When a scene is instanced from a file, it topmost node contains the filename from where it was loaded (see [method set_filename]).

methods.name: get_groups
methods.description: Return an array listing the groups that the node is part of.

methods.name: get_index
methods.description: Get the node index, i.e. its position among the siblings of its parent.

methods.name: get_name
methods.description: Return the name of the node. This name is unique among the siblings (other child nodes from the same parent).

methods.name: get_node
methods.description:
Fetch a node. The [NodePath] must be valid (or else an error will be raised) and can be either the path to child node, a relative path (from the current node to another node), or an absolute path to a node.
				Note: fetching absolute paths only works when the node is inside the scene tree (see [method is_inside_tree]).
				[i]Example:[/i] Assume your current node is Character and the following tree:
				[codeblock]
				/root
				/root/Character
				/root/Character/Sword
				/root/Character/Backpack/Dagger
				/root/MyGame
				/root/Swamp/Alligator
				/root/Swamp/Mosquito
				/root/Swamp/Goblin
				[/codeblock]
				Possible paths are:
				[codeblock]
				get_node("Sword")
				get_node("Backpack/Dagger")
				get_node("../Swamp/Alligator")
				get_node("/root/MyGame")
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: get_owner
methods.description: Get the node owner (see [method set_owner]).

methods.name: get_parent
methods.description: Return the parent node of the current node, or an empty [Node] if the node lacks a parent.

methods.name: get_path
methods.description: Return the absolute path of the current node. This only works if the current node is inside the scene tree (see [method is_inside_tree]).

methods.name: get_path_to
methods.description: Return the relative path from the current node to the specified node in "node" argument. Both nodes must be in the same scene, or else the function will fail.

methods.name: get_pause_mode
methods.description: Return the pause mode (PAUSE_MODE_*) of this Node.

methods.name: get_physics_process_delta_time
methods.description: Return the time elapsed since the last physics-bound frame (see [method _physics_process]). This is always a constant value in physics processing unless the frames per second is changed in [OS].

methods.name: get_position_in_parent
methods.description: Return the order in the node tree branch, i.e. if called by the first child Node, return 0.

methods.name: get_process_delta_time
methods.description: Return the time elapsed (in seconds) since the last process callback. This is almost always different each time.

methods.name: get_tree
methods.description: Return a [SceneTree] that this node is inside.

methods.name: has_node
methods.description: Return whether the node that a given [NodePath] points too exists.

methods.name: is_a_parent_of
methods.description: Return [i]true[/i] if the "node" argument is a direct or indirect child of the current node, otherwise return [i]false[/i].

methods.name: is_greater_than
methods.description: Return [i]true[/i] if "node" occurs later in the scene hierarchy than the current node, otherwise return [i]false[/i].

methods.name: is_in_group
methods.description: Return whether this Node is in the specified group.

methods.name: is_inside_tree
methods.description: Return whether this Node is inside a [SceneTree].

methods.name: is_physics_processing
methods.description: Return true if physics processing is enabled (see [method set_physics_process]).

methods.name: is_processing
methods.description: Return whether processing is enabled in the current node (see [method set_process]).

methods.name: is_processing_input
methods.description: Return true if the node is processing input (see [method set_process_input]).

methods.name: is_processing_unhandled_input
methods.description: Return true if the node is processing unhandled input (see [method set_process_unhandled_input]).

methods.name: move_child
methods.description: Move a child node to a different position (order) amongst the other children. Since calls, signals, etc are performed by tree order, changing the order of children nodes may be useful.

methods.name: print_tree
methods.description: Print the scene to stdout. Used mainly for debugging purposes.

methods.name: propagate_call
methods.description: Calls the method (if present) with the arguments given in "args" on this Node and recursively on all children. If the parent_first argument is true then the method will be called on the current [Node] first, then on all children. If it is false then the children will get called first.

methods.name: propagate_notification
methods.description: Notify the current node and all its children recursively by calling notification() in all of them.

methods.name: queue_free
methods.description: Queues a node for deletion at the end of the current frame. When deleted, all of its children nodes will be deleted as well. This method ensures it's safe to delete the node, contrary to [method Object.free]. Use [method Object.is_queued_for_deletion] to know whether a node will be deleted at the end of the frame.

methods.name: raise
methods.description: Move this node to the top of the array of nodes of the parent node. This is often useful on GUIs ([Control]), because their order of drawing fully depends on their order in the tree.

methods.name: remove_and_skip
methods.description: Remove a node and set all its children as children of the parent node (if exists). All even subscriptions that pass by the removed node will be unsubscribed.

methods.name: remove_child
methods.description: Remove a child [Node]. Node is NOT deleted and will have to be deleted manually.

methods.name: remove_from_group
methods.description: Remove a node from a group.

methods.name: replace_by
methods.description: Replace a node in a scene by a given one. Subscriptions that pass through this node will be lost.

methods.name: request_ready
methods.description: Request that [code]_ready[/code] be called again.

methods.name: rpc
methods.description: Send a remote procedure call request to all peers on the network (and locally), optionally sending additional data as arguments. Call request will be received by nodes with the same [NodePath].

methods.name: rpc_config
methods.description: Change the method's RPC mode (one of RPC_MODE_* constants).

methods.name: rpc_id
methods.description: Send a [method rpc] to a specific peer identified by [i]peer_id[/i].

methods.name: rpc_unreliable
methods.description: Send a [method rpc] using an unreliable protocol.

methods.name: rpc_unreliable_id
methods.description: Send a [method rpc] to a specific peer identified by [i]peer_id[/i] using an unreliable protocol.

methods.name: rset
methods.description: Remotely change property's value on other peers (and locally).

methods.name: rset_config
methods.description: Change the property's RPC mode (one of RPC_MODE_* constants).

methods.name: rset_id
methods.description: Remotely change property's value on a specific peer identified by [i]peer_id[/i].

methods.name: rset_unreliable
methods.description: Remotely change property's value on other peers (and locally) using an unreliable protocol.

methods.name: rset_unreliable_id
methods.description: Remotely change property's value on a specific peer identified by [i]peer_id[/i] using an unreliable protocol.

methods.name: set_filename
methods.description: A node can contain a filename. This filename should not be changed by the user, unless writing editors and tools. When a scene is instanced from a file, it topmost node contains the filename from where it was loaded.

methods.name: set_name
methods.description: Set the name of the [Node]. Name must be unique within parent, and setting an already existing name will cause for the node to be automatically renamed.

methods.name: set_owner
methods.description: Set the node owner. A node can have any other node as owner (as long as a valid parent, grandparent, etc ascending in the tree). When saving a node (using SceneSaver) all the nodes it owns will be saved with it. This allows to create complex SceneTrees, with instancing and subinstancing.

methods.name: set_pause_mode
methods.description: Set pause mode (PAUSE_MODE_*) of this Node.

methods.name: set_physics_process
methods.description: Enables or disables the node's physics (alias fixed framerate) processing. When a node is being processed, it will receive a NOTIFICATION_PHYSICS_PROCESS at a fixed (usually 60 fps, check [OS] to change that) interval (and the [method _physics_process] callback will be called if exists). It is common to check how much time was elapsed since the previous frame by calling [method get_physics_process_delta_time].

methods.name: set_process
methods.description: Enables or disables node processing. When a node is being processed, it will receive a NOTIFICATION_PROCESS on every drawn frame (and the [method _process] callback will be called if exists). It is common to check how much time was elapsed since the previous frame by calling [method get_process_delta_time].

methods.name: set_process_input
methods.description: Enable input processing for node. This is not required for GUI controls! It hooks up the node to receive all input (see [method _input]).

methods.name: set_process_unhandled_input
methods.description: Enable unhandled input processing for node. This is not required for GUI controls! It hooks up the node to receive all input that was not previously handled before (usually by a [Control]). (see [method _unhandled_input]).

signals.name: renamed
signals.description: Emitted when the node is renamed.

signals.name: tree_entered
signals.description: Emitted when Node enters the tree.

signals.name: tree_exited
signals.description: Emitted when Node exits the tree.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_PHYSICS_PROCESS
constants.description: Notification received every frame when the physics process flag is set (see [method set_physics_process]).

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_PROCESS
constants.description: Notification received every frame when the process flag is set (see [method set_process]).

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_PARENTED
constants.description: Notification received when a node is set as a child of another node. Note that this doesn't mean that a node entered the Scene Tree.

constants.name: NOTIFICATION_UNPARENTED
constants.description: Notification received when a node is unparented (parent removed it from the list of children).

constants.name: RPC_MODE_REMOTE
constants.description: Call a method remotely.

constants.name: RPC_MODE_SYNC
constants.description: Call a method both remotely and locally.

constants.name: RPC_MODE_MASTER
constants.description: Call a method if the Node is Master.

constants.name: RPC_MODE_SLAVE
constants.description: Call a method if the Node is Slave.

constants.name: PAUSE_MODE_INHERIT
constants.description: Inherits pause mode from parent. For root node, it is equivalent to PAUSE_MODE_STOP.

constants.name: PAUSE_MODE_STOP
constants.description: Stop processing when SceneTree is paused.

constants.name: PAUSE_MODE_PROCESS
constants.description: Continue to process regardless of SceneTree pause state.

VisualScript.name: VisualScript
VisualScript.brief_description: A script implemented in the Visual Script programming environment.
VisualScript.description:
A script implemented in the  Visual Script programming environment. The script extends the functionality of all objects that instance it.
		[method Object.set_script] extends an existing object, if that object's class matches one of the script's base classes.
		You are most likely to use this class via the Visual Script editor or when writing plugins for it.

methods.name: add_custom_signal
methods.description: Add a custom signal with the specified name to the VisualScript.

methods.name: add_function
methods.description: Add a function with the specified name to the VisualScript.

methods.name: add_node
methods.description: Add a node to a function of the VisualScript.

methods.name: add_variable
methods.description: Add a variable to the VisualScript, optionally giving it a default value or marking it as exported.

methods.name: custom_signal_add_argument
methods.description: Add an argument to a custom signal added with [method add_custom_signal].

methods.name: custom_signal_get_argument_count
methods.description: Get the count of a custom signal's arguments.

methods.name: custom_signal_get_argument_name
methods.description: Get the name of a custom signal's argument.

methods.name: custom_signal_get_argument_type
methods.description: Get the type of a custom signal's argument.

methods.name: custom_signal_remove_argument
methods.description: Remove a specific custom signal's argument.

methods.name: custom_signal_set_argument_name
methods.description: Rename a custom signal's argument.

methods.name: custom_signal_set_argument_type
methods.description: Change the type of a custom signal's argument.

methods.name: custom_signal_swap_argument
methods.description: Swap two of the arguments of a custom signal.

methods.name: data_connect
methods.description: Connect two data ports. The value of [code]from_node[/code]'s [code]from_port[/code] would be fed into [code]to_node[/code]'s [code]to_port[/code].

methods.name: data_disconnect
methods.description: Disconnect two data ports previously connected with [method data_connect].

methods.name: get_function_node_id
methods.description: Returns the id of a function's entry point node.

methods.name: get_function_scroll
methods.description: Returns the position of the center of the screen for a given function.

methods.name: get_node
methods.description: Returns a node given its id and its function.

methods.name: get_node_position
methods.description: Returns a node's position in pixels.

methods.name: get_variable_default_value
methods.description: Returns the default (initial) value of a variable.

methods.name: get_variable_export
methods.description: Returns whether a variable is exported.

methods.name: get_variable_info
methods.description: Returns the info for a given variable as a dictionary. The information includes its name, type, hint and usage.

methods.name: has_custom_signal
methods.description: Returns whether a signal exists with the specified name.

methods.name: has_data_connection
methods.description: Returns whether the specified data ports are connected.

methods.name: has_function
methods.description: Returns whether a function exists with the specified name.

methods.name: has_node
methods.description: Returns whether a node exists with the given id.

methods.name: has_sequence_connection
methods.description: Returns whether the specified sequence ports are connected.

methods.name: has_variable
methods.description: Returns whether a variable exists with the specified name.

methods.name: remove_custom_signal
methods.description: Remove a custom signal with the given name.

methods.name: remove_function
methods.description: Remove a specific function and its nodes from the script.

methods.name: remove_node
methods.description: Remove a specific node.

methods.name: remove_variable
methods.description: Remove a variable with the given name.

methods.name: rename_custom_signal
methods.description: Change the name of a custom signal.

methods.name: rename_function
methods.description: Change the name of a function.

methods.name: rename_variable
methods.description: Change the name of a variable.

methods.name: sequence_connect
methods.description:
Connect two sequence ports. The execution will flow from of [code]from_node[/code]'s [code]from_output[/code] into [code]to_node[/code].
				Unlike [method data_connect], there isn't a [code]to_port[/code], since the target node can have only one sequence port.

methods.name: sequence_disconnect
methods.description: Disconnect two sequence ports previously connected with [method sequence_connect].

methods.name: set_function_scroll
methods.description: Position the center of the screen for a function.

methods.name: set_instance_base_type
methods.description: Set the base type of the script.

methods.name: set_node_position
methods.description: Position a node on the screen.

methods.name: set_variable_default_value
methods.description: Change the default (initial) value of a variable.

methods.name: set_variable_export
methods.description: Change whether a variable is exported.

methods.name: set_variable_info
methods.description: Set a variable's info, using the same format as [method get_variable_info].

signals.name: node_ports_changed
signals.description: Emitted when the ports of a node are changed.

HTTPClient.name: HTTPClient
HTTPClient.description:
Hyper-text transfer protocol client. Supports SSL and SSL server certificate verification.
		Can be reused to connect to different hosts and make many requests.

methods.name: close
methods.description: Cloces the current connection, allows for reusal of [HTTPClient].

methods.name: connect_to_host
methods.description:
Connect to a host. This needs to be done before any requests are sent.
				The host should not have http:// prepended but will strip the protocol identifier if provided.
				verify_host will check the SSL identity of the host if set to true.

methods.name: get_connection
methods.description: Return current connection.

methods.name: get_response_body_length
methods.description: Return the response's body length.

methods.name: get_response_code
methods.description: Return the HTTP status code of the response.

methods.name: get_response_headers
methods.description: Return the response headers.

methods.name: get_response_headers_as_dictionary
methods.description:
Returns all response headers as dictionary where the case-sensitivity of the keys and values is kept like the server delivers it. A value is a simple String, this string can have more than one value where "; " is used as separator.
				Structure: ("key":"value1; value2")
				Example: (content-length:12), (Content-Type:application/json; charset=UTF-8)

methods.name: get_status
methods.description: Returns a STATUS_* enum constant. Need to call [method poll] in order to get status updates.

methods.name: has_response
methods.description: Return whether this [HTTPClient] has a response available.

methods.name: is_blocking_mode_enabled
methods.description: Return whether blocking mode is enabled.

methods.name: is_response_chunked
methods.description: Return whether this [HTTPClient] has a response that is chunked.

methods.name: poll
methods.description: This needs to be called in order to have any request processed. Check results with [method get_status]

methods.name: query_string_from_dict
methods.description:
Generates a GET/POST application/x-www-form-urlencoded style query string from a provided dictionary, e.g.:
				[codeblock]
				var fields = {"username": "user", "password": "pass"}
				String queryString = httpClient.query_string_from_dict(fields)
				returns:= "username=user&password=pass"
				[/codeblock]

methods.name: read_response_body_chunk
methods.description: Reads one chunk from the response.

methods.name: request
request_raw
methods.description:
Sends a raw request to the connected host. The url is what is normally behind the hostname, i.e. in [code]http://somehost.com/index.php[/code], url would be "index.php".
				Headers are HTTP request headers.
				Sends body raw, as a byte array, does not encode it in any way.

methods.name: send_body_data
methods.description: Stub function

methods.name: send_body_text
methods.description: Stub function

methods.name: set_blocking_mode
methods.description: If set to true, execution will block until all data is read from the response.

methods.name: set_connection
methods.description: Set connection to use, for this client.

methods.name: set_read_chunk_size
methods.description: Sets the size of the buffer used and maximum bytes to read per iteration. see [method read_response_body_chunk]

TouchScreenButton.name: TouchScreenButton
TouchScreenButton.description: Button for touch screen devices. You can set it to be visible on all screens, or only on touch devices.

methods.name: get_action
methods.description: Returns the button's action.

methods.name: get_bitmask
methods.description: Returns the button's bitmask.

methods.name: get_shape
methods.description: Returns the button's shape.

methods.name: get_texture
methods.description: Returns the button's texture for the normal state.

methods.name: get_texture_pressed
methods.description: Returns the button's texture for the pressed state.

methods.name: get_visibility_mode
methods.description: Sets the button's visibility mode. See [code]VISIBILITY_*[/code] constants.

methods.name: is_pressed
methods.description: Returns [code]true[/code] if this button is currently pressed.

methods.name: set_action
methods.description: Sets the button's action.

methods.name: set_bitmask
methods.description: Sets the button's [BitMap] bitmask.

methods.name: set_passby_press
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] passby presses are enabled for this button.

methods.name: set_shape
methods.description: Sets the button's shape.

methods.name: set_shape_centered
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the button's shape is centered.

methods.name: set_shape_visible
methods.description: If [code]true[/code] the button's shape is visible.

methods.name: set_texture
methods.description: Sets the button's [Texture] for the normal state.

methods.name: set_texture_pressed
methods.description: Sets the button's [Texture] for the pressed state.

methods.name: set_visibility_mode
methods.description: Sets the button's visibility mode. See the [code]VISIBILITY_*[/code] constants.

signals.name: pressed
signals.description: Emitted when the button is pressed (down).

signals.name: released
signals.description: Emitted when the button is released (up).

constants.name: VISIBILITY_ALWAYS
constants.description: Always visible.

constants.name: VISIBILITY_TOUCHSCREEN_ONLY
constants.description: Visible on touch screens only.

properties.name: action
properties.description: The button's action. Actions can be handled with [InputEventAction].

properties.name: bitmask
properties.description: The button's bitmask.

properties.name: normal
properties.description: The button's texture for the normal state.

properties.name: passby_press
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] passby presses are enabled.

properties.name: pressed
properties.description: The button's texture for the pressed state.

properties.name: shape
properties.description: The button's shape.

properties.name: shape_centered
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the button's shape is centered.

properties.name: shape_visible
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] the button's shape is visible.

properties.name: visibility_mode
properties.description: The button's visibility mode. See [code]VISIBILITY_*[/code] constants.

GrooveJoint2D.name: GrooveJoint2D
GrooveJoint2D.description: Groove constraint for 2D physics. This is useful for making a body "slide" through a segment placed in another.

methods.name: get_initial_offset
methods.description: Set the final offset of the groove on body A.

methods.name: get_length
methods.description: Return the length of the groove.

methods.name: set_initial_offset
methods.description: Set the initial offset of the groove on body A.

methods.name: set_length
methods.description: Set the length of the groove.

@VisualScript.name: @VisualScript
@VisualScript.description: A list of built-in visual script functions, see [VisualScriptBuiltinFunc] and [VisualScript].

AudioEffectEQ6.name: AudioEffectEQ6
AudioEffectEQ6.brief_description:
Adds a 6-band equalizer audio effect to an Audio bus. Gives you control over frequencies from 32 Hz to 10000 Hz.
		Each frequency can be modulated between -60/+24 dB.
AudioEffectEQ6.description:
Frequency bands :
		Band 1 : 32 Hz
		Band 2 : 100 Hz
		Band 3 : 320 Hz
		Band 4 : 1000 Hz
		Band 5 : 3200 Hz
		Band 6 : 10000 Hz

		See also [AudioEffectEQ], [AudioEffectEQ10], [AudioEffectEQ21].

VisualScriptSceneNode.name: VisualScriptSceneNode
VisualScriptSceneNode.description:
A direct reference to a node.
		[b]Input Ports:[/b]
		none
		[b]Output Ports:[/b]
		- Data: [code]node[/code] (obj)

properties.name: node_path
properties.description: The node's path in the scene tree.

GradientTexture.name: GradientTexture
GradientTexture.description: Uses a [Gradient] to fill the texture data, the gradient will be filled from left to right using colors obtained from the gradient, this means that the texture does not necessarily represent an exact copy of the gradient, but instead an interpolation of samples obtained from the gradient at fixed steps (see [method set_width]).

properties.name: gradient
properties.description: The [Gradient] that will be used to fill the texture.

properties.name: width
properties.description: The number of color samples that will be obtained from the [Gradient].

InstancePlaceholder.name: InstancePlaceholder
InstancePlaceholder.brief_description: Placeholder for the root [Node] of a [PackedScene].
InstancePlaceholder.description:
Turning on the option [b]Load As Placeholder[/b] for an instanced scene in the editor causes it to be replaced by an InstacePlaceholder when running the game. This makes it possible to delay actually loading the scene until calling [method replace_by_instance]. This is useful to avoid loading large scenes all at once by loading parts of it selectively.
		The InstancePlaceholder does not have a transform. This causes any child nodes to be positioned relatively to the Viewport from point (0,0), rather than their parent as displayed in the editor. Replacing the placeholder with a scene with a transform will transform children relatively to their parent again.

methods.name: get_instance_path
methods.description: Retrieve the path to the [PackedScene] resource file that is loaded by default when calling [method replace_by_instance].

methods.name: replace_by_instance
methods.description: Replace this placeholder by the scene handed as an argument, or the original scene if no argument is given. As for all resources, the scene is loaded only if it's not loaded already. By manually loading the scene beforehand, delays caused by this function can be avoided.

VisualScriptBuiltinFunc.name: VisualScriptBuiltinFunc
VisualScriptBuiltinFunc.brief_description: A Visual Script node used to call built-in functions.
VisualScriptBuiltinFunc.description:
A built-in function used inside a [VisualScript]. It is usually a math function or an utility function.
		See also [@GDScript], for the same functions in the GDScript language.

constants.name: MATH_SIN
constants.description: Return the sine of the input.

constants.name: MATH_COS
constants.description: Return the cosine of the input.

constants.name: MATH_TAN
constants.description: Return the tangent of the input.

constants.name: MATH_SINH
constants.description: Return the hyperbolic sine of the input.

constants.name: MATH_COSH
constants.description: Return the hyperbolic cosine of the input.

constants.name: MATH_TANH
constants.description: Return the hyperbolic tangent of the input.

constants.name: MATH_ASIN
constants.description: Return the arc sine of the input.

constants.name: MATH_ACOS
constants.description: Return the arc cosine of the input.

constants.name: MATH_ATAN
constants.description: Return the arc tangent of the input.

constants.name: MATH_ATAN2
constants.description: Return the arc tangent of the input, using the signs of both parameters to determine the exact angle.

constants.name: MATH_SQRT
constants.description: Return the square root of the input.

constants.name: MATH_FMOD
constants.description: Return the remainder of one input divided by the other, using floating-point numbers.

constants.name: MATH_FPOSMOD
constants.description: Return the positive remainder of one input divided by the other, using floating-point numbers.

constants.name: MATH_FLOOR
constants.description: Return the input rounded down.

constants.name: MATH_CEIL
constants.description: Return the input rounded up.

constants.name: MATH_ROUND
constants.description: Return the input rounded to the nearest integer.

constants.name: MATH_ABS
constants.description: Return the absolute value of the input.

constants.name: MATH_SIGN
constants.description: Return the sign of the input, turning it into 1, -1, or 0. Useful to determine if the input is positive or negative.

constants.name: MATH_POW
constants.description: Return the input raised to a given power.

constants.name: MATH_LOG
constants.description: Return the natural logarithm of the input. Note that this is not the typical base-10 logarithm function calculators use.

constants.name: MATH_EXP
constants.description: Return [b]e[/b] raised to the power of the input. [b]e[/b] sometimes called "Euler's number" is a mathematical constant whose value is approximately 2.71828.

constants.name: MATH_ISNAN
constants.description: Return whether the input is NaN (Not a Number) or not. NaN is usually produced by dividing 0 by 0, though other ways exist.

constants.name: MATH_ISINF
constants.description: Return whether the input is an infinite floating-point number or not. Infinity is usually produced by dividing a number by 0, though other ways exist.

constants.name: MATH_EASE
constants.description: Easing function, based on exponent. 0 is constant, 1 is linear, 0 to 1 is ease-in, 1+ is ease out. Negative values are in-out/out in.

constants.name: MATH_DECIMALS
constants.description: Return the number of digit places after the decimal that the first non-zero digit occurs.

constants.name: MATH_STEPIFY
constants.description: Return the input snapped to a given step.

constants.name: MATH_LERP
constants.description: Return a number linearly interpolated between the first two inputs, based on the third input. Uses the formula [code]a + (a - b) * t[/code].

constants.name: MATH_DECTIME
constants.description: Return the result of 'value' decreased by 'step' * 'amount'.

constants.name: MATH_RANDOMIZE
constants.description: Randomize the seed (or the internal state) of the random number generator. Current implementation reseeds using a number based on time.

constants.name: MATH_RAND
constants.description: Return a random 32 bits integer value. To obtain a random value between 0 to N (where N is smaller than 2^32 - 1), you can use it with the remainder function.

constants.name: MATH_RANDF
constants.description: Return a random floating-point value between 0 and 1. To obtain a random value between 0 to N, you can use it with multiplication.

constants.name: MATH_RANDOM
constants.description: Return a random floating-point value between the two inputs.

constants.name: MATH_SEED
constants.description: Set the seed for the random number generator.

constants.name: MATH_RANDSEED
constants.description: Return a random value from the given seed, along with the new seed.

constants.name: MATH_DEG2RAD
constants.description: Convert the input from degrees to radians.

constants.name: MATH_RAD2DEG
constants.description: Convert the input from radians to degrees.

constants.name: MATH_LINEAR2DB
constants.description: Convert the input from linear volume to decibel volume.

constants.name: MATH_DB2LINEAR
constants.description: Convert the input from decibel volume to linear volume.

constants.name: LOGIC_MAX
constants.description: Return the greater of the two numbers, also known as their maximum.

constants.name: LOGIC_MIN
constants.description: Return the lesser of the two numbers, also known as their minimum.

constants.name: LOGIC_CLAMP
constants.description: Return the input clamped inside the given range, ensuring the result is never outside it. Equivalent to `min(max(input, range_low), range_high)`

constants.name: LOGIC_NEAREST_PO2
constants.description: Return the nearest power of 2 to the input.

constants.name: OBJ_WEAKREF
constants.description: Create a [WeakRef] from the input.

constants.name: FUNC_FUNCREF
constants.description: Create a [FuncRef] from the input.

constants.name: TYPE_CONVERT
constants.description: Convert between types.

constants.name: TYPE_OF
constants.description: Return the type of the input as an integer. Check [enum Variant.Type] for the integers that might be returned.

constants.name: TYPE_EXISTS
constants.description: Checks if a type is registered in the [ClassDB].

constants.name: TEXT_CHAR
constants.description: Return a character with the given ascii value.

constants.name: TEXT_STR
constants.description: Convert the input to a string.

constants.name: TEXT_PRINT
constants.description: Print the given string to the output window.

constants.name: TEXT_PRINTERR
constants.description: Print the given string to the standard error output.

constants.name: TEXT_PRINTRAW
constants.description: Print the given string to the standard output, without adding a newline.

constants.name: VAR_TO_STR
constants.description: Serialize a [Variant] to a string.

constants.name: STR_TO_VAR
constants.description: Deserialize a [Variant] from a string serialized using [VAR_TO_STR].

constants.name: VAR_TO_BYTES
constants.description: Serialize a [Variant] to a [PoolByteArray].

constants.name: BYTES_TO_VAR
constants.description: Deserialize a [Variant] from a [PoolByteArray] serialized using [VAR_TO_BYTES].

constants.name: COLORN
constants.description: Return the [Color] with the given name and alpha ranging from 0 to 1. Note: names are defined in color_names.inc.

constants.name: FUNC_MAX
constants.description: The maximum value the [member function] property can have.

properties.name: function
properties.description: The function to be executed.

Particles2D.name: Particles2D
Particles2D.description:
2D particle node used to create a variety of particle systems and effects. [code]Particles2D[/code] features an emitter that generates some number of particles at a given rate.
		Use the [code]process_material[/code] property to add a [ParticlesMaterial] to configure particle appearance and behavior. Alternatively, you can add a [ShaderMaterial] which will be applied to all particles.

methods.name: get_amount
methods.description: Returns the amount of particles spawned at each emission

methods.name: get_lifetime
methods.description: Gets the amount of seconds that each particle will be visible.

methods.name: get_texture
methods.description: Returns the texture for emitted particles

methods.name: is_emitting
methods.description: Returns whether this emitter is currently emitting or not

methods.name: set_amount
methods.description: Sets the amount of particles spawned at each emission

methods.name: set_emitting
methods.description: If this is set to true then the particle emitter will emit particles, if its false it will not.

methods.name: set_lifetime
methods.description: Sets the amount of seconds that each particle will be visible.

constants.name: DRAW_ORDER_INDEX
constants.description: Particles are drawn in the order emitted.

constants.name: DRAW_ORDER_LIFETIME
constants.description: Particles are drawn in order of remaining lifetime.

properties.name: amount
properties.description: Number of particles to emit.

properties.name: draw_order
properties.description: Particle draw order. Uses [code]DRAW_ORDER_*[/code] values. Default value: [code]DRAW_ORDER_INDEX[/code].

properties.name: emitting
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] particles are being emitted. Default value: [code]true[/code].

properties.name: explosiveness
properties.description: Time ratio between each emission. If [code]0[/code] particles are emitted continuously. If [code]1[/code] all particles are emitted simultaneously. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: h_frames
properties.description: Number of horizontal frames in [code]texture[/code].

properties.name: lifetime
properties.description: Amount of time each particle will exist. Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: local_coords
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] particles use the parent node's coordinate space. If [code]false[/code] they use global coordinates. Default value: [code]true[/code].

properties.name: one_shot
properties.description: If [code]true[/code] only [code]amount[/code] particles will be emitted. Default value: [code]false[/code].

properties.name: process_material
properties.description: [Material] for processing particles. Can be a [ParticlesMaterial] or a [ShaderMaterial].

properties.name: randomness
properties.description: Emission randomness ratio. Default value: [code]0[/code].

properties.name: speed_scale
properties.description: Speed scaling ratio. Default value: [code]1[/code].

properties.name: texture
properties.description: Particle texture. If [code]null[/code] particles will be squares.

properties.name: v_frames
properties.description: Number of vertical frames in [code]texture[/code].

ToolButton.name: ToolButton
ToolButton.description:
This is a helper class to generate a flat [Button] (see [method Button.set_flat]), creating a ToolButton is equivalent to:

		[codeblock]
		var btn = Button.new()
		btn.set_flat(true)
		[/codeblock]

CheckButton.name: CheckButton
CheckButton.description: CheckButton is a toggle button displayed as a check field.

constants.name: FORMAT_8_BITS
constants.description: Audio codec 8 bit.

constants.name: FORMAT_16_BITS
constants.description: Audio codec 16 bit.

constants.name: FORMAT_IMA_ADPCM
constants.description: Audio codec IMA ADPCM.

constants.name: LOOP_DISABLED
constants.description: Audio does not loop.

constants.name: LOOP_FORWARD
constants.description: Audio loops the data between loop_begin and loop_end playing forward only.

constants.name: LOOP_PING_PONG
constants.description: Audio loops the data between loop_begin and loop_end playing back and forth.

properties.name: data
properties.description: Raw audio data.

properties.name: format

properties.name: loop_begin

properties.name: loop_end
properties.description: Loop end in bytes.

properties.name: loop_mode
properties.description: Loop mode. See LOOP_* constants for values.

properties.name: mix_rate
properties.description: The sample rate for mixing this audio.

properties.name: stereo
properties.description: If [code]true[/code], audio is stereo. Default value: [code]false[/code].

methods.name: add_surface_from_arrays
methods.description:
Create a new surface ([method get_surface_count] that will become surf_idx for this.
				Surfaces are created to be rendered using a "primitive", which may be PRIMITIVE_POINTS, PRIMITIVE_LINES, PRIMITIVE_LINE_STRIP, PRIMITIVE_LINE_LOOP, PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLES, PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLE_STRIP, PRIMITIVE_TRIANGLE_FAN. (As a note, when using indices, it is recommended to only use just points, lines or triangles).

methods.name: get_surface_count
methods.description: Return the amount of surfaces that the [ArrayMesh] holds.

methods.name: surface_get_array_index_len
methods.description: Return the length in indices of the index array in the requested surface (see [method add_surface]).

methods.name: surface_get_array_len
methods.description: Return the length in vertices of the vertex array in the requested surface (see [method add_surface]).

methods.name: surface_get_format
methods.description: Return the format mask of the requested surface (see [method add_surface]).

methods.name: surface_get_material
methods.description: Return a [Material] in a given surface. Surface is rendered using this material.

methods.name: surface_get_primitive_type
methods.description: Return the primitive type of the requested surface (see [method add_surface]).

methods.name: surface_remove
methods.description: Remove a surface at position surf_idx, shifting greater surfaces one surf_idx slot down.

methods.name: surface_set_name
methods.description: Set a [Material] for a given surface. Surface will be rendered using this material.

constants.name: NO_INDEX_ARRAY
constants.description: Default value used for index_array_len when no indices are present.

constants.name: ARRAY_WEIGHTS_SIZE
constants.description: Amount of weights/bone indices per vertex (always 4).

constants.name: ARRAY_VERTEX
constants.description: Vertex array (array of [Vector3] vertices).

constants.name: ARRAY_NORMAL
constants.description: Normal array (array of [Vector3] normals).

constants.name: ARRAY_TANGENT
constants.description: Tangent array, array of groups of 4 floats. first 3 floats determine the tangent, and the last the binormal direction as -1 or 1.

constants.name: ARRAY_COLOR
constants.description: Vertex array (array of [Color] colors).

constants.name: ARRAY_TEX_UV
constants.description: UV array (array of [Vector3] UVs or float array of groups of 2 floats (u,v)).

constants.name: ARRAY_TEX_UV2
constants.description: Second UV array (array of [Vector3] UVs or float array of groups of 2 floats (u,v)).

constants.name: ARRAY_BONES
constants.description: Array of bone indices, as a float array. Each element in groups of 4 floats.

constants.name: ARRAY_WEIGHTS
constants.description: Array of bone weights, as a float array. Each element in groups of 4 floats.

constants.name: ARRAY_INDEX
constants.description: Array of integers, used as indices referencing vertices. No index can be beyond the vertex array size.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_VERTEX
constants.description: Array format will include vertices (mandatory).

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_NORMAL

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_TANGENT
constants.description: Array format will include tangents

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_COLOR

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_TEX_UV
constants.description: Array format will include UVs.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_TEX_UV2
constants.description: Array format will include another set of UVs.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_BONES
constants.description: Array format will include bone indices.

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_WEIGHTS

constants.name: ARRAY_FORMAT_INDEX
